'''Miley Ray Cyrus''' ({{IPAc-en|'|m|aɪ|l|i|_|'|s|aɪ|r|ə|s}} {{respell|MY|lee|_|SY|rəs}}, born '''Destiny Hope Cyrus''' on November 23, 1992) is an American singer, songwriter, and actress. Regarded as a [[pop icon]], she has been recognized for her evolving artistry and style, having been dubbed the "Teen Queen" of the 2000s. Cyrus is also cited as one of the few examples of a [[Child actor|child star]] with a successful musical career as an adult.<ref>{{Cite web|last1=Crucchiola|first1=Jordan|last2=Haylock|first2=Zoe|last3=Polk|first3=Milan|date=June 14, 2019|title=Disney and Nickelodeon Stars Gone Pop: A Ranking|url=https://www.vulture.com/2019/06/disney-and-nick-stars-gone-pop-an-updated-power-ranking.html|access-date=October 25, 2019|website=[[Vulture (website)|Vulture]]|archive-date=September 28, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190928113404/https://www.vulture.com/2019/06/disney-and-nick-stars-gone-pop-an-updated-power-ranking.html|url-status=live}}</ref> As the daughter of country singer [[Billy Ray Cyrus]], she emerged as a [[teen idol]] at age 13 as the [[Miley Stewart|lead character]] in the [[Disney Channel]] television series ''[[Hannah Montana]]'' (2006–2011). As Hannah Montana, she achieved success on the [[Billboard charts|''Billboard'' charts]] with two number-one soundtracks and a US top-ten single. 

Cyrus's solo career started with the US number-one [[pop rock]] albums ''[[Hannah Montana 2: Meet Miley Cyrus|Meet Miley Cyrus]]'' (2007) and ''[[Breakout (Miley Cyrus album)|Breakout]]'' (2008), featuring the top-ten singles "[[See You Again (Miley Cyrus song)|See You Again]]" and "[[7 Things]]". The EP ''[[The Time of Our Lives (EP)|The Time of Our Lives]]'' (2009) reached number two in the US while its lead single "[[Party in the U.S.A.]]" became one of the [[List of best-selling singles in the United States|best-selling singles of all time]] in the country and was later certified [[RIAA certification|14-times platinum]] by the [[Recording Industry Association of America|RIAA]]. The ballad "[[The Climb (song)|The Climb]]" also reached number four in the US. Trying to establish a mature image, she explored [[dance-pop]] in ''[[Can't Be Tamed]]'' (2010), which received mixed reviews; its [[Can't Be Tamed (song)|title track]] reached the top-ten in the US. Cyrus later signed with [[RCA Records]] and took a new artistic direction with the [[hip-hop]] and [[contemporary R&B|R&B]]-influenced ''[[Bangerz]]'' (2013). It became her fifth chart-topping album, and yielded the singles "[[We Can't Stop]]" and her first [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] number-one, "[[Wrecking Ball (Miley Cyrus song)|Wrecking Ball]]". She then dabbled in [[experimental music|experimental]] styles on ''[[Miley Cyrus & Her Dead Petz]]'' (2015), embraced [[country pop]] on ''[[Younger Now]]'' (2017), and ventured into [[rock music|rock]] and [[synth-pop]] on'' [[Plastic Hearts]]'' (2020). After signing with [[Columbia Records]] in 2021, Cyrus released her eighth studio album ''[[Endless Summer Vacation]]'' (2023). Its lead single "[[Flowers (Miley Cyrus song)|Flowers]]" topped charts internationally, set various records, and marked her second US number-one. The song won two Grammy Awards including [[Grammy Award for Record of the Year|Record of the Year]], and the album was nominated for [[Grammy Award for Album of the Year|Album of the Year]].

Apart from music, Cyrus starred in the films ''[[Bolt (2008 film)|Bolt]]'' (2008), ''[[Hannah Montana: The Movie]]'' (2009), ''[[The Last Song (2010 film)|The Last Song]]'' (2010), ''[[LOL (2012 film)|LOL]]'' (2012), and ''[[So Undercover]]'' (2013), and appeared briefly in ''[[Guardians of the Galaxy Vol. 2]]'' (2017) and ''[[Drive-Away Dolls]]'' (2024). On television, she produced and appeared in the documentary, ''[[Miley: The Movement]]'' (2013), served as a coach on ''[[The Voice (American TV series)|The Voice]]'' (2016–2017), starred in the "[[Rachel, Jack and Ashley Too]]" episode of ''[[Black Mirror]]'' (2019), hosts the yearly holiday special ''[[Miley's New Year's Eve Party]]'' (2021–present), and starred in and executive produced the documentary concert special ''[[Endless Summer Vacation (Backyard Sessions)]]'' (2023). In 2014, Cyrus founded the non-profit [[Happy Hippie Foundation]], which was supported by the web video series ''[[Backyard Sessions]]'' (2012–2023).

Cyrus has received [[List of awards and nominations received by Miley Cyrus|numerous accolades]], including two [[Grammy Awards]], one [[Brit Award]], five [[Billboard Music Awards|''Billboard'' Music Awards]], three [[MTV Video Music Awards]], and eight ''[[Guinness World Records]]''. She has appeared in [[List of awards and nominations received by Miley Cyrus#Listicles|listicles]] such as the [[Time 100|''Time'' 100]] (2008 and 2014) and [[Forbes 30 Under 30|''Forbes'' 30 Under 30]] (2014 and 2021). ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' ranked her as the ninth-greatest ''Billboard'' 200 female artist and the 62nd greatest artist of all time. Cyrus is the [[List of highest-certified music artists in the United States|eighth-highest-certified female digital singles artist]] by the RIAA,<ref>{{Cite web |title=Gold & Platinum – Top Artists (Digital Singles) |url=https://www.riaa.com/gold-platinum/?tab_active=top_tallies&ttt=TAS |access-date=February 6, 2024 |publisher=[[Recording Industry Association of America]] |archive-date=January 26, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160126081620/http://www.riaa.com/gold-platinum/?tab_active=top_tallies&ttt=TAS |url-status=live }}</ref> and [[Billboard Decade-End|one of the most successful artists of the 2010s]] according to ''Billboard''.<ref>{{cite magazine |date=October 31, 2019 |title=Billboard's Top Artists of the 2010s |url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/decade-end/top-artists |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210511033038/https://www.billboard.com/charts/decade-end/top-artists |archive-date=May 11, 2021 |access-date=February 6, 2024 |magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]}}</ref>

==Early life and career beginnings==
Destiny Hope Cyrus was born November 23, 1992, in [[Franklin, Tennessee]],<ref name=childhood>{{cite web|title=Miley Cyrus Biography |url=http://www.thebiographychannel.co.uk/biographies/miley-cyrus.html |publisher=[[The Biography Channel (UK and Ireland)|The Biography Channel]] |access-date=April 7, 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150512170758/http://www.thebiographychannel.co.uk/biographies/miley-cyrus.html |archive-date=May 12, 2015 |url-status=dead }}</ref> to [[Tish Cyrus|Leticia "Tish" Jean Cyrus]] (née Finley) and country singer [[Billy Ray Cyrus]].<ref name=childhood /> She was born with [[supraventricular tachycardia]], a condition causing an abnormal resting heart rate.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mtv.com/news/1606651/miley-cyrus-opens-up-about-heart-condition/ |title=Miley Cyrus Opens Up About Heart Condition |website=mtv.com |publisher=MTV |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170304192429/http://www.mtv.com/news/1606651/miley-cyrus-opens-up-about-heart-condition/ |archive-date=March 4, 2017 |access-date=March 4, 2017}}</ref> Her birth name, Destiny Hope, expressed her parents' belief that she would accomplish great things. Her parents nicknamed her "Smiley", which they later shortened to "Miley", because she often smiled as an infant.<ref name="signonsandiego">{{cite web|last=Hiltbrand|first=David|url=http://www.utsandiego.com/uniontrib/20060520/news_1c20hannah.html|title=Miley Cyrus braced for Disney stardom|work=[[The San Diego Union-Tribune]]|publisher=Platinum Equity|date=May 20, 2006|access-date=May 30, 2010|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305075515/http://www.sandiegouniontribune.com/uniontrib/20060520/news_1c20hannah.html|archive-date=March 5, 2016}}</ref> In 2008, she legally changed her name to Miley Ray Cyrus; her middle name honors her grandfather, [[U.S. Democratic Party|Democratic]] politician [[Ron Cyrus|Ronald Ray Cyrus]], who was from [[Kentucky]].<ref>{{cite news|last=France | first=Lisa Respers |url=http://edition.cnn.com/2009/SHOWBIZ/08/25/billy.ray.cyrus/|title='Eraserhead' director inspired Billy Ray Cyrus|work=CNN|date=August 25, 2009|access-date=July 21, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170304194018/http://edition.cnn.com/2009/SHOWBIZ/08/25/billy.ray.cyrus/|archive-date=March 4, 2017}}</ref> Cyrus's [[Godparent|godmother]] is singer-songwriter [[Dolly Parton]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://music.yahoo.com/blogs/our-country/dolly-parton-surprising-family-role-just-may-not-205451471.html|title=Dolly Parton Has A Surprising Family Role–That You Just May Not Know About!|last=Geller|first=Wendy|date=January 18, 2013|publisher=[[Yahoo! Music]]|access-date=April 7, 2014|archive-date=September 7, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140907040539/https://music.yahoo.com/blogs/our-country/dolly-parton-surprising-family-role-just-may-not-205451471.html|url-status=live}}</ref>

Against the advice of her father's record company,<ref name="abcnews"/> Cyrus's parents secretly married on December 28, 1993, a year after her birth.<ref name=GQBilly>{{cite web| url = https://www.gq.com/entertainment/celebrities/201103/billy-ray-cyrus-mr-hannah-montana-miley?currentPage=4| last = Heath| first = Chris| title = Mr. Hannah Montana's Achy Broken Heart| date = March 2011| work = [[GQ]]| access-date = September 10, 2017| archive-date = October 6, 2014| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20141006175652/http://www.gq.com/entertainment/celebrities/201103/billy-ray-cyrus-mr-hannah-montana-miley?currentPage=4| url-status = live}}</ref> They had two more children, son Braison and daughter [[Noah Cyrus|Noah]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Miley Cyrus' Brother Hospitalized With Serious Bleeding|url=https://hollywoodreporter.com/news/miley-cyrus-billy-ray-cyrus-braison-bloody-349473|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|access-date=April 7, 2014|date=July 15, 2012|archive-date=June 8, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140608220052/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/miley-cyrus-billy-ray-cyrus-braison-bloody-349473|url-status=live}}</ref> From a previous relationship, her mother has two other children, [[Brandi Cyrus|Brandi]] and [[Trace Cyrus|Trace]].<ref name="adopt">{{cite web |url=https://people.com/archive/cover-story-my-girl-billy-ray-and-miley-cyrus-vol-68-no-1/ |last=Tan |first=Michelle |title=My Girl |date=July 2, 2007 |access-date=March 7, 2019 |work=[[People (magazine)|People]] |archive-date=December 19, 2008 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081219104405/http://www.people.com/people/archive/article/0,,20061306,00.html |url-status=live }}</ref> Her father's first child, Christopher Cody, was born in April 1992<ref name=GQBilly/> and grew up separately with his mother, waitress Kristin Luckey, in [[South Carolina]].<ref name="abcnews">{{cite web|url=https://abcnews.go.com/Primetime/story?id=132388&page=1|title=Once a Country Superstar, He Got Out of the Spotlight for Fatherhood|access-date=August 14, 2008|date=March 13, 2004|publisher=[[The Walt Disney Company]]|work=[[ABC News (United States)|ABC News]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131015215128/http://abcnews.go.com/Primetime/story?id=132388|archive-date=October 15, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/CX991nVO8M8/?igshid=MzRlODBiNWFlZA==|title=Instagram|website=www.instagram.com|accessdate=February 9, 2024}}</ref>

All of Cyrus's maternal siblings are established entertainers. Trace is a vocalist and guitarist for the electronic pop band [[Metro Station (band)|Metro Station]].<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/268332/metro-station-ready-to-roll-with-miley|title=Metro Station Ready To Roll With Miley|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=June 19, 2009|access-date=August 4, 2009|last=Graff|first=Gary|location=[[Detroit]], Michigan|archive-date=April 23, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130423122753/http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/268332/metro-station-ready-to-roll-with-miley|url-status=live}}</ref> Noah is an actress and, along with Braison, models, sings, and is a songwriter.<ref>{{cite magazine |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/8473442/noah-cyrus-good-cry-ep-release-date |title=Noah Cyrus Announces 'Good Cry' EP Release Date |magazine=Billboard |access-date=January 12, 2019 |archive-date=September 5, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180905113246/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/8473442/noah-cyrus-good-cry-ep-release-date |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |first=Brittany |last=Spanos |author-link=Brittany Spanos |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/noah-cyrus-announces-first-headlining-tour-697671/ |title=Noah Cyrus Announces 'The Good Cry' Tour |work=Rollingstone.com |date=July 9, 2018 |access-date=January 12, 2019 |archive-date=February 21, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230221173606/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/noah-cyrus-announces-first-headlining-tour-697671/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=See Miley Cyrus' Brother Braison Make His Modeling Debut|url=http://www.eonline.com/news/366470/see-miley-cyrus-brother-braison-make-his-modeling-debut-first-look-at-the-sexy-pics|publisher=[[E! Online]]|access-date=April 7, 2014|date=November 25, 2013|archive-date=July 23, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140723013955/http://www.eonline.com/news/366470/see-miley-cyrus-brother-braison-make-his-modeling-debut-first-look-at-the-sexy-pics|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BrFyK4llEXI/  |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/iarchive/s/instagram/BrFyK4llEXI |archive-date=December 23, 2021 |url-access=subscription|title=Braison Cyrus on Instagram |work=Instagram.com |access-date=January 12, 2019}}{{cbignore}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://musicmayhemmagazine.com/braison-cyrus-gets-engaged-releases-debut-single-ill-never-leave-you/|title=Braison Cyrus Gets Engaged, Releases Debut Single "I'll Never Leave You"|date=December 8, 2018|website=Music Mayhem Magazine|access-date=October 8, 2019|archive-date=April 12, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190412171814/https://musicmayhemmagazine.com/braison-cyrus-gets-engaged-releases-debut-single-ill-never-leave-you/|url-status=live}}</ref> Brandi was formerly a musician for the [[indie rock]] band Frank + Derol<ref>{{cite web|last=Fisher|first=Luchina|title=5 Things About Miley Cyrus' Sister Brandi|url=https://abcnews.go.com/blogs/entertainment/2013/11/5-things-about-miley-cyrus-sister-brandi/|work=[[ABC News (United States)|ABC News]]|access-date=April 7, 2014|date=November 25, 2013|archive-date=April 11, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140411182952/http://abcnews.go.com/blogs/entertainment/2013/11/5-things-about-miley-cyrus-sister-brandi/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |first=Jocelyn |last=Vena |title=Cyrus And Jonas Siblings Team Up For Miyazaki Movie |work=[[MTV]] Movies Blog |date=April 3, 2009 |access-date=April 4, 2009 |url=http://moviesblog.mtv.com/2009/04/03/cyrus-and-jonas-siblings-team-up-for-miyazaki-movie/ |archive-date=September 7, 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150907211429/http://moviesblog.mtv.com/2009/04/03/cyrus-and-jonas-siblings-team-up-for-miyazaki-movie/ |url-status=dead }}</ref> and is a professional [[disk jockey|DJ]]. The Cyrus farmhouse is located on 500 acres of land outside Nashville.<ref name=":0">{{Cite journal|last=Cyrus|first=Miley|date=September 2017|title=Chillin' at Miley's House|journal=Cosmopolitan|volume=263| issue =  3|page=140}}</ref>

Cyrus attended Heritage Elementary School in Williamson County while she and her family lived in Thompson's Station, Tennessee.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://schools.wcs.edu/InFocus/infocus0708/Issue_10/hannah_montana.htm|title=WCS Teacher Surprises Hannah Montana|publisher=[[Williamson County Schools]]|access-date=May 30, 2010|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20140322225130/http://schools.wcs.edu/InFocus/infocus0708/Issue_10/hannah_montana.htm|archive-date= March 22, 2014}}</ref> When she was cast in ''Hannah Montana,'' the family moved to [[Los Angeles]] and she attended Options for Youth Charter Schools<ref>{{cite interview|last=Cyrus|first=Miley|title=Miley Cyrus|date=July 2007|work=[[PBS Kids]]}}</ref> studying with a private tutor on set.<ref>{{cite news|last=Steinberg|first=Jacques|title=Hannah Montana and Miley Cyrus: A Tale of Two Tweens|work=[[The New York Times]]|date=April 20, 2006|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2006/04/20/arts/television/20cyru.html|access-date=June 9, 2010|archive-date=November 2, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201102050322/https://www.nytimes.com/2006/04/20/arts/television/20cyru.html|url-status=live}}</ref> Raised as a Christian, she was baptized in a [[Southern Baptist]] church before moving to [[Hollywood, Los Angeles|Hollywood]] in 2005.<ref name=baptized>{{cite news|url=http://parade.condenast.com/131365/kevinsessums/miley-cyrus-4/|title=Miley Cyrus: 'I Know Who I Am Now'|author-link=Kevin Sessums|last=Sessums|first=Kevin|work=[[Parade (magazine)|Parade]]|date=March 21, 2010|access-date=October 7, 2011|archive-date=September 7, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140907035857/http://parade.condenast.com/131365/kevinsessums/miley-cyrus-4/|url-status=live}}</ref> She attended church regularly while growing up and wore a [[purity ring]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.foxnews.com/story/2008/07/16/miley-cyrus-wants-to-do-cleaner-sex-and-city/|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140108232216/http://www.foxnews.com/story/2008/07/16/miley-cyrus-wants-to-do-cleaner-sex-and-city/|archive-date=January 8, 2014|title=Miley Cyrus Wants to Do 'Cleaner' 'Sex and the City'|publisher=[[Fox News Channel]]. [[21st Century Fox]]|date=July 16, 2008|access-date=May 30, 2010}}</ref> In 2001, when Cyrus was eight, she and her family moved to [[Toronto, Ontario, Canada|Toronto, Canada]], while her father filmed the television series ''[[Doc (2001 TV series)|Doc]]''.<ref>{{cite interview|url=http://www.tribute.ca/features/hannahmontana|title=Miley Cyrus aka Hannah Montana Interview|first=Miley|last=Cyrus|interviewer=Bonnie Laufer|work=[[Tribute (magazine)|Tribute]]|access-date=June 1, 2010|archive-date=January 23, 2010|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100123050205/http://www.tribute.ca/features/hannahmontana/|url-status=live}}</ref> After Billy Ray Cyrus took her to see a 2001 [[Mirvish Productions|Mirvish production]] of ''[[Mamma Mia! (musical)|Mamma Mia!]]'' at the [[Royal Alexandra Theatre]], Miley Cyrus grabbed his arm and told him, "This is what I want to do, daddy. I want to be an actress."<ref>{{cite news|last=Ouzounian|first=Richard|url=https://www.thestar.com/entertainment/2009/04/04/miley_cyrus_teen_of_all_media.html|title=Miley Cyrus: Teen of all media|website=[[Toronto Star]]|date=April 4, 2009|access-date=May 30, 2010|archive-date=February 21, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230221173606/https://www.thestar.com/entertainment/2009/04/04/miley_cyrus_teen_of_all_media.html|url-status=live}}</ref> She began to take singing and acting lessons at the Armstrong Acting Studio in Toronto.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cineplex.com/Movies/FamousNews/FamousMagazine/March%202009.aspx?FamousArticles=26633|title=Famous Teens: Miley Cyrus|access-date=April 13, 2009|first=Marni|last=Weisz|date=March 1, 2009|publisher=[[Cineplex Entertainment]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110221002409/http://www.cineplex.com/Movies/FamousNews/FamousMagazine/March%202009.aspx?FamousArticles=26633|archive-date=February 21, 2011 }}</ref>

Cyrus's first acting role was as Kylie in her father's television series ''Doc''.<ref name="signonsandiego" /> In 2003, she received credit under her birth name for her role as "Young Ruthie" in [[Tim Burton]]'s ''[[Big Fish]]''.<ref name="instanthit" /> During this period she auditioned with [[Taylor Lautner]] for the feature film ''[[The Adventures of Sharkboy and Lavagirl in 3-D]].'' Although she was one of two finalists for the role, she chose to appear in ''Hannah Montana'' instead.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://b96.cbslocal.com/2009/10/30/interview-with-miley-cyrus/|title=Interview with Miley Cyrus|work=B96|access-date=March 21, 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120724021857/http://b96.cbslocal.com/2009/10/30/interview-with-miley-cyrus/|archive-date=July 24, 2012|url-status=dead}}</ref> Her mother took on the role of Miley's manager and worked to acquire a team to build her daughter's career.<ref>{{cite news|first=Allyssia|last=Alleyne|title=Inside Miley Cyrus' exuberant Los Angeles home -- designed by her mother|url=https://www.cnn.com/style/article/inside-miley-cyrus-los-angeles-home-architectural-digest/index.html|access-date=May 4, 2021|website=CNN|archive-date=May 3, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210503123852/https://www.cnn.com/style/article/inside-miley-cyrus-los-angeles-home-architectural-digest/index.html|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="hollywoodreporter">{{cite news|last=Swertlow|first=Frank|url=https://hollywoodreporter.com/news/showbiz-kids-bring-talent-toronto-88796|title=Showbiz Kids|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=October 26, 2009|access-date=June 1, 2010|archive-date=October 25, 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121025002030/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/showbiz-kids-bring-talent-toronto-88796|url-status=live}}</ref> Cyrus signed with Mitchell Gossett, director of the youth division at Cunningham Escott Slevin Doherty.<ref name="4deal">{{cite news|first=Tara|last=McNamara|url=https://variety.com/article/VR1117973379.html?categoryid=2721&cs=1|title=Director of youth at Cunningham eyes multitalents|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=October 4, 2007|access-date=May 30, 2010|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071011010500/http://variety.com/article/VR1117973379.html?categoryid=2721&cs=1|archive-date=October 11, 2007}}</ref> Gossett is often credited with "discovering" Cyrus and played a key role in her auditioning for ''Hannah Montana''.<ref>{{cite news|last=Kit|first=Borys|url=https://hollywoodreporter.com/news/miley-cyrus-agent-moves-uta-110832|title=Miley Cyrus' agent moves to UTA|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=May 4, 2008|access-date=May 30, 2010|archive-date=October 25, 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121025002057/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/miley-cyrus-agent-moves-uta-110832|url-status=live}}</ref> She later signed with Jason Morey of Morey Management Group to handle her music career; Dolly Parton steered her to him.<ref name="hollywoodreporter" /> She hired her father's finance manager as part of her team.<ref name="hollywoodreporter" />

== Career ==

=== 2006–2009: ''Hannah Montana'' and early musical releases ===
[[File:Miley Cyrus Concert.jpg|thumb|upright|Cyrus performing on her [[Best of Both Worlds Tour]] in 2007]]

Cyrus auditioned for the [[Disney Channel]] television series ''[[Hannah Montana]]'' when she was thirteen years old.<ref name=montana>{{cite book|last=Cyrus|first=Miley|title=''Miles to Go''|url=https://archive.org/details/milestogo00mile|url-access=registration|publisher=[[Disney Hyperion]]|year=2009|page=[https://archive.org/details/milestogo00mile/page/7 7]|isbn=978-1-4231-1992-0}}</ref> She auditioned for the role of the title character's best friend, but was called to audition for the [[Miley Stewart|lead role]] instead seeing her performance.<ref name=montana /> Despite being denied the part at first because she was "too small and too young" for the role,<ref>{{cite news|last=Oldenburg|first=Ann|website=[[USA Today]]|date=March 23, 2006|url=http://usatoday30.usatoday.com/life/television/news/2006-03-23-miley-cyrus_x.htm|title=Lifelong work pays off, says Miley Cyrus, 13.|access-date=October 1, 2006|archive-date=April 28, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230428190048/https://usatoday30.usatoday.com/life/television/news/2006-03-23-miley-cyrus_x.htm|url-status=live}}</ref> she was later cast as the lead because of her singing and goofy acting abilities.<ref name="especial">{{Cite episode|title=Miley Cyrus|series=E! Special|series-link=E!|credits=Cyrus, Miley; Cyrus, Tish; Cyrus, Billy Ray; Patterson, Lesley; Tan, Michelle|network=[[E!]]|airdate=April 8, 2009}}</ref> The series premiered in March 2006 to the largest audience for a Disney Channel program<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tvguide.com/celebrities/miley-cyrus/bio/259138|title=Miley Cyrus Biography|work=[[TV Guide]]|access-date=May 30, 2010|archive-date=September 23, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200923210541/https://www.tvguide.com/celebrities/miley-cyrus/bio/259138/|url-status=dead}}</ref> and quickly ranked among the highest-rated series on basic cable.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dallasnews.com/sharedcontent/dws/ent/stories/DN-hannah_1024gl.ART.State.Edition2.422c049.html|title=Disney marketers making most of 'Hannah Montana'|website=[[The Dallas Morning News]]|date=October 25, 2007|access-date=May 30, 2010|last=Ostrow|first=Joanne|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080116154513/http://www.dallasnews.com/sharedcontent/dws/ent/stories/DN-hannah_1024gl.ART.State.Edition2.422c049.html|archive-date=January 16, 2008}}</ref> The success of the series led to Cyrus' being labeled a "[[teen idol]]."<ref name="instanthit">{{cite news|last=Hiscock|first=John|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/film/7521454/Miley-Cyrus-interview-Im-going-to-hire-an-acting-coach.html |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/archive/20220110/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/film/7521454/Miley-Cyrus-interview-Im-going-to-hire-an-acting-coach.html |archive-date=January 10, 2022 |url-access=subscription |url-status=live|title=Miley Cyrus interview: I'm going to hire an acting coach|website=[[The Daily Telegraph]]|date=March 25, 2010|access-date=May 30, 2010}}{{cbignore}}</ref><ref name=TIMEmag>{{cite magazine|last=Poniewozik|first=James|url=http://content.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,1673286,00.html|title=Hurricane Hannah|magazine=[[Time (magazine)|Time]]|date=October 18, 2007|access-date=May 5, 2010|archive-date=February 21, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230221183537/https://content.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,1673286,00.html|url-status=live}}</ref> She toured with [[The Cheetah Girls (group)|the Cheetah Girls]] as Hannah Montana in September 2006 and performed songs from the show's first season.<ref>{{cite magazine|last=McDowell|first=Jeanne|title=A Disney Star Is Born|url=http://content.time.com/time/arts/article/0,8599,1564394,00.html|magazine=[[Time (magazine)|Time]]|access-date=April 5, 2014|date=November 30, 2006|archive-date=October 25, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201025055711/http://content.time.com/time/arts/article/0,8599,1564394,00.html|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Walt Disney Records]] released a [[Hannah Montana (soundtrack)|soundtrack credited to Cyrus's character]] in October of that year.<ref name="AllMusic">{{cite web|url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/hannah-montana-mw0000421737|title=Hannah Montana - Hannah Montana|first=Heather|last=Phares|publisher=[[AllMusic]]. [[Rovi Corporation]]|access-date=January 20, 2014|archive-date=January 10, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140110161906/http://www.allmusic.com/album/hannah-montana-mw0000421737|url-status=live}}</ref> The record was both a critical and commercial success, topping the [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]] chart in the United States; it went on to sell over three{{nbsp}}million copies worldwide.<ref>{{cite news |last=LaPorte |first=Nicole |url=http://www.thedailybeast.com/articles/2010/06/18/have-the-jonas-brothers-been-eclipsed-by-justin-bieber.html |title=Have the Jonas Brothers Been Eclipsed by Justin Bieber? |newspaper=The Daily Beast |date=June 17, 2010 |access-date=April 29, 2013 |archive-date=January 5, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170105142129/http://www.thedailybeast.com/articles/2010/06/18/have-the-jonas-brothers-been-eclipsed-by-justin-bieber.html |url-status=live }}</ref> With the release of the soundtrack, Cyrus became the first act within [[the Walt Disney Company]] to have deals in television, film, consumer products, and music.<ref name=TIMEmag />

Cyrus signed a four-album deal with [[Hollywood Records]] to distribute her non-''Hannah Montana'' soundtrack music.<ref>{{cite web|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180804110348/http://www.alloy.com/entertainment/miley-cyrus-spotlight/|archive-date=August 4, 2018|url-status=dead|url=http://www.crushable.com/2007/11/04/entertainment/miley-cyrus-spotlight/|title=Miley Cyrus – Spotlight|publisher=Defy Media LLC|access-date=July 31, 2016}}</ref> She released the two-disc album ''[[Hannah Montana 2: Meet Miley Cyrus]]'' in June 2007.<ref name=hm2>{{cite web |url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/hannah-montana-2-meet-miley/id257915495 |title=iTunes – Music – Hannah Montana 2 – Meet Miley Cyrus by Hannah Montana & Miley Cyrus |publisher=[[iTunes]] |date=June 26, 2007 |access-date=April 29, 2013 |archive-date=November 11, 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131111003817/https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/hannah-montana-2-meet-miley/id257915495 |url-status=live }}</ref> The first disc was credited as the second soundtrack by "Hannah Montana", while the second disc served as Cyrus's debut studio album.<ref name=hm2 /> The album became her second to reach the top of the ''Billboard'' 200, and has sold over three{{nbsp}}million copies.<ref>{{cite magazine |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/1051137/cyrus-sidesteps-clarkson-to-debut-at-no-1 |title=Cyrus Sidesteps Clarkson To Debut at No. 1 |magazine=Billboard |date=July 4, 2007 |access-date=April 29, 2013 |archive-date=August 19, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200819203909/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/1051137/cyrus-sidesteps-clarkson-to-debut-at-no-1 |url-status=live }}</ref> Months after the release of the project, "[[See You Again (Miley Cyrus song)|See You Again]]" (2007) was released as the lead single from the album.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.co.uk/See-You-Again-2008-Edit/dp/B001E4424Q/ref=sr_1_33?s=music&ie=UTF8&qid=1430294305&sr=1-33|title=See You Again|date=August 21, 2008|access-date=July 31, 2016|website=Amazon.co.uk|archive-date=September 12, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190912172451/https://www.amazon.co.uk/See-You-Again-2008-Edit/dp/B001E4424Q/ref=sr_1_33?s=music&ie=UTF8&qid=1430294305&sr=1-33|url-status=live}}</ref> The song was a commercial success, and has sold over two{{nbsp}}million copies in the United States since its release.<ref name="sales2013">{{cite web|url=http://music.yahoo.com/blogs/chart-watch/week-ending-aug-25-2013-songs-robin-marvin-191212316.html |title=Week Ending Aug. 25, 2013. Songs: Robin & Marvin |first=Paul | last=Grein |work=Chart Watch |date=August 28, 2013 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141222063740/https://www.yahoo.com/music/bp/week-ending-aug-25-2013-songs-robin-marvin-191212316.html |archive-date=December 22, 2014 }}</ref> She collaborated with her father on the single "[[Ready, Set, Don't Go]]" (2007).<ref name="cmt home">{{cite web|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081011124057/http://www.cmt.com/news/country-music/1568875/billy-ray-cyrus-returns-with-new-cd-and-tour.jhtml|archive-date=October 11, 2008|url-status=dead|url=http://www.cmt.com/news/country-music/1568875/billy-ray-cyrus-returns-with-new-cd-and-tour.jhtml|title=Billy Ray Cyrus Returns With New CD and Tour|first=Calvin|last=Gilbert|date=September 5, 2007|work=[[CMT News]]|access-date=October 30, 2009}}</ref> Next Cyrus embarked on her highly successful [[Best of Both Worlds Tour (Miley Cyrus)|Best of Both Worlds Tour]] (2007–08) to promote its release.<ref>{{cite web|title=Miley Cyrus is hottest concert ticket going|url=http://www.today.com/id/21084902/ns/today-today_entertainment/t/miley-cyrus-hottest-concert-ticket-going/|publisher=Today|access-date=May 2, 2014|date=October 8, 2007|archive-date=October 5, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151005034645/http://www.today.com/id/21084902/ns/today-today_entertainment/t/miley-cyrus-hottest-concert-ticket-going/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite press release|url=http://www.businesswire.com/portal/site/google/index.jsp?ndmViewId=news_view&newsId=20070808005287&newsLang=en|title=Miley Cyrus Launches 54-Date 'Best Of Both Worlds Tour' On October 18|date=August 8, 2007|publisher=[[Hollywood Records]]|access-date=January 16, 2011|archive-date=February 22, 2008|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080222040643/http://www.businesswire.com/portal/site/google/index.jsp?ndmViewId=news_view&newsId=20070808005287&newsLang=en|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Ticketmaster]] officials commented that "there [hadn't] been a demand of this level or intensity since [[The Beatles]] or [[Elvis Presley|Elvis]]."<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.latimes.com/archives/la-xpm-2007-oct-06-et-montana6-story.html|title='Hannah Montana' stirs a U.S. tizzy|last1=Boucher|first1=Geoff|last2=Lee|first2=Chris|newspaper=[[Los Angeles Times]]|date=October 6, 2007|access-date=October 7, 2007|archive-date=January 19, 2010|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100119175433/http://articles.latimes.com/2007/oct/06/entertainment/et-montana6|url-status=live}}</ref> The tour's success led to the theatrical release of the 3D concert film ''[[Hannah Montana & Miley Cyrus: Best of Both Worlds Concert]]'' (2008).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=hannahmontanaconcert.htm|title=Hannah Montana/Miley Cyrus: Best of Both Worlds Concert Tour (2008)|website=Box Office Mojo|access-date=August 7, 2011|archive-date=June 4, 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240604151142/https://www.boxofficemojo.com/release/rl508986881/|url-status=live}}</ref> While initially intended to be a limited release, the film's success led to a longer run.<ref>{{cite news|last=Bowles|first=Scott|date=February 3, 2008|url=http://usatoday30.usatoday.com/life/movies/news/2008-02-03-boxoffice_N.htm|title=''Hannah Montana'' concert film earns extended theater stay|website=[[USA Today]]|access-date=February 3, 2008|archive-date=April 6, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230406174429/https://usatoday30.usatoday.com/life/movies/news/2008-02-03-boxoffice_N.htm|url-status=live}}</ref>

[[File:Miley Cyrus Wonder World concert at Auburn Hills 07.jpg|thumb|upright|left|Cyrus singing on her 2009 [[Wonder World Tour]]]]

Cyrus and friend [[Mandy Jiroux]] began posting videos on [[YouTube]] in February 2008, referring to the clips as "The Miley and Mandy Show"; the videos garnered a large online following.<ref name="Youtube">{{cite web|url=http://www.extratv.com/2008/02/27/miley-and-mandy-take-it-to-youtube/|title=Miley and Mandy Take It to YouTube|work=ExtraTV|date=February 27, 2008|access-date=April 6, 2014|archive-date=May 31, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230531085627/https://extratv.com/2008/02/27/miley-and-mandy-take-it-to-youtube/|url-status=live}}</ref> In April 2008, several pictures of Cyrus in her underwear and swimsuit were leaked online by a teenager who hacked her [[Gmail]] account.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.wired.com/threatlevel/2009/02/miley-cyrus-hac-2|title=Miley Cyrus Hacker Raided by FBI|magazine=[[Wired (magazine)|Wired]]|access-date=May 29, 2010|last=Zetter|first=Kim|date=February 23, 2009|archive-date=December 17, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131217045438/http://www.wired.com/threatlevel/2009/02/miley-cyrus-hac-2/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.foxnews.com/story/2008/10/22/hacker-who-posted-racy-miley-cyrus-pics-busted/|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140109022347/http://www.foxnews.com/story/2008/10/22/hacker-who-posted-racy-miley-cyrus-pics-busted/|archive-date=January 9, 2014|title=Hacker Who Posted Racy Miley Cyrus Pics Busted|work=Fox News Channel. 21st Century Fox|access-date=May 29, 2010 | date=October 22, 2008}}</ref> Further controversy erupted when it was reported that the then-15-year-old Cyrus had posed topless during a photo shoot by [[Annie Leibovitz]] for ''[[Vanity Fair (magazine)|Vanity Fair]]''.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.news.com.au/dailytelegraph/story/0,22049,23608789-5001026,00.html |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080501145339/http://www.news.com.au/dailytelegraph/story/0%2C22049%2C23608789-5001026%2C00.html |archive-date=May 1, 2008 |title=Miley Cyrus topless controversy |date=April 28, 2008 |access-date=April 27, 2008 |publisher=News |url-status=dead }}</ref> ''[[The New York Times]]'' subsequently clarified that although the shot left the impression that Cyrus was bare-breasted, she was wrapped in a bed sheet and was not topless.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2008/04/28/business/media/28hannah.html|title=A Topless Photo Threatens a Major Disney Franchise|last=Barnes|first=Brook|date=April 28, 2008|access-date=April 29, 2008|work=The New York Times|archive-date=May 12, 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110512221952/http://www.nytimes.com/2008/04/28/business/media/28hannah.html|url-status=live}}</ref>

Cyrus went on to release her second studio album, ''[[Breakout (Miley Cyrus album)|Breakout]]'' (2008), in June of that year.<ref name="billboard">{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/1044960/exclusive-miley-cyrus-grows-up-on-breakout|title=Miley Cyrus grows up on 'Breakout'|magazine=Billboard|last=Harding|first=Cortney|date=June 27, 2008|access-date=June 27, 2008|archive-date=February 7, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130207050458/http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/1044960/exclusive-miley-cyrus-grows-up-on-breakout|url-status=live}}</ref> The album earned the highest first-week sales of her career thus far and became her third to top the ''Billboard'' 200.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/1044636/miley-trumps-sugarland-to-lead-billboard-200|title=Miley Trumps Sugarland to Lead Billboard 200|last1=Caulfield | first1=Keith |last2=Hasty | first2=Katie |date=July 31, 2008|magazine=Billboard|access-date=February 14, 2010}}</ref><ref name="Serjeant, Jill">{{cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-cyrus-idUSN1843781520080721|title=Miley Cyrus grows up and away from Hannah Montana|last=Serjeant|first=Jill|publisher=[[Thomson Reuters]]|date=July 21, 2008|access-date=July 21, 2008|archive-date=March 10, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160310210603/http://www.reuters.com/article/us-cyrus-idUSN1843781520080721|url-status=live}}</ref> Cyrus later starred with [[John Travolta]] in the animated film ''[[Bolt (2008 film)|Bolt]]'' (2008), her debut as a film actress; she also co-wrote the song "[[I Thought I Lost You]]" (2008) for the film, which she sings as a duet with Travolta.<ref>{{cite web|last=Vena|first=Jocelyn|title=Miley Cyrus' Golden Globe Nomination Caps A Busy Year For 'Hannah Montana' Star|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1601974/miley-cyrus-golden-globe-nomination-caps-busy-year.jhtml|work=MTV News. Viacom|access-date=April 7, 2014|date=January 5, 2009|archive-date=March 27, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220327153153/http://www.mtv.com/news/1601974/miley-cyrus-golden-globe-nomination-caps-a-busy-year-for-hannah-montana-star/|url-status=dead}}</ref> The film was a critical and commercial success and earned her a [[Golden Globe Award]] nomination for [[Golden Globe Award for Best Original Song|Best Original Song]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://rottentomatoes.com/m/bolt|title=Bolt Movie Reviews, Pictures|website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|access-date=November 23, 2008|archive-date=December 1, 2008|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081201014719/http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/bolt/|url-status=live}}</ref>

In March 2009, Cyrus released "[[The Climb (Miley Cyrus song)|The Climb]]" (2009) as a single from the soundtrack to the [[Hannah Montana: The Movie|Hannah Montana feature film]].<ref name="weekly">{{cite journal|last=Paxman|first=Bob|date=September 14, 2009|title=Climb Every Mountain|journal=[[Country Weekly]]|volume=16|issue=31|issn=1074-3235}}</ref> It was met with a warm critical and commercial reaction, becoming a crossover hit in both pop and country music formats.<ref name="sales2014">{{cite news |url=http://music.yahoo.com/blogs/music-news/chart-watch-pitbull-kesha-eminem-riri-230734884.html |title=Chart Watch: Pitbull & Kesha & Eminem & RiRi |first=Paul |last=Grein |date=January 8, 2013 |work=Yahoo Music |access-date=June 26, 2016 |archive-date=October 7, 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141007024430/https://music.yahoo.com/blogs/music-news/chart-watch-pitbull-kesha-eminem-riri-230734884.html |url-status=live }}</ref> The soundtrack, which features the single, went on to become Cyrus's fourth entry to top the ''Billboard'' 200; at age 16, she became the youngest artist in history to have four number-one albums on the chart.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nbc.com/news/2011/02/28/snl-roars-into-march-with-host-miley-cyrus-and-musical-guest-the-strokes-on-march-5/|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131105113150/http://www.nbc.com/news/2011/02/28/snl-roars-into-march-with-host-miley-cyrus-and-musical-guest-the-strokes-on-march-5/|archive-date=November 5, 2013|title=SNL Roars into March with Host Miley Cyrus and Musical Guest the Strokes on March 5|date=February 28, 2011|publisher=[[NBCUniversal]]|access-date=April 4, 2011}}</ref> She released her [[Hannah Montana 3|fourth soundtrack as Hannah Montana]] in July 2009, which debuted at number two on the ''Billboard'' 200.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://content.usatoday.com/communities/idolchatter/post/2009/07/68494541/1#.UXwbhMrNS1c |title=What's Hannah Montana doing in the American Idol sales report? |website=USA Today |date=July 15, 2009 |access-date=April 29, 2013 |archive-date=November 29, 2010 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101129063956/http://content.usatoday.com/communities/idolchatter/post/2009/07/68494541/1#.UXwbhMrNS1c |url-status=live }}</ref> Cyrus later launched her first fashion line, Miley Cyrus and [[Max Azria]], through [[Walmart]].<ref>{{cite web|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180915211107/http://www.accessonline.com/articles/miley-cyrus-talks-walmart-clothing-line-gears-up-for-fall-tour-74464/|archive-date=September 15, 2018|url=https://www.accessonline.com/articles/miley-cyrus-talks-walmart-clothing-line-gears-up-for-fall-tour-74464|title=Miley Cyrus Talks Walmart Clothing Line, Gears Up For Fall Tour |website=Access Online|access-date=October 2, 2019}}</ref> It was promoted by the release of "[[Party in the U.S.A.]]" (2009) and the [[extended play|EP]] ''[[The Time of Our Lives (EP)|The Time of Our Lives]]'' (2009).<ref>{{cite web |url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/the-time-of-our-lives/id348638946 |title=iTunes – Music – The Time of Our Lives by Miley Cyrus |publisher=iTunes |date=August 31, 2009 |access-date=April 29, 2013 |archive-date=October 11, 2010 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101011042350/http://itunes.apple.com/us/album/the-time-of-our-lives/id348638946 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name="associatedpress">{{cite news|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131002161449/http://www.foxnews.com/story/2009/09/24/miley-cyrus-says-has-no-plans-to-retire-hannah-montana-character-yet/|archive-date=October 2, 2013|url=http://www.foxnews.com/story/2009/09/24/miley-cyrus-says-has-no-plans-to-retire-hannah-montana-character-yet/|title=Miley Cyrus Says She Has No Plans to Retire 'Hannah Montana' Character – Yet|date=September 24, 2009|access-date=June 6, 2010|agency=Associated Press|publisher=[[Fox News Channel]]}}</ref> Cyrus said the record was "a transitioning album [...] really to introduce people to what I want my next record to sound like and with time I will be able to do that a little more."<ref name="associatedpress"/> "Party in the U.S.A." became one of Cyrus's most successful singles to date and is considered to be one of her [[signature song]]s.<ref>{{cite press release|title=Miley Cyrus Catapults to No. 2 Debut on Billboard Hot 100 with 'Party in the USA;' Tied for Highest Debut of the Year|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/267653/miley-cyrus-jay-z-make-noise-on-hot-100|magazine=Billboard|date=August 20, 2009|access-date=August 21, 2009|last1=Ben-Yehuda|first1=Ayala|last2=Caulfield|first2=Keith|last3=Pietroluongo|first3=Silvio|archive-date=June 6, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130606110711/http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/267653/miley-cyrus-jay-z-make-noise-on-hot-100|url-status=live}}</ref> She embarked on her first world tour, the [[Wonder World Tour (Miley Cyrus)|Wonder World Tour]] (2009) which was a critical and commercial success.<ref>{{cite news|last=Lawrence|first=Jesse|title=Miley Cyrus Bangerz Tour Could Learn A Thing Or Two From Lady Gaga's ArtPop Tour|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/jesselawrence/2014/01/24/miley-cyrus-bangerz-tour-could-learn-a-thing-or-two-from-lady-gagas-artpop-tour/|work=[[Forbes]]|date=January 24, 2014|access-date=August 22, 2017|archive-date=January 29, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140129144900/http://www.forbes.com/sites/jesselawrence/2014/01/24/miley-cyrus-bangerz-tour-could-learn-a-thing-or-two-from-lady-gagas-artpop-tour/|url-status=live}}</ref> On December 7, 2009, Cyrus performed for [[Elizabeth II|Queen Elizabeth II]] and other members of the [[British royal family]] at the [[Royal Variety Performance]] in [[Blackpool]], [[Lancashire]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/entertainment/8320913.stm|title=Entertainment &#124; Kay to present Royal Variety show|work=BBC News|date=October 22, 2009|access-date=March 5, 2010|archive-date=February 24, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230224100806/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/entertainment/8320913.stm|url-status=live}}</ref>

''Billboard'' [[List of awards and nominations received by Miley Cyrus|ranked]] her as the fourth best-selling female music artist of 2009.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/266426/taylor-swift-kanye-west-named-top-female-and-male-artists-of-2009|title=Taylor Swift, Kanye West Named Top Female and Male Artists of 2009|magazine=Billboard|date=September 14, 2009|access-date=March 8, 2010|archive-date=April 8, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190408092036/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/266426/taylor-swift-kanye-west-named-top-female-and-male-artists-of-2009|url-status=live}}</ref>

===2010–2012: New image with ''Can't Be Tamed'' and focus on acting===
[[File:Miley Cyrus Gypsi Tour Acer Arena Sydney (5872497845).jpg|thumb|upright|Cyrus performing on her [[Gypsy Heart Tour]] in [[São Paulo]], 2011|left]]

Hoping to foster a more mature image, Cyrus starred in the film ''[[The Last Song (2010 film)|The Last Song]]'' (2010), based on the [[Nicholas Sparks]] novel.<ref>{{cite news|last=Fleming |first=Michael |title=Miley Cyrus to star in Disney film |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |date=September 16, 2008 |url=https://www.variety.com/article/VR1117992306.html?categoryid=1236&cs=1 |access-date=June 18, 2009 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100405111748/http://www.variety.com/article/VR1117992306.html?categoryid=1236&cs=1 |archive-date=April 5, 2010 |url-status=live }}</ref> It was met with negative critical reviews<ref>{{cite web|url=https://metacritic.com/movie/the-last-song|title=Last Song, the reviews at Metacritic.com|website=Metacritic|access-date=June 4, 2010|archive-date=August 21, 2010|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100821143345/http://www.metacritic.com/movie/the-last-song|url-status=live}}</ref> but was a box office hit.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=lastsong.htm |title=The Last Song (2010)-Box Office Mojo |access-date=May 27, 2010 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100404072126/http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=lastsong.htm |archive-date=April 4, 2010 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Bible | first=Karie |url=http://www.ercboxoffice.com/index.php?section=news&subsection=show_news_details&news_id=283 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100521051759/http://ercboxoffice.com/index.php?section=news&subsection=show_news_details&news_id=283 |url-status=dead |archive-date=May 21, 2010 |title=Box Office Obits |publisher=Exhibitor Relations Co. Inc. |date=May 12, 2010 |access-date=June 4, 2010 }}</ref> Cyrus further attempted to shift her image with the release of her third studio album, ''[[Can't Be Tamed]]'' (2010).<ref>{{cite web |url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/cant-be-tamed/id375866638 |title=iTunes – Music – Can't Be Tamed by Miley Cyrus |publisher=iTunes |date=June 21, 2010 |access-date=April 29, 2013 |archive-date=January 17, 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140117053610/https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/cant-be-tamed/id375866638 |url-status=live }}</ref> The album featured a more dance-oriented sound than her prior releases and stirred a considerable amount of controversy over its lyrical content and Cyrus's live performances.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://huffingtonpost.com/2010/05/04/miley-cyrus-cant-be-tamed_n_563718.html|title=Miley Cyrus 'Can't Be Tamed' VIDEO: Too Sexy Or Age Appropriate? (PHOTOS)|date=July 4, 2010|access-date=July 31, 2016|newspaper=Huffington Post|archive-date=August 26, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160826114605/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2010/05/04/miley-cyrus-cant-be-tamed_n_563718.html|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thaindian.com/newsportal/entertainment/is-miley-cyrus-new-video-cant-be-tamed-too-racy_100359572.html|title=Is Miley Cyrus' new video 'Can't Be Tamed' too racy?|website=Theindian.com|access-date=July 31, 2016|archive-date=August 15, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160815062349/http://www.thaindian.com/newsportal/entertainment/is-miley-cyrus-new-video-cant-be-tamed-too-racy_100359572.html|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://ew.com/article/2010/05/05/miley-cyrus-cant-be-tamed-video|title=Miley Cyrus' 'Can't Be Tamed' video: Has our little tween star flown the coop?|magazine=Entertainment Weekly|access-date=July 31, 2016|archive-date=November 7, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161107222718/http://www.ew.com/article/2010/05/05/miley-cyrus-cant-be-tamed-video|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/music-arts/miley-cyrus-tamed-music-video-singer-17-pole-dancing-plunging-s-m-style-corsets-article-1.178039|title=Miley's sexy new video is anything but 'Tame'|website=New York Daily News|date=May 5, 2010|access-date=July 31, 2016|archive-date=March 6, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160306232918/http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/music-arts/miley-cyrus-tamed-music-video-singer-17-pole-dancing-plunging-s-m-style-corsets-article-1.178039|url-status=live}}</ref> It sold 106,000 copies in its first week of release and became her first studio album not to top the ''Billboard'' 200 chart in the United States.<ref name=mstar>{{cite web |url=http://www.mstarz.com/articles/9365/20130306/miley-cyrus-breaks-up-twitter-signs-britney-spears-manager-larry.htm |last=Cortez |first=Lauren |title=Miley Cyrus Breaks Up from Twitter and Signs with Britney Spears Manager; Can Larry Rudolph Orchestrate Another Comeback? : News |publisher=Mstarz |date=March 6, 2013 |access-date=April 29, 2013 |archive-date=March 5, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305192446/http://www.mstarz.com/articles/9365/20130306/miley-cyrus-breaks-up-twitter-signs-britney-spears-manager-larry.htm |url-status=live }}</ref> Cyrus released her [[Hannah Montana Forever (soundtrack)|final soundtrack as Hannah Montana]] that October; it was seen as a commercial failure due to its low position on the charts compared to her previous albums.<ref name="new.music.yahoo.com">{{Cite web |title=Week Ending Oct. 24, 2010: Place Your Bets &#124; Chart Watch - Yahoo! Music |url=http://new.music.yahoo.com/blogs/chart_watch/68460/week-ending-oct-24-2010-place-your-bets/ |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121001171215/http://music.yahoo.com/blogs/chart-watch/week-ending-oct-24-2010-place-your-bets.html |archive-date=2012-10-01 |access-date=2010-10-28}}</ref>

Cyrus was the subject of further controversy when a video posted online in December 2010 showed her, then aged eighteen, smoking [[Salvia divinorum|salvia]] with a [[bong]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/life-style/health/salvia-miley-cyrus-caught-smoking-salvia-bong-plant-high-akin-marijuana-lsd-article-1.470512|title=What is salvia? Miley Cyrus caught smoking plant|website=New York Daily News|date=December 10, 2010|access-date=July 31, 2016|archive-date=April 11, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230411234558/https://www.nydailynews.com/life-style/health/salvia-miley-cyrus-caught-smoking-salvia-bong-plant-high-akin-marijuana-lsd-article-1.470512|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/473147/miley-cyrus-opens-up-about-salvia-bong-hit|title=Miley Cyrus Opens Up About Salvia Bong Hit|magazine=Billboard|access-date=July 31, 2016|archive-date=August 6, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160806160932/http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/473147/miley-cyrus-opens-up-about-salvia-bong-hit|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://hollywoodlife.com/2011/02/09/miley-cyrus-marie-claire-bong-salvia/|title=Miley Cyrus Admits To Smoking Salvia: It Was A Huge Mistake!|first1=Chloe|last1=Melas|date=February 9, 2011|website=Hollywoodlife.com|access-date=July 31, 2016|archive-date=April 24, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190424083334/https://hollywoodlife.com/2011/02/09/miley-cyrus-marie-claire-bong-salvia/|url-status=live}}</ref> 2010 ended with her ranking at number thirteen on the [[Forbes Celebrity 100|''Forbes'' Celebrity 100]] list.<ref>{{cite news|title=#13 Miley Cyrus|url=https://www.forbes.com/lists/2010/53/celeb-100-10_Miley-Cyrus_EB0C.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100701031726/http://www.forbes.com/lists/2010/53/celeb-100-10_Miley-Cyrus_EB0C.html|url-status=dead|archive-date=July 1, 2010|work=[[Forbes]]|access-date=April 5, 2014|date=June 28, 2010}}</ref> She embarked on her worldwide [[Gypsy Heart Tour]] in April 2011 which had no North American dates;<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cambio.com/news/miley-cyrus-is-heading-back-to-music |title=Miley Cyrus Back to Music |publisher=Cambio |date=February 14, 2011 |access-date=August 7, 2011 |archive-date=November 17, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171117001427/http://www.cambio.com/news/miley-cyrus-is-heading-back-to-music/ |url-status=live }}</ref> she cited her various controversial moments as the reason, claiming that she only wanted to travel where she felt "the most love".<ref>{{cite web|last=Allin|first=Olivia|title=Miley Cyrus won't tour in U.S., says foreign fans show the 'most love'|url=http://www.ontheredcarpet.com/Miley-Cyrus-wont-tour-in-U-S---says-foreign-fans-show-the-most-love/8075657|publisher=On the Red Carpet|access-date=April 7, 2014|date=April 15, 2011|archive-date=July 11, 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110711173950/http://www.ontheredcarpet.com/Miley-Cyrus-wont-tour-in-U-S---says-foreign-fans-show-the-most-love/8075657|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.smh.com.au/entertainment/music/cant-be-tamed-singer-to-hit-perth-shores-20110330-1cfk7.html|title=Can't be Tamed singer to hit Perth shores|last=Gallo|first=Lee-Maree|date=March 30, 2011|newspaper=[[The Sydney Morning Herald]]|access-date=April 16, 2011|archive-date=April 7, 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110407083157/http://www.smh.com.au/entertainment/music/cant-be-tamed-singer-to-hit-perth-shores-20110330-1cfk7.html|url-status=live}}</ref> Following the release of ''Can't Be Tamed'', Cyrus officially parted ways with Hollywood Records.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/1536344/miley-cyrus-signs-with-rca-will-work-with-dr-luke-on-new-lp|title=Miley Cyrus Signs With RCA, Will Work With Dr. Luke on New LP|magazine=Billboard|access-date=July 31, 2016|archive-date=June 17, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160617191421/http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/1536344/miley-cyrus-signs-with-rca-will-work-with-dr-luke-on-new-lp|url-status=live}}</ref> With her obligations to ''Hannah Montana'' fulfilled, Cyrus announced her plans to take a hiatus from music so she could focus on her acting career.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pasadenastarnews.com/ci_14773276|title=Miley Cyrus ready to sing a new tune|work=Pasadena Star-News|date=March 28, 2010|access-date=April 3, 2010|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100330192550/http://www.pasadenastarnews.com/ci_14773276|archive-date=March 30, 2010}}</ref> She confirmed she would not be going to college.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://marquee.blogs.cnn.com/2010/05/25/miley-cyrus-nothing-i-do-is-for-shock-value|title=Miley Cyrus: Nothing I do is for shock value|work=CNN|date=May 25, 2010|access-date=May 27, 2010|archive-date=May 27, 2010|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100527034253/http://marquee.blogs.cnn.com/2010/05/25/miley-cyrus-nothing-i-do-is-for-shock-value/|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://voices.washingtonpost.com/celebritology/2010/05/miley_cyrus_opts_out_of_colleg.html|title=Miley Cyrus opts out of college|newspaper=[[The Washington Post]]|date=May 25, 2010|access-date=May 27, 2010|archive-date=October 24, 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111024234520/http://voices.washingtonpost.com/celebritology/2010/05/miley_cyrus_opts_out_of_colleg.html|url-status=dead}}</ref>

Cyrus hosted the March 5, 2011, episode of ''[[Saturday Night Live]]'' where she poked fun at her recent controversies.<ref>{{cite web |last=McGee |first=Ryan |url=http://www.hitfix.com/blogs/monkeys-as-critics/posts/recap-saturday-night-live-miley-cyrus-and-the-strokes#~ojw2g1z3oxbKRa |title=Recap: Saturday Night Live – Miley Cyrus and The Strokes |publisher=Hitfix |date=March 6, 2011 |access-date=October 7, 2013 |archive-date=March 4, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304072735/http://www.hitfix.com/blogs/monkeys-as-critics/posts/recap-saturday-night-live-miley-cyrus-and-the-strokes#~ojw2g1z3oxbKRa |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name="EW2">{{cite magazine |last=Tucker |first=Ken |url=https://ew.com/article/2011/03/06/saturday-night-live-miley-cyrus-strokes/ |title='Saturday Night Live' review: Miley Cyrus and a show better than 'pretty cool': It was pretty funny |magazine=Entertainment Weekly |date=March 6, 2011 |access-date=October 2, 2019 |archive-date=September 25, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190925182818/https://ew.com/article/2011/03/06/saturday-night-live-miley-cyrus-strokes/ |url-status=live }}</ref> That November it was announced that Cyrus would be the voice of Mavis in the animated film ''[[Hotel Transylvania (film)|Hotel Transylvania]]'';<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Vary|first=Adam B.|title=Miley Cyrus joins 'Hotel Transylvania'|url=https://ew.com/article/2011/11/04/miley-cyrus-adam-sandler-hotel-transylvania/|magazine=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|access-date=November 4, 2011|archive-date=October 6, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141006133444/http://insidemovies.ew.com/2011/11/04/miley-cyrus-adam-sandler-hotel-transylvania/|url-status=live}}</ref> however by February 2012 she was dropped from the project and replaced with [[Selena Gomez]]. At the time Cyrus said her reason for leaving the movie was wanting to work on her music;<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.entertainmentwise.com/news/69288/Miley-Cyrus-Drops-Out-Of-Film-Role-To-Make-Pop-Comeback |title=Miley Cyrus Drops Out Of Film Role To Make Pop Comeback |first=Shaun |last=Kitchener |publisher=Entertainmentwise. [[Gigwise]] |date=February 10, 2012 |access-date=September 21, 2013 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150404070727/http://www.entertainmentwise.com/news/69288/miley-cyrus-drops-out-of-film-role-to-make-pop-comeback |archive-date=April 4, 2015}}</ref> later it was revealed the real reason behind her exit was because she bought her then-boyfriend Liam Hemsworth a birthday cake shaped like a penis and licked it.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://people.com/movies/miley-cyrus-kicked-off-hotel-transylvania-over-liam-hemsworth-penis-cake/|title=Miley Cyrus Says She Was 'Kicked Off' Hotel Transylvania After Licking Liam Hemsworth's Penis Cake|work=[[People (magazine)|People]]|date=August 22, 2019|first=Ale|last=Russian|access-date=October 28, 2020|archive-date=November 11, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201111184832/https://people.com/movies/miley-cyrus-kicked-off-hotel-transylvania-over-liam-hemsworth-penis-cake/|url-status=live}}</ref> She made an appearance on the [[MTV]] television series ''[[Punk'd]]'' with [[Kelly Osbourne]] and [[Khloé Kardashian]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Kaufman |first=Gil |url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1678777/punkd-premiere-justin-bieber-miley-cyrus.jhtml |title='Punk'd' Taps Justin Bieber, Miley Cyrus For Comeback&nbsp;— Music, Celebrity, Artist News |work=MTV News. Viacom |date=February 8, 2012 |access-date=February 13, 2012 |archive-date=December 13, 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131213105627/http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1678777/punkd-premiere-justin-bieber-miley-cyrus.jhtml |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eonline.com/news/283585/how-did-khloe-kardashian-odom-get-punk-d-by-miley-cyrus-hint-it-s-pretty-gross|title=How Did Khloé Kardashian Odom Get Punk'd by Miley Cyrus? (Hint: It's Pretty Gross)|publisher=[[E! Online]]|date=January 3, 2012|access-date=February 13, 2012|archive-date=February 21, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230221191451/https://www.eonline.com/news/283585/how-did-khloe-kardashian-odom-get-punk-d-by-miley-cyrus-hint-it-s-pretty-gross|url-status=live}}</ref> Cyrus starred alongside [[Demi Moore]] in the independent film ''[[LOL (2012 film)|LOL]]'' (2012).<ref>{{cite news|last=Gomez|first=Luis|title=Trailer for Chicago-based 'LOL' features Miley Cyrus, Edwardo's Pizza sign|url=https://www.chicagotribune.com/2012/04/11/trailer-for-chicago-based-lol-features-miley-cyrus-edwardos-pizza-sign/|work=[[Chicago Tribune]]|access-date=December 27, 2013|date=April 11, 2012|archive-date=December 28, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131228143248/http://articles.chicagotribune.com/2012-04-11/entertainment/chi-trailer-chicago-miley-cyrus-lol-web-20120411_1_film-lol-trailer|url-status=live}}</ref> The film had a limited release; it was a critical and commercial failure.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Fritz|first1=Ben|last2=Kaufman|first2=Amy|url=http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/entertainmentnewsbuzz/2012/04/lol-miley-cyrus-lionsgate.html|title=OMG! Miley Cyrus' 'LOL' gets no love from Lionsgate|website=Los Angeles Times|date=April 18, 2012|access-date=March 2, 2013|archive-date=July 15, 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120715104742/http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/entertainmentnewsbuzz/2012/04/lol-miley-cyrus-lionsgate.html|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Fritz|first1=Ben|last2=Kaufman|first2=Amy|title=Miley Cyrus' 'LOL' is a box office flop – but how big a flop?|url=http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/entertainmentnewsbuzz/2012/05/miley-cyrus-lol-release-box-office.html|website=Los Angeles Times|access-date=December 27, 2013|date=May 7, 2012|archive-date=January 23, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140123221611/http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/entertainmentnewsbuzz/2012/05/miley-cyrus-lol-release-box-office.html|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://rottentomatoes.com/m/lol_2011/ |title=LOL |website=Rotten Tomatoes |access-date=April 29, 2013 |archive-date=June 23, 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130623054009/http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/lol_2011/ |url-status=live }}</ref> She starred in the comedy film ''[[So Undercover]]'' playing the role of an undercover FBI agent at a college sorority.<ref>{{cite news|title=So Undercover – the mystery of Miley Cyrus's film career|url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/filmblog/2012/nov/08/so-undercover-miley-cyrus-trailer|work=[[The Guardian]]|access-date=May 2, 2014|last=Heritage|first=Stuart|date=November 8, 2012|archive-date=February 21, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230221191452/https://www.theguardian.com/film/filmblog/2012/nov/08/so-undercover-miley-cyrus-trailer|url-status=live}}</ref>

Cyrus released a string of live performances known as the ''[[Backyard Sessions]]'' on YouTube during the spring and summer of 2012; the performances were of classic songs she personally liked.<ref>{{cite web |last=Lansky |first=Sam |url=http://idolator.com/7356722/miley-cyrus-covers-jolene-in-stunning-backyard-sessions-video-watch |title=Miley Cyrus Covers "Jolene" In Stunning 'Backyard Sessions' Video: Watch &#124; |publisher=Idolator |date=December 27, 2012 |access-date=April 29, 2013 |archive-date=June 4, 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240604151055/https://www.idolator.com/7356722/miley-cyrus-covers-jolene-in-stunning-backyard-sessions-video-watch |url-status=live }}</ref> Having begun working on a failed fourth album the previous year, Cyrus resumed working on a new musical project in late 2012.<ref name="Entertainmentwise">{{cite web|url=http://www.entertainmentwise.com/news/117838/I-Want-To-Erase-My-Past-Miley-Cyrus-Admits-Shes-Embarrassed-By-Hannah-Montana|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141226214357/http://www.entertainmentwise.com/news/117838/I-Want-To-Erase-My-Past-Miley-Cyrus-Admits-Shes-Embarrassed-By-Hannah-Montana|title='I Want To Erase My Past': Miley Cyrus Admits She's 'Embarrassed' By Hannah Montana|last=Chester|first=Jason|publisher=Entertainmentwise. [[Gigwise]]|date=June 14, 2013|archive-date=December 26, 2014|access-date=September 26, 2013}}</ref>{{Failed verification|date=April 2023}} She collaborated with producers [[Rock Mafia]] on their song "Morning Sun" (2012), which was made available for free download online.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://soundcloud.com/fredjpariona/miley-cyrus-morning-sun-prod|title=Miley Cyrus - Morning Sun (Prod. Diplo, Tiesto & Rock Mafia)|website=SoundCloud|access-date=July 31, 2016|archive-date=February 21, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230221191451/https://soundcloud.com/fredjpariona/miley-cyrus-morning-sun-prod|url-status=live}}</ref> She had previously appeared in the music video for their debut single, "[[The Big Bang (song)|The Big Bang]]" (2010).<ref>{{cite magazine |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/viral-videos/951945/rock-mafia-recruits-miley-cyrus-for-the-big-bang-video |title=Rock Mafia Recruits Miley Cyrus For 'The Big Bang' Video |magazine=Billboard |date=November 2, 2010 |access-date=April 8, 2014 |archive-date=September 7, 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140907130613/http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/viral-videos/951945/rock-mafia-recruits-miley-cyrus-for-the-big-bang-video |url-status=live }}</ref> Cyrus later provided guest vocals on "[[Decisions (song)|Decisions]]" (2012) by [[Borgore]].<ref name="Secret">{{cite magazine|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/exclusive-borgore-on-secret-collaboration-with-miley-cyrus-20120823|title=Borgore on His Secret Dubstep Track With Miley Cyrus: 'She Likes Surprises'|first=Steve|last=Baltin|magazine=Rolling Stone|date=August 23, 2012|access-date=January 18, 2014|archive-date=March 31, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140331171533/http://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/exclusive-borgore-on-secret-collaboration-with-miley-cyrus-20120823|url-status=dead}}</ref> Both Cyrus and Hemsworth appeared in the song's music video.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ontheredcarpet.com/Miley-Cyrus--Liam-Hemsworth-make-out-in-Borgore-music-video---Watch/8870656|title=Miley Cyrus, Liam Hemsworth 'make out' in Borgore music video - Watch|first=Olivia|last=Allin|publisher=On the Red Carpet|date=November 1, 2012|access-date=January 18, 2014|archive-date=February 26, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140226073105/http://www.ontheredcarpet.com/Miley-Cyrus--Liam-Hemsworth-make-out-in-Borgore-music-video---Watch/8870656|url-status=live}}</ref> She went on to guest star as Missi in two episodes of the [[CBS]] sitcom ''[[Two and a Half Men]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.kpopstarz.com/articles/26062/20130427/two-and-a-half-men-angus-t-jones.htm |title=Two and a Half Men Returning for 11th Season, Fate of Angus T Jones To Be Determined |publisher=KpopStarz |date=April 25, 2013 |access-date=April 29, 2013 |archive-date=October 17, 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211017215922/https://www.kpopstarz.com/articles/26062/20130427/two-and-a-half-men-angus-t-jones.htm |url-status=live }}</ref> Cyrus drew significant media attention when she cut her traditionally long, brown hair in favor of a blonde, [[pixie cut]]; she commented that she had "never felt more [herself] in [her] whole life" and that "it really changed [her] life."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eonline.com/news/337305/miley-cyrus-chops-off-her-hair-do-you-like|title=Miley Cyrus Chops Off Her Hair—Do You Like?|last=Nessif|first=Bruna|publisher=[[E! Online]]|date=August 12, 2012|access-date=August 31, 2013|archive-date=April 11, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230411234647/https://www.eonline.com/news/337305/miley-cyrus-chops-off-her-hair-do-you-like|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.torontosun.com/2013/07/16/miley-cyrus-busy-making-music-having-fun|title=Miley Cyrus busy making music, having fun|last=Stevenson|first=Jane|newspaper=[[Toronto Sun]]|date=July 16, 2013|access-date=September 1, 2013|archive-date=May 13, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230513004625/https://torontosun.com/2013/07/16/miley-cyrus-busy-making-music-having-fun|url-status=live}}</ref>

===2013–2015: ''Bangerz'' and ''Miley Cyrus & Her Dead Petz''===
[[File:93.3 FLZ Jingle Ball Tampa Florida IMG 6955 (11490119034) (cropped).jpg|thumb|upright|left|Cyrus performing at the 2013 [[Jingle Ball]] in [[Tampa, Florida|Tampa]], [[Florida]]]]

In 2013, Cyrus hired [[Larry Rudolph]] to be her manager, although she is currently managed by [[Maverick Management|Maverick]]'s [[Adam Leber]]; Rudolph is best known for representing [[Britney Spears]].<ref>{{cite news|last=McKay|first=Hollie|title=Is Miley Cyrus' manager behind her sexed up transformation?|url=http://www.foxnews.com/entertainment/2013/09/11/is-miley-cyrus-manager-behind-her-sexed-up-transformation/|work=Fox News|date=September 11, 2013|access-date=April 7, 2014|archive-date=March 3, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303221740/http://www.foxnews.com/entertainment/2013/09/11/is-miley-cyrus-manager-behind-her-sexed-up-transformation/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://hitsdailydouble.com/news%26id%3D316286%26title+MAVERICK-IS-A-LEGEND-OF-COUNTRY-TRAP |title=MAVERICK IS A LEGEND OF COUNTRY TRAP |author=<!--Not stated--> |date=May 3, 2019 |website=Hits Daily Double |access-date=January 8, 2020 |archive-date=August 4, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200804012825/https://hitsdailydouble.com/news%26id%3D316286%26title+MAVERICK-IS-A-LEGEND-OF-COUNTRY-TRAP |url-status=live }}</ref> It was confirmed that Cyrus had signed with [[RCA Records]] for her future releases.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/5657600/miley-cyrus-reveals-bangerz-release-date|title=Miley Cyrus Reveals 'Bangerz' Release Date|last=Lipshutz|first=Jason|magazine=Billboard|date=August 15, 2013|access-date=September 1, 2013|archive-date=August 27, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130827001108/http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/5657600/miley-cyrus-reveals-bangerz-release-date|url-status=live}}</ref> She worked with producers such as [[Pharrell Williams]] and [[Mike Will Made-It]] on her fourth studio album, resulting in a hip hop-influenced sound.<ref name=hiphop>{{cite web|url=http://blogs.phoenixnewtimes.com/uponsun/2013/10/miley-cyrus-hip-hop-list.php|title=5 Reasons Why Miley Cyrus Is Good for Hip-Hop|last=Escudero|first=Nicki|work=[[Phoenix New Times]]|date=October 14, 2013|access-date=November 30, 2013|archive-date=October 28, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131028034657/http://blogs.phoenixnewtimes.com/uponsun/2013/10/miley-cyrus-hip-hop-list.php|url-status=dead}}</ref> She collaborated with numerous hip hop artists releases<ref name=hiphop /> and appeared on the [[Snoop Dogg|Snoop Lion]] song "[[Ashtrays and Heartbreaks]]" (2013), released as the lead single from his twelfth studio album, ''[[Reincarnated (album)|Reincarnated]]''.<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Blistein|first=Jon|title=Snoop Lion's 'Ashtrays and Heartbreaks' Features Miley Cyrus|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/snoop-lions-ashtrays-and-heartbreaks-features-miley-cyrus-20130404|magazine=Rolling Stone|date=April 4, 2013|access-date=August 22, 2017|archive-date=August 23, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170823121055/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/snoop-lions-ashtrays-and-heartbreaks-features-miley-cyrus-20130404|url-status=dead}}</ref> She collaborated with [[will.i.am]] on the song "[[Fall Down (will.i.am song)|Fall Down]]" (2013), released as a promotional single that same month.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://music.ninemsn.com.au/blog.aspx?blogentryid=1112163&showcomments=true |title=Exclusive interview: Will.i.am believes Miley Cyrus will be the new Bjork! |last=Nelmes | first=Amy |publisher=[[MSN]] |date=April 2013 |access-date=January 3, 2014 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131103030432/http://music.ninemsn.com.au/blog.aspx?blogentryid=1112163&showcomments=true |archive-date=November 3, 2013 }}</ref> The song entered the ''Billboard'' Hot 100 at number fifty-eight, marking her first appearance on the chart since "[[Can't Be Tamed (song)|Can't Be Tamed]]" (2010).<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/artist/431547/william/chart?f=379|title=will.i.am – Chart history|magazine=Billboard|access-date=April 29, 2013|archive-date=June 22, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130622110135/http://www.billboard.com/artist/431547/william/chart?f=379|url-status=live}}</ref> She provided guest vocals on the [[Lil Twist]] song "Twerk", which also featured vocals by [[Justin Bieber]].<ref name=twist>{{cite magazine |url=http://www.rap-up.com/2013/07/06/lil-twist-enlists-justin-bieber-and-miley-cyrus-for-new-single-twerk/ |title=Lil Twist Enlists Justin Bieber and Miley Cyrus for New Single 'Twerk' |magazine=[[Rap-Up]] |access-date=September 10, 2013 |archive-date=February 24, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230224100829/https://www.rap-up.com/2013/07/06/lil-twist-enlists-justin-bieber-and-miley-cyrus-for-new-single-twerk/ |url-status=live }}</ref> The song was unreleased for unknown reasons but leaked online.<ref name=twist /> On May 23, 2013, it was confirmed that Cyrus would be featured on the [[Mike Will Made It]] single "[[23 (Mike Will Made It song)|23]]", with [[Wiz Khalifa]] and [[Juicy J]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://rapdose.com/2013/05/23/mike-will-made-it-wiz-khalifa-miley-cyrus-juicy-j-23-single |title=Mike Will Made It Teases Wiz Khalifa, Miley Cyrus & Juicy J Featured Single 23 |publisher=Rap Dose |date=May 23, 2013 |access-date=September 10, 2013 |archive-date=February 22, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230222215456/http://rapdose.com/2013/05/23/mike-will-made-it-wiz-khalifa-miley-cyrus-juicy-j-23-single |url-status=live }}</ref> The single went on to peak at number eleven on the Hot 100, and had sold over one{{nbsp}}million copies worldwide as of 2013.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/artist/5747924/mike-will-made-it/chart|title=Mike Will Made-It - Chart history|magazine=Billboard|access-date=December 30, 2013|archive-date=March 19, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140319075607/http://www.billboard.com/artist/5747924/mike-will-made-it/chart|url-status=live}}</ref>

Cyrus released her new single "[[We Can't Stop]]" on June 3.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/events/bbma-2013/1562889/miley-cyrus-we-cant-stop-single-due-june-3|title=Miley Cyrus' 'We Can't Stop' Single Due June 3|magazine=Billboard|date=May 19, 2013|access-date=September 10, 2013|archive-date=October 9, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131009052352/http://www.billboard.com/articles/events/bbma-2013/1562889/miley-cyrus-we-cant-stop-single-due-june-3|url-status=live}}</ref> Touted as her comeback single, it became a worldwide commercial success, topping charts in territories such as the United Kingdom.<ref>{{cite web |last=Hung |first=Steffen |url=https://charts.nz/showitem.asp?interpret=Miley+Cyrus&titel=We+Can%27t+Stop&cat=s |title=Miley Cyrus – We Can't Stop |publisher=charts.nz |access-date=September 10, 2013 |archive-date=May 18, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170518094027/http://charts.nz/showitem.asp?interpret=Miley+Cyrus&titel=We+Can%27t+Stop&cat=s |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/news/a505799/miley-cyrus-earns-first-uk-number-one-single-with-we-cant-stop.html |title=Miley Cyrus earns first UK number one single with 'We Can't Stop' – Music News |website=Digital Spy |date=August 11, 2013 |access-date=September 10, 2013 |archive-date=September 24, 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924154636/http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/news/a505799/miley-cyrus-earns-first-uk-number-one-single-with-we-cant-stop.html |url-status=live }}</ref> The song's music video set the [[Vevo]] record for most views within twenty-four hours of release and became the first to reach 100{{nbsp}}million views on the site.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/5047747/miley-cyrus-we-cant-stop-video-breaks-vevo-record|title=Miley Cyrus' 'We Can't Stop' Video Breaks VEVO Record|magazine=Billboard|date=July 29, 2013|access-date=September 10, 2013|archive-date=September 17, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130917183555/http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/5047747/miley-cyrus-we-cant-stop-video-breaks-vevo-record|url-status=live}}</ref> Cyrus performed with [[Robin Thicke]] at the [[2013 MTV Video Music Awards]], a performance that resulted in widespread media attention and public scrutiny. Her simulated sex acts with a foam finger were described as "disturbing" and the whole performance as "cringe-worthy".<ref name="Hollywood Reporter">{{cite web|url=https://hollywoodreporter.com/earshot/note-miley-cyrus-please-stop-614407|title=Note to Miley Cyrus: Please Stop; Plus Other VMAs Ruminations|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=August 26, 2013|access-date=August 26, 2013|archive-date=August 26, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130826100256/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/earshot/note-miley-cyrus-please-stop-614407|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="auto">{{cite magazine|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/tv/news/miley-cyrus-robin-thicke-vma-performance-one-year-later-20140822|archive-date=May 13, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160513101122/http://www.rollingstone.com/tv/news/miley-cyrus-robin-thicke-vma-performance-one-year-later-20140822|title=Twerk It Out: Miley and Robin's VMA Performance, One Year Later|last=Kroll | first=Katy |magazine=Rolling Stone|date=August 22, 2014|access-date=January 29, 2015}}</ref> Cyrus released "[[Wrecking Ball (Miley Cyrus song)|Wrecking Ball]]" (2013) as the second single from ''Bangerz'' on the same day as the VMAs.<ref name=wbsingle>{{cite web|url=https://thewrap.com/miley-cyrus-wrecking-ball-breaks-vevo-record-for-most-first-day-views/|title=Miley Cyrus' 'Wrecking Ball' Smashes One Direction's VEVO Record|last=Gilman|first=Greg|publisher=The Wrap|date=September 10, 2013|access-date=September 14, 2013|archive-date=September 12, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130912235303/http://www.thewrap.com/miley-cyrus-wrecking-ball-breaks-vevo-record-for-most-first-day-views/|url-status=live}}</ref> The accompanying music video, which showed her swinging naked on a wrecking ball, was viewed over nineteen million times within 24 hours of its release, and drew criticism from some for allegedly [[Sexual objectification|objectifying]] Cyrus, including fellow singer [[Sinéad O'Connor|Sinéad O’Connor]], who said that "you will obscure your talent by allowing yourself to be pimped, whether it's the music business or yourself doing the pimping".<ref name=wbsingle /><ref name="auto"/><ref>{{Cite web |last=Garcia |first=Thania |date=August 25, 2023 |title=Miley Cyrus Addresses Sinéad O'Connor Feud Over 'Wrecking Ball': 'I Had No Idea About the Fragile Mental State She Was In' |url=https://variety.com/2023/music/news/miley-cyrus-sinead-oconnor-feud-wrecking-ball-fragile-state-1235704732/ |access-date=September 6, 2023 |website=Variety|archive-date=September 6, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230906040029/https://variety.com/2023/music/news/miley-cyrus-sinead-oconnor-feud-wrecking-ball-fragile-state-1235704732/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Despite this, the single became Cyrus's first to top the Hot 100 in the US, and maintained the #1 spot for three weeks.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Trust |first=Gary |date=February 16, 2023 |title=Ask Billboard: Where Does 'Flowers' (Already) Rank Among Miley Cyrus' Biggest Hits? |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/chart-beat/miley-cyrus-top-songs-albums-ask-billboard-1235255167/ |access-date=September 6, 2023 |magazine=Billboard |archive-date=February 17, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230217210717/https://www.billboard.com/music/chart-beat/miley-cyrus-top-songs-albums-ask-billboard-1235255167/ |url-status=live }}</ref> It sold over two million copies.<ref>{{cite magazine |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/5695590/miley-cyrus-wrecking-ball-swings-to-top-of-hot-100 |title=Miley Cyrus' 'Wrecking Ball' Swings Atop Hot 100 |last=Trust |first=Gary |magazine=Billboard |date=September 18, 2013 |access-date=September 18, 2013 |archive-date=September 20, 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130920000156/http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/5695590/miley-cyrus-wrecking-ball-swings-to-top-of-hot-100 |url-status=live }}</ref>

[[File:CyrusBangerz.jpg|thumb|upright|Cyrus performing on her 2014 [[Bangerz Tour]]]]

On October 2, 2013, MTV aired the documentary ''[[Miley: The Movement]]'', that chronicled the recording of her fourth studio album ''[[Bangerz]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2013/10/02/mtv-to-premiere-miley-the-movement-tonight-at-10pm-video/206431/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131002144143/http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2013/10/02/mtv-to-premiere-miley-the-movement-tonight-at-10pm-video/206431/ |url-status=dead |archive-date=October 2, 2013 |title=MTV to Premiere 'Miley: The Movement' Tonight at 10PM (Video) |publisher=TVbytheNumbers |date=October 2, 2013 |access-date=October 7, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eonline.com/news/465684/miley-the-movement-sneak-peek-singer-says-mom-tish-cyrus-is-my-homie|title=Miley: The Movement Sneak Peek: Singer Says Mom Tish Cyrus Is My Homie|publisher=[[E! Online]]|date=October 2, 2013|access-date=October 7, 2013|archive-date=August 6, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230806033921/https://www.eonline.com/news/465684/miley-the-movement-sneak-peek-singer-says-mom-tish-cyrus-is-my-homie|url-status=live}}</ref> which was released on October 4.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/au/album/bangerz-deluxe-version/id691238659|title=iTunes – Music – Bangerz (Deluxe Version) by Miley Cyrus|publisher=iTunes Store (AU). Apple Inc|date=October 4, 2013|access-date=August 25, 2013|archive-date=October 12, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131012053819/https://itunes.apple.com/au/album/bangerz-deluxe-version/id691238659|url-status=live}}</ref> The album was a commercial success, debuting at number one on the ''Billboard'' 200 with first week sales of 270,000 copies.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/5755773/miley-cyrus-bangerz-debuts-at-no-1-on-billboard-200|title=Miley Cyrus' 'Bangerz' Debuts At No. 1 On Billboard 200|last=Caulfield|first=Keith|magazine=Billboard|date=October 16, 2013|access-date=October 16, 2013|archive-date=July 1, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180701002314/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/5755773/miley-cyrus-bangerz-debuts-at-no-1-on-billboard-200|url-status=live}}</ref> On October 5, Cyrus hosted ''Saturday Night Live'' for the second time.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://guardianlv.com/2013/10/miley-cyrus-hosted-worst-snl-episode-in-recent-history/ |title=Miley Cyrus Hosted Worst SNL Episode in Recent History |publisher=Guardian Liberty Voice |date=August 13, 2013 |access-date=October 7, 2013 |archive-date=February 22, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230222215444/https://guardianlv.com/2013/10/miley-cyrus-hosted-worst-snl-episode-in-recent-history/ |url-status=live }}</ref> On November 5, Cyrus featured on rapper [[Future (rapper)|Future]]'s "[[Real and True]]" with [[Mr. Hudson]]; an accompanying music video premiered five days later on November 10, 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/news/2013/11/05/mtv-to-world-premiere-futures-new-music-video-real-and-true-featuring-miley-cyrus-immediately-before-2013-mtv-ema-telecast-sunday-november-10-at-655pm-et-pt-115310/20131105mtv02/|title=MTV to World Premiere Future's New Music Video "Real & True" Featuring Miley Cyrus Immediately Before "2013 MTV EMA" Telecast Sunday, November 10 at 6:55PM ET/PT|website=The Futon Critic|date=November 5, 2013|access-date=November 5, 2013|archive-date=September 12, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190912172455/http://www.thefutoncritic.com/news/2013/11/05/mtv-to-world-premiere-futures-new-music-video-real-and-true-featuring-miley-cyrus-immediately-before-2013-mtv-ema-telecast-sunday-november-10-at-655pm-et-pt-115310/20131105mtv02/|url-status=live}}</ref> In late 2013 she was declared Artist of the Year by MTV.<ref>{{cite news |agency=Associated Press |url=http://www.utsandiego.com/news/2013/dec/09/mtv-declares-miley-cyrus-its-artist-of-the-year/ |title=MTV declares Miley Cyrus its artist of the year |website=The San Diego Union-Tribune |date=December 9, 2013 |access-date=January 12, 2014 |archive-date=March 25, 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150325130351/http://www.utsandiego.com/news/2013/dec/09/mtv-declares-miley-cyrus-its-artist-of-the-year/ |url-status=live }}</ref> 

On January 29, 2014, she played an acoustic concert show on ''[[MTV Unplugged]]'', performing songs from ''Bangerz'' featuring a guest appearance by [[Madonna]].<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/miley-cyrus-unplugged-10-hilarious-twerkcentric-observations-20140130|title=Miley Cyrus 'Unplugged': 10 Hilarious, Twerkcentric Observations|magazine=[[Rolling Stone]]|access-date=January 29, 2014|date=January 29, 2014|archive-date=January 31, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140131071352/http://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/miley-cyrus-unplugged-10-hilarious-twerkcentric-observations-20140130|url-status=dead}}</ref> It became the highest-rated ''MTV Unplugged'' in the past decade, with over 1.7{{nbsp}}million streams.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://hollywoodreporter.com/earshot/miley-cyrus-uncensored-mtv-unplugged-677724|title=Miley Cyrus' Uncensored 'MTV Unplugged' Performance Released|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|access-date=February 6, 2014|date=February 6, 2014|first=Ashley|last=Lee|archive-date=June 4, 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240604151100/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/music-news/miley-cyrus-uncensored-mtv-unplugged-677724/|url-status=live}}</ref> Cyrus was also featured in the [[Marc Jacobs]] Spring 2014 campaign along with [[Natalie Westling]] and Esmerelda Seay Reynolds.<ref>{{cite journal|url=http://www.wwd.com/media-news/fashion-memopad/marc-and-miley-7344293|access-date=April 5, 2014|date=January 9, 2014|title=Marc Jacobs Taps Miley Cyrus for Spring Campaign|first=Marc|last=Karimzadeh|journal=Women's Wear Daily|archive-date=December 17, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141217081710/http://www.wwd.com/media-news/fashion-memopad/marc-and-miley-7344293|url-status=live}}</ref> She launched her controversial [[Bangerz Tour]] (2014) that year, which was positively received by critics.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/music-arts/miley-meadowlands-show-surreal-lacks-substance-review-article-1.1745322|title=Bangerz Tour is Campy and Surreal|last=Farber|first=Jim|date=April 4, 2014|work=[[Daily News (New York)|New York Daily News]]|access-date=July 31, 2014|archive-date=April 11, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230411234558/https://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/music-arts/miley-meadowlands-show-surreal-lacks-substance-review-article-1.1745322|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://metro.co.uk/2014/02/15/miley-cyrus-bangerz-tour-kicks-off-in-canada-11-weird-moments-from-the-first-show-4305349/|title=Miley Cyrus Bangerz tour kicks off in Canada: 11 weird moments from the first show|last=Deen|first=Sarah|date=February 15, 2014|work=[[Metro International|Metro Canada]]|access-date=April 5, 2014|archive-date=April 6, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230406174429/https://metro.co.uk/2014/02/15/miley-cyrus-bangerz-tour-kicks-off-in-canada-11-weird-moments-from-the-first-show-4305349/|url-status=live}}</ref> Two months into her tour, Cyrus's [[Alaskan Klee Kai]] was found mauled to death at her home after fighting with a coyote. Two weeks later, Cyrus suffered an allergic reaction to the [[antibiotic]] [[cephalexin]], prescribed to treat a sinus infection,<ref>{{cite news|title=Miley Cyrus faces long recovery from 'extreme allergic reaction'|url=http://www.cnn.com/2014/04/17/showbiz/miley-cyrus-hospitalized/|work=CNN|last=Duke|first=Alan|date=April 18, 2014|access-date=April 29, 2014|archive-date=February 22, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230222215444/https://www.cnn.com/2014/04/17/showbiz/miley-cyrus-hospitalized/|url-status=live}}</ref> resulting in her hospitalization in [[Kansas City, Missouri|Kansas City]]. Though she rescheduled some of her US tour dates, she resumed the tour two weeks later, beginning with the European leg.<ref>{{cite web|title=Miley Cyrus leaves Kansas City for undisclosed location, still hospitalized |url=http://www.kansascity.com/2014/04/21/4974128/miley-cyrus-leaves-kansas-city.html |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140423222219/http://www.kansascity.com/2014/04/21/4974128/miley-cyrus-leaves-kansas-city.html |url-status=dead |archive-date=April 23, 2014 |work=The Kansas City Star |last=Gutierrez | first=Lisa |date=April 21, 2014 }}</ref>

While collaborating with [[the Flaming Lips]] on their remake of the Beatles' ''[[Sgt. Pepper's Lonely Hearts Club Band]]'', ''[[With a Little Help from My Fwends]]'',<ref name="Flaming1">{{cite magazine |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/flaming-lips-sgt-peppers-tribute-album-out-this-fall-20140515 |title=Flaming Lips' 'Sgt. Peppers' Tribute Album Out this Fall |date=May 16, 2014 |access-date=May 16, 2014 |magazine=Rolling Stone |archive-date=May 15, 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140515155125/http://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/flaming-lips-sgt-peppers-tribute-album-out-this-fall-20140515 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref name="flaming2">{{cite news | url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2014/oct/30/flaming-lips-with-a-little-help-fwends-review | title=The Flaming Lips: With a Little Help from My Fwends review – predictable Beatles cover album | newspaper=[[The Guardian]] | date=October 30, 2014 | access-date=May 7, 2015 | last=Dennis | first=Jon | archive-date=February 22, 2023 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230222215442/https://www.theguardian.com/music/2014/oct/30/flaming-lips-with-a-little-help-fwends-review | url-status=live }}</ref> Cyrus began working with [[Wayne Coyne]] on her fifth studio album.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.etonline.com/music/156740_miley_cyrus_thought_grammy_nomination_was_a_joke_works_on_new_album_every_day/|title=Miley Cyrus Works on New Album 'Every Day,' Thought Grammy Nom Was a 'Joke'|last=Krause|first=Katie|work=Entertainment Tonight|date=January 26, 2015|access-date=February 17, 2015|archive-date=February 22, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150222011835/http://www.etonline.com/music/156740_miley_cyrus_thought_grammy_nomination_was_a_joke_works_on_new_album_every_day/|url-status=live}}</ref> She said that she was taking her time to focus on the music, and that the album would not be released until she felt it was ready.<ref name="Retwired">{{cite web|url=https://people.com/tv/vmas-2014-miley-cyrus-teases-new-music-its-not-about-twerking/|title=Miley Cyrus Teases Her New Music: 'It's Not About Twerking'|last=Margaret|first=Mary|work=[[People (magazine)|People]]|date=August 24, 2014|access-date=March 7, 2019|archive-date=April 4, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190404171527/https://people.com/tv/vmas-2014-miley-cyrus-teases-new-music-its-not-about-twerking/|url-status=live}}</ref> Coyne compared his collaborative material with Cyrus to the catalogs of [[Pink Floyd]] and [[Portishead (band)|Portishead]] and described their sound as being "a slightly wiser, sadder, more true version" of Cyrus's pop music output.<ref name="flaming3">{{cite magazine | url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/the-flaming-lips-miley-cyrus-plot-trippy-collaborative-lp-20150504 | title=The Flaming Lips, Miley Cyrus Plot Trippy Collaborative LP | magazine=[[Rolling Stone]] | date=May 4, 2015 | access-date=May 6, 2015 | last=Reed | first=Ryan | archive-date=May 6, 2015 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150506210330/http://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/the-flaming-lips-miley-cyrus-plot-trippy-collaborative-lp-20150504 | url-status=dead }}</ref> Cyrus also worked on the films ''[[The Night Before (2015 film)|The Night Before]]'' (2015) and ''[[A Very Murray Christmas]]'' (2015) during this period; both roles were cameos.<ref>{{cite news|title=The Untitled X-Mas Project, starring Seth Rogen & Joseph Gordon Levitt, is filming at Rockefeller Center today|url=http://www.onlocationvacations.com/2015/01/05/the-untitled-x-mas-project-starring-seth-rogen-joseph-gordon-levitt-is-filming-at-rockefeller-center-today/|access-date=January 9, 2015|work=onlocationvacations.com|date=January 5, 2015|archive-date=October 22, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211022072805/https://onlocationvacations.com/2015/01/05/the-untitled-x-mas-project-starring-seth-rogen-joseph-gordon-levitt-is-filming-at-rockefeller-center-today/|url-status=live}}</ref> 

Reports began to surface in 2015 that Cyrus was working on two albums simultaneously, one of which she hoped to release at no charge.<ref name=freealbum>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6671437/miley-cyrus-next-album-not-a-miley-record|title=Miley Cyrus' Next Album is 'Not a Miley Record'|last=Aswad|first=Jem|magazine=Billboard|date=August 24, 2015|access-date=September 1, 2015|archive-date=August 28, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150828022321/http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6671437/miley-cyrus-next-album-not-a-miley-record|url-status=live}}</ref> This was confirmed by her manager who claimed she was willing to end her contract with RCA Records if they refused to let her release a free album.<ref name=freealbum /> Cyrus was the host of the [[2015 MTV Video Music Awards]], making her its first openly [[pansexual]] host, and gave a surprise performance of a new song "[[Dooo It!]]" (2015) during the show's finale.<ref>{{cite web |last=Ermac |first=Raffy |url=https://www.advocate.com/arts-entertainment/2015/08/30/young-stars-give-good-face-miley-cyrus-vmas-first-pansexual-host |title=Young Stars Give Good Face for Miley Cyrus, VMAs' First Pansexual Host |work=[[The Advocate (LGBT magazine)|The Advocate]] |date=August 30, 2015 |access-date=June 6, 2018 |archive-date=June 12, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612145314/https://www.advocate.com/arts-entertainment/2015/08/30/young-stars-give-good-face-miley-cyrus-vmas-first-pansexual-host |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name="MusicalVision">{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/09/01/arts/music/miley-cyrus-and-her-dead-petz.html|title=Inside the Making of 'Dead Petz,' Miley Cyrus's Surprise Album|last=Coscarelli|first=Joe|work=[[The New York Times]]|date=August 31, 2015|access-date=August 31, 2015|archive-date=July 26, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190726214750/https://www.nytimes.com/2015/09/01/arts/music/miley-cyrus-and-her-dead-petz.html|url-status=live}}</ref> Immediately following the performance, Cyrus announced that her fifth studio album, ''[[Miley Cyrus & Her Dead Petz]]'' (2015), was available for free streaming on [[SoundCloud]].<ref name="MusicalVision" /> The album was written and produced primarily by Cyrus, and has been called [[Experimental music|experimental]] and [[psychedelic music|psychedelic]],<ref name="LA Times review">{{cite web | url=https://latimes.com/entertainment/music/posts/la-et-ms-review-miley-cyrus-her-dead-petz-20150901-story.html | title='Miley Cyrus & Her Dead Petz': a wrecking ball in need of a target | website=[[Los Angeles Times]] | date=September 1, 2015 | access-date=September 3, 2015 | last=Wood | first=Mikael | archive-date=September 3, 2015 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150903222359/http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/music/posts/la-et-ms-review-miley-cyrus-her-dead-petz-20150901-story.html | url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://mashable.com/2015/09/02/miley-cyrus-dead-petz-album-review/|title=Sex, death and sadness: A look inside Miley's free 'Dead Petz' album|date=September 2, 2015|website=Mashable|access-date=September 3, 2015|archive-date=September 4, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150904093204/http://mashable.com/2015/09/02/miley-cyrus-dead-petz-album-review/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/2015-the-year-teen-pop-grew-up-20151214|title=2015: The Year Teen Pop Grew Up|magazine=Rolling Stone|access-date=January 14, 2016|date=December 14, 2015|archive-date=January 16, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160116125900/http://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/2015-the-year-teen-pop-grew-up-20151214|url-status=dead}}</ref> with elements of [[psychedelic pop]],<ref name="NME review">{{cite web|url=https://www.nme.com/reviews/miley-cyrus/16231|title=NME Reviews – Miley Cyrus – 'Miley Cyrus And Her Dead Petz'|last=Levine|first=Nick|work=NME|date=September 1, 2015|access-date=September 2, 2015|archive-date=September 3, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150903222815/http://www.nme.com/reviews/miley-cyrus/16231|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="NY Daily News review">{{cite web|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/music/miley-cyrus-dead-petz-album-review-article-1.2342757|title='Miley Cyrus & Her Dead Petz' : Album Review|last=Farber|first=Jim|work=New York Daily News|date=August 31, 2015|access-date=August 31, 2015|archive-date=September 2, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150902155447/http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/music/miley-cyrus-dead-petz-album-review-article-1.2342757|url-status=live}}</ref> [[psychedelic rock]],<ref name="Billboard review">{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/review/6678826/miley-cyrus-her-dead-petz-album-review|title=Miley Cyrus Leaves Pop Behind (For Now) on 'Miley Cyrus & Her Dead Petz': Album Review|magazine=Billboard|date=August 31, 2015|access-date=August 31, 2015|archive-date=July 25, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180725143206/https://www.billboard.com/articles/review/6678826/miley-cyrus-her-dead-petz-album-review|url-status=live}}</ref> and [[alternative pop]].<ref name="Entertainment Weekly review">{{cite web|url=https://ew.com/article/2015/09/01/miley-cyrus-and-her-dead-petz-review|title='Miley Cyrus and Her Dead Petz' review|last=Anderson|first=Kyle|work=Entertainment Weekly.|date=September 1, 2015|access-date=September 2, 2015|archive-date=September 3, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150903181636/http://www.ew.com/article/2015/09/01/miley-cyrus-and-her-dead-petz-review|url-status=live}}</ref>

===2016–2017: ''The Voice'' and ''Younger Now''===
[[File:170526-N-EO381-052 Miley Cyrus on Today show.jpg|thumb|upright|left|Cyrus performing on ''[[Today (American TV program)|The Today Show]]'' in 2017]]

In 2016, following the release of her fifth studio album the previous year, Cyrus resumed working on her sixth studio effort.<ref>{{Cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/6693000/miley-cyrus-next-album-mtv-vmas|title=What's Next for Miley Cyrus?|last=Halperin|first=Shirley|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=September 10, 2015|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150912153957/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/6693000/miley-cyrus-next-album-mtv-vmas|archive-date=September 12, 2015|access-date=March 5, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.youthhealthmag.com/articles/32726/20160117/miley-cyrus-new-album-2016.htm|title=Miley Cyrus New Album For 2016 Confirmed? Singer Engaged Again To Liam Hemsworth?|date=January 17, 2016|work=Youth Health Magazine|access-date=July 31, 2016|archive-date=May 6, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170506083103/http://www.youthhealthmag.com/articles/32726/20160117/miley-cyrus-new-album-2016.htm|url-status=live}}</ref> She was a key advisor during the [[The Voice (U.S. season 10)|tenth season]] of the reality singing competition ''[[The Voice (American TV series)|The Voice]]''.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/7311482/miley-cyrus-the-voice-coach|title=Miley Cyrus Joining 'The Voice' as a Coach|last=Stanhope|first=Kate|magazine=Billboard|date=March 25, 2016|access-date=March 25, 2016|archive-date=April 3, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190403090616/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/7311482/miley-cyrus-the-voice-coach|url-status=live}}</ref> In March, Cyrus had signed on as a coach for the [[The Voice (U.S. season 11)|eleventh season]] of ''The Voice'' as a replacement for [[Gwen Stefani]]; Cyrus became the youngest coach to appear in any incarnation of the series.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Iannucci|first1=Rebecca|title=''The Voice'': Miley Cyrus, Alicia Keys Confirmed as Season 11 Coaches|url=http://tvline.com/2016/03/25/the-voice-miley-cyrus-season-11-judge/|website=[[TVLine]]|access-date=March 25, 2016|location=United States|date=March 25, 2016|archive-date=August 12, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160812084823/https://tvline.com/2016/03/25/the-voice-miley-cyrus-season-11-judge/|url-status=live}}</ref> In September 2016, Cyrus co-starred in ''[[Crisis in Six Scenes]]'', a television series [[Woody Allen]] created for [[Amazon Studios]]. She played a radical activist who causes chaos in a conservative 1960s household while hiding from the police.<ref>{{cite magazine |url=https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2016/09/miley-cyrus-woody-allen-amazon |title=Miley Cyrus Explains Why She's in Awe of Woody Allen: 'He's Never Fake' |magazine=Vanity Fair |date=September 16, 2016 |last=Chi |first=Paul |access-date=July 15, 2021 |archive-date=September 19, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200919133644/https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2016/09/miley-cyrus-woody-allen-amazon |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/tv/news/watch-first-clip-from-woody-allens-crisis-in-six-scenes-tv-show-w433176 |title=Watch First Clip From Woody Allen's 'Crisis in Six Scenes' TV Show |magazine=Rolling Stone |date=August 8, 2016 |last=Kreps |first=Daniel |access-date=July 15, 2021 |archive-date=September 23, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170923032103/http://www.rollingstone.com/tv/news/watch-first-clip-from-woody-allens-crisis-in-six-scenes-tv-show-w433176 |url-status=dead }}</ref> On September 17, 2016, she appeared on ''[[The Tonight Show Starring Jimmy Fallon]]'' and covered [[Bob Dylan]]'s "Baby, I'm In the Mood for You".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://huffingtonpost.com/entry/miley-cyrus-jimmy-fallon-donald-trump-controversy_us_57ddb5eee4b0071a6e07bf77 |title=Miley Cyrus Pauses Performance To Comment On Fallon's Trump Controversy |last=Bradley |first=Bill |website=The Huffington Post |date=September 17, 2016 |access-date=July 15, 2021 |archive-date=May 17, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170517071429/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/miley-cyrus-jimmy-fallon-donald-trump-controversy_us_57ddb5eee4b0071a6e07bf77 |url-status=live }}</ref> Cyrus also had an uncredited voice cameo as [[Mainframe (comics)|Mainframe]] in the superhero film ''[[Guardians of the Galaxy Vol. 2]]'', released in May 2017.

On May 11, 2017, Cyrus released "[[Malibu (Miley Cyrus song)|Malibu]]" as the lead single from her sixth album.<ref>{{cite magazine|last1=Norris|first1=John|author-link1=John Norris (reporter)|title=Miley Cyrus Breaks Silence on Rootsy New Music, Fiance Liam Hemsworth & America: 'Unity Is What We Need'|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/magazine-feature/7783997/miley-cyrus-cover-story-new-music-malibu|access-date=May 4, 2017|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=May 3, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170504130342/http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/magazine-feature/7783997/miley-cyrus-cover-story-new-music-malibu|archive-date=May 4, 2017|location=United States}}</ref> The single debuted at No. 64 on the ''Billboard'' Hot 100 and peaked at No. 10 on the chart on its second week.<ref>{{cite magazine|first=Gary|last=Trust|title=Hot 100 Chart Moves: Miley Cyrus Makes Waves With 'Malibu'|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/7800256/miley-cyrus-malibu-hot-100-chart-moves|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=May 18, 2017|location=United States|access-date=April 20, 2020|archive-date=March 30, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190330215428/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/7800256/miley-cyrus-malibu-hot-100-chart-moves|url-status=live}}</ref> On June 9, Cyrus released "[[Inspired (Miley Cyrus song)|Inspired]]" after performing the song at the [[One Love Manchester]] benefit concert.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://pitchfork.com/news/74085-listen-to-miley-cyrus-new-song-inspired |title=Listen to Miley Cyrus' New Song "Inspired" |website=Pitchfork |date=June 9, 2017 |last=Strauss |first=Matthew |access-date=July 15, 2021 |archive-date=May 17, 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210517031320/https://pitchfork.com/news/74085-listen-to-miley-cyrus-new-song-inspired/ |url-status=live }}</ref> It served as a promotional single from the album. On August 8, Cyrus announced that her sixth studio album would be titled ''[[Younger Now]]'' and would be released on September 29, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mileycyrus.com/|title=Miley Cyrus|website=Miley Cyrus|access-date=August 23, 2017|archive-date=October 9, 2009|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091009113132/http://www.mileycyrus.com/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eska.pl/news/miley_cyrus_wraca_z_younger_now_data_premiery_i_okladka_nowej_plyty_2017/144774|title=Miley Cyrus wraca z Younger Now: data premiery i okładka nowej płyty 2017|website=Eska.pl|access-date=August 23, 2017|archive-date=June 16, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180616030726/http://www.eska.pl/news/miley_cyrus_wraca_z_younger_now_data_premiery_i_okladka_nowej_plyty_2017/144774|url-status=live}}</ref> The album's title track was released as the second single from the album on August 18 and debuted and peaked at No. 79 on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]].<ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://www.billboard.com/artist/miley-cyrus/chart-history/hsi/ |title=Miley Cyrus - Billboard Hot 100 |magazine=Billboard |access-date=November 24, 2021 |archive-date=August 1, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180801012540/https://www.billboard.com/music/miley-cyrus/chart-history/hot-100 |url-status=live }}</ref> On August 27, Cyrus performed the track at the [[2017 MTV Video Music Awards]].<ref>{{cite magazine|first=Joyce|last=Chen|title=VMAs 2017: Watch Miley Cyrus Go Retro in 'Younger Now' Performance|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/vmas-2017-miley-cyrus-goes-retro-in-younger-now-performance-w499120|magazine=[[Rolling Stone]]|date=August 27, 2017|location=United States|access-date=September 5, 2017|archive-date=June 16, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180616030811/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/vmas-2017-miley-cyrus-goes-retro-in-younger-now-performance-w499120|url-status=dead}}</ref> On September 15, she performed "Malibu", "[[Younger Now (song)|Younger Now]]", "[[See You Again (Miley Cyrus song)|See You Again]]", "[[Party in the U.S.A.]]" and a cover of the [[Roberta Flack]] hit "[[The First Time Ever I Saw Your Face]]" (written by [[Ewan McColl]]) for the [[BBC Radio 1]] [[Live Lounge]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.mtv.co.uk/news/6xjg3p/miley-cyrus-returned-to-live-lounge-and-performed-see-you-again-in-the-year-2017|title=Miley Cyrus Returned To Live Lounge And Performed 'See You Again' In The Year 2017|date=September 15, 2017|work=[[MTV News]]|access-date=September 15, 2017|archive-date=March 30, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190330143454/http://www.mtv.co.uk/miley-cyrus/news/miley-cyrus-returned-to-live-lounge-and-performed-see-you-again-in-the-year-2017|url-status=live}}</ref> On October 2, as part of her one-week regular musical appearances on ''[[The Tonight Show Starring Jimmy Fallon]]'', Cyrus sang her 2009 hit single "The Climb" for the first time since 2011 alongside a cover of "[[No Freedom]]" by [[Dido (singer)|Dido]] to honor the victims of the [[2017 Las Vegas shooting|Las Vegas shooting]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Farley|first=Rebecca|title=Miley Cyrus Performed "The Climb" For The First Time In Years — & It Was Chilling|url=https://www.refinery29.com/en-us/2017/10/174938/miley-cyrus-fallon-las-vegas-no-freedom-the-climb|access-date=June 23, 2021|website=Refinery29|archive-date=June 24, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210624202958/https://www.refinery29.com/en-us/2017/10/174938/miley-cyrus-fallon-las-vegas-no-freedom-the-climb|url-status=live}}</ref> The former song has since been performed at multiple charity events, protests, and marches, including at the [[March for Our Lives|March For Our Lives]] demonstrations in [[Washington, D.C.]]<ref>{{Cite news|title=March For Our Lives: Miley Cyrus, Kim Kardashian & More Show Support In and Beyond D.C.|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/8258915/miley-cyrus-kim-kardashian-march-for-our-lives-tweets/|access-date=June 23, 2021|magazine=Billboard|archive-date=June 26, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210626120005/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/8258915/miley-cyrus-kim-kardashian-march-for-our-lives-tweets/|url-status=live}}</ref> That same year, Cyrus returned as a coach in the [[The Voice (U.S. season 13)|thirteenth season]] of ''The Voice'' after taking a one-season hiatus.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2016/tv/news/the-voice-renewed-season-12-13-gwen-stefani-miley-cyrus-1201891741/|title='The Voice' Renewed Through Season 13 — Which Coaches Are Returning?|first=Elizabeth|last=Wagmeister|date=October 18, 2016|website=Variety|access-date=August 23, 2017|archive-date=March 30, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190330143504/https://variety.com/2016/tv/news/the-voice-renewed-season-12-13-gwen-stefani-miley-cyrus-1201891741/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goldderby.com/article/2017/the-voice-jennifer-hudson-miley-cyrus-coach-season-13/|title='The Voice': Jennifer Hudson, Miley Cyrus to coach in season 13|first=Paul|last=Sheehan|date=May 11, 2017|website=Goldderby.com|access-date=August 23, 2017|archive-date=February 24, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230224100847/https://www.goldderby.com/article/2017/the-voice-jennifer-hudson-miley-cyrus-coach-season-13/|url-status=live}}</ref> On October 5, 2017, Cyrus confirmed that she would not be returning to ''The Voice'' for season fourteen.<ref name="Miley Cyrus Leaving">{{cite web|url=https://www.inquisitr.com/4537728/miley-cyrus-done-leaving-the-voice-wont-return-season-14/|title=Miley Cyrus Confirms She's 'Done' With 'The Voice', Won't Return For Season 14|date=October 5, 2017|access-date=November 24, 2017|archive-date=March 30, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190330154631/https://www.inquisitr.com/4537728/miley-cyrus-done-leaving-the-voice-wont-return-season-14/|url-status=live}}</ref> On October 30, 2017, Cyrus revealed she would not release any further singles from ''Younger Now'', nor would she tour for it.<ref name=mtvoct30>{{cite web|url=https://www.mtv.co.uk/news/334bo7/miley-cyrus-isnt-releasing-any-more-younger-now-singles|title=Miley Cyrus Isn't Releasing Any More 'Younger Now' Singles|work=MTV|date=October 30, 2017|access-date=November 4, 2017|archive-date=December 6, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181206172050/http://www.mtv.co.uk/miley-cyrus/news/miley-cyrus-isnt-releasing-any-more-younger-now-singles|url-status=live}}</ref>

===2018–2019: ''She Is Coming'' and ''Black Mirror''===
Before the release of ''Younger Now'' in September 2017, Cyrus expressed she was "already two songs deep on the next [album]."<ref>{{cite web|url=https://people.com/music/miley-cyrus-already-over-new-album/|title=Miley Cyrus Is Already 'Over' Her New Album: 'I Want To Figure Out What I Want to Do Next'|last=Quinn|first=Dave|work=[[People (magazine)|People]]|date=September 17, 2017|access-date=November 29, 2018|archive-date=November 30, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181130030315/https://people.com/music/miley-cyrus-already-over-new-album/|url-status=live}}</ref> Producers attached to her seventh studio album included previous collaborator [[Mike Will Made It]] and new collaborators [[Mark Ronson]] and [[Andrew Wyatt]].<ref>{{cite magazine| url=https://www.billboard.com/amp/articles/news/dance/8463046/miley-cyrus-mark-ronson-wrote-song-together| title=Miley Cyrus and Mark Ronson Have a Song 'Coming Soon'| magazine=Billboard| date=June 27, 2018| access-date=August 11, 2018| archive-date=September 6, 2018| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180906111115/https://www.billboard.com/amp/articles/news/dance/8463046/miley-cyrus-mark-ronson-wrote-song-together| url-status=live}}</ref> Her first collaboration with Ronson, "[[Nothing Breaks Like a Heart]]" from his 2019 album ''[[Late Night Feelings]]'', was released on November 29, 2018, to great commercial reception, especially in Europe, where it peaked at number two on the [[UK Singles Chart]] as well as in [[Ireland]] and topped the charts in several [[Eastern Europe]]an countries including [[Hungary]] or [[Croatia]].<ref>{{cite web| url=https://consequence.net/2018/11/miley-cyrus-new-single-nothing-breaks-like-a-heart/| title=Miley Cyrus to release new single "Nothing Breaks Like a Heart"| website=Consequence Of Sound.net| date=November 26, 2018| access-date=January 17, 2023| archive-date=January 17, 2023| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230117015419/https://consequence.net/2018/11/miley-cyrus-new-single-nothing-breaks-like-a-heart/| url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| url=https://www.idolator.com/7688637/miley-cyrus-release-date-nothing-breaks-like-a-heart?edge=1| title=Miley Cyrus Confirms a Release Date for "Nothing Breaks Like a Heart"| website=Idolator.com| date=November 26, 2018| access-date=November 29, 2018| archive-date=June 4, 2024| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240604151248/https://www.idolator.com/7688637/miley-cyrus-release-date-nothing-breaks-like-a-heart?edge=1| url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url=http://time.com/5338162/miley-cyrus-instagram/ | title=Miley Cyrus Just Deleted All of Her Instagram Posts | website=Time.com | access-date=November 13, 2018 | archive-date=April 11, 2023 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230411234558/https://time.com/5338162/miley-cyrus-instagram/ | url-status=live }}</ref>

During the first quarter of 2019, Cyrus became quite notable for her cover songs.<ref>{{cite web|last=Cubit|first=Brea|date=October 19, 2020|title=19 Times Miley Cyrus Honoured Other Artists With Applause-Worthy Song Covers|url=https://www.popsugar.co.uk/node/47592839|access-date=June 23, 2021|website=POPSUGAR Entertainment UK}}</ref> Having already taken part in [[MusiCares Person of the Year]] in 2018 celebrating [[Fleetwood Mac]], she returned the year after to honor the career of her godmother [[Dolly Parton]] by performing "[[Islands in the Stream (song)|Islands in the Stream]]" alongside Canadian singer-songwriter [[Shawn Mendes]], with who she also performed "[[In My Blood (Shawn Mendes song)|In My Blood]]" a couple days later at the [[61st Grammy Awards]].<ref>{{Cite news|title=Miley Cyrus sings Dolly Parton's hit duet Islands In the Stream as tribute to the legend|url=https://www.thenews.com.pk/latest/817449-miley-cyrus-pays-tribute-to-dolly-parton-in-a-show-streamed-by-netflix|access-date=June 23, 2021|newspaper=The News International|archive-date=June 24, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210624204218/https://www.thenews.com.pk/latest/817449-miley-cyrus-pays-tribute-to-dolly-parton-in-a-show-streamed-by-netflix|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine|title=Miley Cyrus Joins Shawn Mendes for 'In My Blood' at 2019 Grammys|url=https://www.billboard.com/video/bbnews021019mendesgrammy-8497605|access-date=June 23, 2021|magazine=Billboard|archive-date=June 26, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210626151535/https://www.billboard.com/video/bbnews021019mendesgrammy-8497605|url-status=live}}</ref> Cyrus's other covers include her version of [[Ariana Grande]]'s "[[No Tears Left to Cry]]" for [[BBC Radio]]'s [[Live Lounge]], her participation at the [[Chris Cornell]] tribute concert I Am The Highway, where she sang "As Hope & Promise Fade" as well as her cover record of [[Elton John]]'s "[[Don't Let the Sun Go Down on Me|Don't Let The Sun Go Down On Me]]", included in the tribute album ''[[Revamp: Reimagining the Songs of Elton John & Bernie Taupin]].''<ref>{{Cite news|date=March 15, 2018|title=Elton John Announces Two Cover Albums Featuring Miley Cyrus, Lady Gaga and Ed Sheeran|url=https://www.eonline.com/news/920883/elton-john-announces-two-cover-albums-featuring-miley-cyrus-lady-gaga-and-ed-sheeran|access-date=June 23, 2021|agency=E!|archive-date=June 24, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210624203356/https://www.eonline.com/news/920883/elton-john-announces-two-cover-albums-featuring-miley-cyrus-lady-gaga-and-ed-sheeran|url-status=live}}</ref> Cyrus also honored John at the I'm Still Standing: A Grammy Salute to Elton John tribute concert in 2018, where she covered "[[The Bitch Is Back]]".<ref>{{cite web|title=Miley Cyrus version of Elton John's 'The Bitch is Back' could not be a more appropriate choice for her|publisher=Leosigh.com|date=April 6, 2018|url=https://leosigh.com/miley-cyrus-version-of-elton-johns-the-bitch-is-back-could-not-be-a-more-appropriate-choice-for-her/|access-date=June 23, 2021|archive-date=June 24, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210624203324/https://leosigh.com/miley-cyrus-version-of-elton-johns-the-bitch-is-back-could-not-be-a-more-appropriate-choice-for-her/|url-status=live}}</ref>

[[File:Miley Cyrus Primavera19 -231 (48986108626) (cropped).jpg|thumb|upright|Cyrus performing ''[[She Is Coming]]'' at [[Primavera Sound]]]]

On May 31, 2019, Cyrus tweeted that her seventh studio album would be titled ''She Is Miley Cyrus'' and would comprise three six-song EPs, which would be released before the full-length album: ''[[She Is Coming]]'' on May 31, ''She Is Here'' in the summer, and ''She Is Everything'' in the fall.<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Blistein|first=Jon|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/miley-cyrus-new-music-she-is-coming-840693/|title=Miley Cyrus Plots New Project 'She Is Coming'|magazine=[[Rolling Stone]]|date=May 27, 2019|access-date=May 27, 2019|archive-date=June 4, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190604111240/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/miley-cyrus-new-music-she-is-coming-840693/|url-status=live}}</ref> ''She Is Coming'', which also included vocal collaborations with [[RuPaul]], [[Swae Lee]], [[Mike Will Made It]] and [[Ghostface Killah]], debuted at number five on the US ''Billboard'' 200 with 36,000 album-equivalent units,<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8515077/thomas-rhett-no-1-billboard-200-albums-chart-center-point-road|title=Thomas Rhett Scores Second No. 1 on Billboard 200 Albums Chart With 'Center Point Road'|last=Caulfield|first=Keith|magazine=Billboard|date=June 9, 2019|access-date=June 10, 2019|archive-date=October 22, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191022044916/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8515077/thomas-rhett-no-1-billboard-200-albums-chart-center-point-road|url-status=live}}</ref> while the lead single "[[Mother's Daughter (song)|Mother's Daughter]]" entered at number 54 on the US ''Billboard'' Hot 100.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/hughmcintyre/2019/06/15/x---katy-perry-cardi-b-and-miley-cyrus-five-important-moves-on-this-weeks-hot-100/#4ad73e7f2673|title=Katy Perry, Cardi B And Miley Cyrus: Five Important Moves On This Week's Hot 100|last=McIntyre|first=Hugh|work=Forbes|date=June 15, 2019|access-date=June 15, 2019|archive-date=July 6, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190706185529/https://www.forbes.com/sites/hughmcintyre/2019/06/15/x---katy-perry-cardi-b-and-miley-cyrus-five-important-moves-on-this-weeks-hot-100/#4ad73e7f2673|url-status=live}}</ref> The [[Wuki]] remix of "Mother's Daughter" received a nomination for [[Grammy Award for Best Remixed Recording, Non-Classical|Best Remixed Recording]] at the [[62nd Annual Grammy Awards]] while the original music video won two [[MTV Video Music Awards]].<ref>{{cite web|title=MTV VMAs 2020: Best Editing award goes to Miley Cyrus's 'Mother's Daughter', Internet bows to 'the queen'|url=https://meaww.com/mtv-vma-2020-best-editing-award-winner-mylie-cyrus-mothers-daughter-activists-models-women-power|access-date=June 23, 2021|website=meaww|date=August 31, 2020 |archive-date=September 30, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210930003946/https://meaww.com/mtv-vma-2020-best-editing-award-winner-mylie-cyrus-mothers-daughter-activists-models-women-power|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|date=November 23, 2020|title=Wuki|url=https://www.grammy.com/grammys/artists/wuki/252063|access-date=June 23, 2021|agency=Grammy Awards|archive-date=September 26, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210926102620/https://www.grammy.com/grammys/artists/wuki/252063|url-status=live}}</ref> Cyrus promoted the EP with a summer European tour that visited A-list festivals like [[Glastonbury Festival|Glastonbury]] and [[Primavera Sound]].<ref>{{Cite magazine|title=Miley Cyrus Performs as Ashley O, Brings Out Her Dad & Lil Nas X at Glastonbury: Watch|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/8518135/miley-cyrus-glastonbury-performance-videos/|access-date=June 23, 2021|magazine=Billboard|archive-date=June 27, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210627004955/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/8518135/miley-cyrus-glastonbury-performance-videos/|url-status=live}}</ref>

Cyrus starred in "[[Rachel, Jack and Ashley Too]]", an episode of the [[Netflix]] sci-fi series ''[[Black Mirror]]'', which was filmed in South Africa in November 2018. It was released on Netflix on June 5, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.iheart.com/content/2019-05-15-black-mirror-season-5-trailer-stars-miley-cyrus-unveils-release-date/|title='Black Mirror' Season 5 Trailer Stars Miley Cyrus, Unveils Release Date|last=Brooks|first=Hayden|publisher=iHeartRadio|date=May 15, 2019|access-date=June 15, 2019|archive-date=February 23, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230223190053/https://www.iheart.com/content/2019-05-15-black-mirror-season-5-trailer-stars-miley-cyrus-unveils-release-date/|url-status=live}}</ref> In the episode, she played fictional pop star Ashley O and voiced her [[Artificial intelligence|AI]] doll extension, Ashley Too. The plot was compared to [[Britney Spears]]'s [[conservatorship]] and the [[Free Britney|Free Britney movement]], which Cyrus has been an advocate for.<ref>{{Cite magazine|date=June 6, 2019|title=Is Miley Cyrus' 'Black Mirror' Episode Part of #FreeBritney?|url=https://www.papermag.com/miley-cyrus-black-mirror-britney-spears-2638714814.html?rebelltitem=12#rebelltitem12?rebelltitem=12|access-date=June 23, 2021|magazine=Paper|archive-date=February 23, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230223190052/https://www.papermag.com/miley-cyrus-black-mirror-britney-spears-2638714814.html?rebelltitem=12#rebelltitem12?rebelltitem=12|url-status=live}}</ref> The music video for the song "[[On a Roll]]" from the episode was released on June 13;<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8516049/miley-cyrus-black-mirror-right-where-it-belongs-ashley-o-listen|title=Ashley O Is Back: Listen to New Miley Cyrus 'Black Mirror' Song 'Right Where I Belong'|last=Spruch|first=Kirsten|magazine=Billboard|date=June 13, 2019|access-date=June 15, 2019|archive-date=October 3, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211003075943/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8516049/miley-cyrus-black-mirror-right-where-it-belongs-ashley-o-listen/|url-status=live}}</ref> the song itself and the B-side "Right Where I Belong" were released to digital platforms the next day.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://music.apple.com/us/album/on-a-roll-single/1468372211|title=On a Roll &ndash; Single by Ashley O on Apple Music|publisher=Apple Inc.|date=June 14, 2019|access-date=June 15, 2019|archive-date=February 5, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230205153911/https://music.apple.com/us/album/on-a-roll-single/1468372211|url-status=live}}</ref>

On June 27, it was revealed that Cyrus had collaborated with [[Ariana Grande]] and [[Lana Del Rey]] on "[[Don't Call Me Angel]]", the lead single of the soundtrack to the 2019 film ''[[Charlie's Angels (2019 film)|Charlie's Angels]].''<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://ew.com/music/2019/06/27/miley-cyrus-ariana-grande-lana-del-rey-charlies-angels-song/|title=Miley Cyrus, Ariana Grande, Lana Del Rey team up for Charlie's Angels theme song|magazine=Entertainment Weekly|date=June 27, 2019|access-date=July 24, 2019|archive-date=November 8, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191108023841/https://ew.com/music/2019/06/27/miley-cyrus-ariana-grande-lana-del-rey-charlies-angels-song/|url-status=live}}</ref> It was released on September 13, 2019.<ref>{{cite news |last=Garvey |first=Marianne |url=https://www.cnn.com/2019/09/13/entertainment/ariana-grande-miley-cyrus-lana-del-rey-charlies-angels/index.html |title=Ariana Grande, Miley Cyrus and Lana Del Rey release 'Don't Call Me Angel' video |work=CNN |date=September 13, 2019 |access-date=September 25, 2019 |archive-date=September 25, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190925022929/https://www.cnn.com/2019/09/13/entertainment/ariana-grande-miley-cyrus-lana-del-rey-charlies-angels/index.html |url-status=live }}</ref> In August 2019, Cyrus released "[[Slide Away (Miley Cyrus song)|Slide Away]]", her first song since announcing her separation from then-husband Hemsworth. The song hinted at their breakup and contained lyrics such as "Move on, we're not 17, I'm not who I used to be".<ref>{{cite magazine |url=https://ew.com/music/2019/08/16/miley-cyrus-releases-breakup-song-slide-away-liam-hemsworth-split/ |title=Miley Cyrus releases emotional breakup song 'Slide Away' after Liam Hemsworth split |last=Yang |first=Rachel |date=August 16, 2019 |magazine=Entertainment Weekly |access-date=August 16, 2019 |archive-date=May 28, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230528181835/https://ew.com/music/2019/08/16/miley-cyrus-releases-breakup-song-slide-away-liam-hemsworth-split/ |url-status=live }}</ref> A music video was released in September 2019 that contained further references, including a [[Standard 52-card deck|ten of hearts playing card]] at the bottom of a pool to represent the end of her decade-long relationship with Hemsworth.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cosmopolitan.com/entertainment/celebs/a28941032/miley-cyrus-slide-away-music-video-liam-hemsworth-references-easter-eggs-fan-reactions/ |title=Fans Are Freaking Out About Miley Cyrus's "Slide Away" Music Video and All the Liam Hemsworth Easter Eggs |last=Barbour |first=Shannon |date=September 6, 2019 |website=Cosmopolitan |access-date=September 13, 2019 |archive-date=September 11, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190911063612/https://www.cosmopolitan.com/entertainment/celebs/a28941032/miley-cyrus-slide-away-music-video-liam-hemsworth-references-easter-eggs-fan-reactions/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

===2020–2022: ''Plastic Hearts'' and television projects===
On August 14, 2020, Cyrus released the lead single from her seventh studio album, "[[Midnight Sky]]" and confirmed the cancellation of the EPs ''She Is Here'' and ''She Is Everything'' due to major recent changes in her life that did not fit the essence of the project, including her divorce from Hemsworth, and the burning of the couple's house during the [[Woolsey Fire]] in [[California]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Copsey|first=Rob|date=August 14, 2020|title=Miley Cyrus isn't planning to release an album any time soon: 'It doesn't make sense for me'|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/miley-cyrus-isnt-planning-to-release-an-album-any-time-soon-it-doesnt-make-sense-for-me__30761/|access-date=August 14, 2020|archive-date=September 18, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200918163101/https://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/miley-cyrus-isnt-planning-to-release-an-album-any-time-soon-it-doesnt-make-sense-for-me__30761/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Cyrus |first=Miley |date=November 12, 2018 |title=Completely devastated by the fires affecting my family. I am one of the lucky ones. My animals and... |url=https://www.facebook.com/story.php?story_fbid=10156917914262147&id=5845317146 |access-date=July 17, 2022 |website=Miley Cyrus on [[Facebook]] |archive-date=November 7, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231107192008/https://www.facebook.com/story.php?story_fbid=10156917914262147&id=5845317146 |url-status=live }}</ref> "Midnight Sky" became her highest-charting solo single since "[[Malibu (Miley Cyrus song)|Malibu]]" in 2017, peaking at number 14 on the US ''Billboard'' Hot 100. Internationally, in the United Kingdom the song has thus far peaked at number five on the [[UK Singles Chart]]. The track was later [[Mashup (music)|mashed up]] with [[Stevie Nicks]]' "[[Edge of Seventeen]]".<ref>{{cite web|date=November 6, 2020|title=Miley Cyrus and Stevie Nicks join forces for 'Midnight Sky/Edge of Seventeen' mash-up|url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/miley-cyrus-and-stevie-nicks-join-forces-for-midnight-sky-edge-of-seventeen-mash-up-2810466|access-date=June 23, 2021|website=NME|archive-date=June 24, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210624204519/https://www.nme.com/news/music/miley-cyrus-and-stevie-nicks-join-forces-for-midnight-sky-edge-of-seventeen-mash-up-2810466|url-status=live}}</ref> 

In October, Cyrus had a third [[Backyard Sessions|Backyard Session]] on [[MTV]] and announced via Instagram that her seventh studio album ''[[Plastic Hearts]]'' would be released on November 27, 2020.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/miley-cyrus-new-album-plastic-hearts-1076491/ |title=Miley Cyrus Announces Seventh Album 'Plastic Hearts' |date=October 23, 2020 |last=Spanos |first=Brittany |access-date=October 23, 2020 |archive-date=October 25, 2020 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20201025111337/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/miley-cyrus-new-album-plastic-hearts-1076491/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Curto|first=Justin|date=October 16, 2020|title=Here's What Happened in Miley Cyrus's MTV Unplugged 'Backyard Sessions' Special|url=https://www.vulture.com/2020/10/miley-cyrus-backyard-sessions-mtv-2020.html|access-date=June 23, 2021|website=Vulture|archive-date=June 4, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230604081739/https://www.vulture.com/2020/10/miley-cyrus-backyard-sessions-mtv-2020.html|url-status=live}}</ref> It was previously intended to be called ''She Is Miley Cyrus'', completing the EP series once finalized.<ref>{{cite web|title="She is Miley Cyrus", todo lo que debes saber del álbum|url=https://www.grupolegado.com.mx/legado/MUS/She_is_Miley_Cyrus_todo_lo_que_debes_saber_del_album|access-date=June 23, 2021|website=Grupo Legado|language=es|archive-date=June 24, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210624202730/https://www.grupolegado.com.mx/legado/MUS/She_is_Miley_Cyrus_todo_lo_que_debes_saber_del_album|url-status=live}}</ref> The album was released to positive reviews from critics and performed well, debuting at number two on the Billboard 200, with 60,000 units, becoming her twelfth top ten entry on the chart. With that entry, Cyrus broke the record for attaining the most US [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]] top-five albums in the 21st century by a female music artist. ''Plastic Hearts'' marked a step of Cyrus into [[Rock music|rock]] and [[glam rock]] music and spawned two other singles: "[[Prisoner (Miley Cyrus song)|Prisoner]]" featuring English singer [[Dua Lipa]] and "[[Angels like You]]", which peaked at 8 and 66 respectively in the United Kingdom.<ref>{{cite web|last=Buksbaum|first=Sydney|date=November 20, 2020|title=Miley Cyrus and Dua Lipa Take a Sexy, Bloody Road Trip in 'Prisoner' Music Video|url=https://people.com/music/miley-cyrus-dua-lipa-prisoner-music-video/|access-date=November 26, 2020|website=People|archive-date=December 10, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201210053237/https://people.com/music/miley-cyrus-dua-lipa-prisoner-music-video/|url-status=live}}</ref> The album also included vocal collaborations with [[Billy Idol]] and [[Joan Jett]]. Due to popular demand and social media virality, Cyrus included the live covers of [[Blondie (band)|Blondie]]'s "[[Heart of Glass (song)|Heart of Glass]]" and [[The Cranberries]]' "[[Zombie (The Cranberries song)|Zombie]]".<ref>{{cite web|date=November 27, 2020|title=''Plastic Hearts'' by Miley Cyrus|url=https://open.spotify.com/album/5BRhg6NSEZOj0BR6Iz56fR?si=7Trihb9_QE6GQgPAGav1kA|access-date=November 27, 2020|publisher=[[Spotify]]|archive-date=August 20, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210820093704/https://open.spotify.com/album/5BRhg6NSEZOj0BR6Iz56fR?si=7Trihb9_QE6GQgPAGav1kA|url-status=live}}</ref>

Cyrus won a [[2020 Webby Awards|2020 Webby Special Achievement Award]].<ref name="Kastrenakes">{{cite web|last1=Kastrenakes|first1=Jacob|date=May 20, 2020|title=Here are all the winners of the 2020 Webby Awards|url=https://www.theverge.com/2020/5/20/21263445/2020-webby-awards-winners-lil-nas-x-nasa-jon-krasinski|access-date=May 22, 2020|website=The Verge|archive-date=October 2, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201002020426/https://www.theverge.com/2020/5/20/21263445/2020-webby-awards-winners-lil-nas-x-nasa-jon-krasinski|url-status=live}}</ref> In February 2021, Cyrus performed at the first TikTok Tailgate show in [[Tampa, Florida|Tampa]], for 7,500 [[COVID-19 vaccine|vaccinated]] healthcare workers. It served as a pre-show before [[Super Bowl LV]]. It aired on [[TikTok]] and [[CBS]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Sahadeo|first=Andy|date=January 25, 2021|title=What is the TikTok Tailgate? Everything you need to know|url=https://www.foxnews.com/entertainment/tiktok-tailgate-need-to-know|access-date=January 30, 2021|website=Fox News|archive-date=June 23, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230623171458/https://www.foxnews.com/entertainment/tiktok-tailgate-need-to-know|url-status=live}}</ref> The performance was featured in the music video for "[[Angels like You]]".<ref>{{cite web|last=Tuccillo|first=Andrea|date=March 9, 2021|title=Miley Cyrus releases 'Angels Like You' video with message encouraging COVID-19 vaccination|url=https://abcnews.go.com/GMA/Culture/miley-cyrus-releases-angels-video-message-encouraging-covid/story?id=76340051|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210316074558/https://abcnews.go.com/GMA/Culture/miley-cyrus-releases-angels-video-message-encouraging-covid/story?id=76340051|archive-date=March 16, 2021|access-date=April 2, 2021|publisher=[[ABC News (United States)|ABC News]]}}</ref> In March 2021, Cyrus departed RCA and signed with [[Columbia Records]], a sister label of RCA under the [[Sony Music Entertainment|Sony Music]] umbrella.<ref>{{Cite magazine|date=March 4, 2021|title=Miley Cyrus Signs With Columbia Records: Exclusive|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/9534313/miley-cyrus-columbia-records-deal/|access-date=March 4, 2021|magazine=Billboard|archive-date=August 14, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210814053846/https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/9534313/miley-cyrus-columbia-records-deal/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Aswad|first=Jem|date=March 4, 2021|title=Miley Cyrus Signs With Columbia Records|url=https://variety.com/2021/music/news/miley-cyrus-columbia-records-1234921757/|access-date=March 4, 2021|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|archive-date=March 4, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210304154310/https://variety.com/2021/music/news/miley-cyrus-columbia-records-1234921757/|url-status=live}}</ref> That same month Cyrus embraced her days as Hannah Montana and wrote an open letter to the character on social media for the show's 15th anniversary, despite all statements that her days as Montana gave Cyrus an [[identity crisis]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Miley Cyrus's Letter to Hannah Montana Is Making Us Emotional|url=https://www.teenvogue.com/story/miley-cyrus-letter-to-hannah-montana-15th-anniversary|access-date=June 23, 2021|website=Teen Vogue|date=March 25, 2021|archive-date=June 24, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210624202849/https://www.teenvogue.com/story/miley-cyrus-letter-to-hannah-montana-15th-anniversary|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Weaver|first=Hilary|date=March 6, 2021|title=Miley Cyrus Says That 'Hannah Montana' Gave Her an 'Identity Crisis'|url=https://www.elle.com/culture/celebrities/a35751744/miley-cyrus-hannah-montana-identity-crisis/|access-date=June 23, 2021|website=Elle|archive-date=June 24, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210624205354/https://www.elle.com/culture/celebrities/a35751744/miley-cyrus-hannah-montana-identity-crisis/|url-status=live}}</ref> Rumors about a possible revival of the show have been around ever since.<ref>{{cite web|last=Presley|first=James Kenneth|date=March 25, 2021|title='Hannah Montana' cast reunion: Will there be a revival of the Disney classic?|url=https://filmdaily.co/news/hannah-montana-reunion/|access-date=June 23, 2021|website=Film Daily|archive-date=June 24, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210624204434/https://filmdaily.co/news/hannah-montana-reunion/|url-status=live}}</ref> On April 23, 2021, [[The Kid Laroi]] released a remix of his single "[[Without You (The Kid Laroi song)|Without You]]" featuring Cyrus, her first release under Columbia Records.<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Kaufman|first=Gil|date=April 23, 2021|title=Miley Cyrus Finally Reveals When Her Kid Laroi Remix Will Drop|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/9561781/miley-cyrus-release-date-kid-laroi-remix/|magazine=Billboard|access-date=April 25, 2021|archive-date=April 25, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210425013900/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/9561781/miley-cyrus-release-date-kid-laroi-remix/|url-status=live}}</ref> On April 3, 2021, Cyrus performed at the [[NCAA Final Four Tournament|NCAA March Madness Final Four]] in Indianapolis with the frontline health care workers in the audience.<ref>{{cite web|last=Jaipuriar|first=Rashika|title=Miley Cyrus coming to Indianapolis, NCAA Final Four to perform tribute to frontline workers|url=https://www.indystar.com/story/sports/basketball/2021/03/26/miley-cyrus-perform-march-madness-final-four/7011880002/|access-date=April 3, 2021|website=The Indianapolis Star|archive-date=April 13, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210413093951/https://www.indystar.com/story/sports/basketball/2021/03/26/miley-cyrus-perform-march-madness-final-four/7011880002/|url-status=live}}</ref> 

In May 2021, Cyrus signed an overall deal with [[NBCUniversal]], including a first-look deal with her studio Hopetown Entertainment, as part of which she will develop projects for the company's outlets and star in three specials; with the first project off the deal being the ''Stand By You'' [[Pride parade|Pride]] concert special, which was released the following month on [[Peacock (streaming service)|Peacock]].<ref>{{Cite news|date=June 9, 2021|title=At Miley Cyrus' Intimate Pride Concert in Nashville, Love and Rainbows Were in the Air|url=https://consequence.net/2021/06/miley-cyrus-nashville-concert-recap-pride/|access-date=June 23, 2021|website=Consequence|archive-date=February 24, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230224100801/https://consequence.net/2021/06/miley-cyrus-nashville-concert-recap-pride/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Evans|first1=Greg|date=May 14, 2021|title=Miley Cyrus Teams With NBCUniversal For Overall Deal; Pride Concert Special Named First Project|url=https://deadline.com/2021/05/miley-cyrus-nbcuniversal-overall-deal-pride-concert-special-first-project-1234756661/|access-date=May 15, 2021|website=Deadline|archive-date=February 24, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230224100803/https://deadline.com/2021/05/miley-cyrus-nbcuniversal-overall-deal-pride-concert-special-first-project-1234756661/|url-status=live}}</ref> In June, Cyrus released a studio cover version of [[Metallica]]'s "[[Nothing Else Matters]]", which was included in ''[[The Metallica Blacklist]]'', a [[tribute album]] to the band's [[Metallica (album)|homonymous record]], featuring renditions recorded by various artists and released in conjunction to the original album's 30th anniversary.<ref>{{cite web|title=Metallica Covers Album to Feature Phoebe Bridgers, Moses Sumney, St. Vincent, Mac DeMarco, and More|url=https://pitchfork.com/news/metallica-covers-album-to-feature-phoebe-bridgers-moses-sumney-st-vincent-mac-demarco-and-more/|access-date=June 23, 2021|website=Pitchfork|date=June 22, 2021|archive-date=June 29, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210629162228/https://pitchfork.com/news/metallica-covers-album-to-feature-phoebe-bridgers-moses-sumney-st-vincent-mac-demarco-and-more/|url-status=live}}</ref> The track also features [[Elton John]] on the piano, [[Yo-Yo Ma]] and [[Red Hot Chili Peppers]]' [[Chad Smith]].<ref name="capitalfm.com">{{cite web|title=WATCH: Miley Cyrus teases Elton John, Red Hot Chili Peppers, Metallica collaboration|url=https://www.capitalfm.com/news/miley-cyrus-collaboration-elton-john-chad-smith-metallica/|access-date=June 23, 2021|website=Capital|archive-date=June 17, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210617212532/https://www.capitalfm.com/news/miley-cyrus-collaboration-elton-john-chad-smith-metallica/|url-status=live}}</ref> The singer initially teased a Metallica cover album in October 2020 and had already performed the track live during her set at [[Glastonbury Festival 2019|Glastonbury]].<ref>{{cite web|date=October 19, 2020|title=Rick Owens and Miley Cyrus on Rock Stars, Recklessness, and Life on the Road|url=https://www.interviewmagazine.com/fashion/rick-owens-and-miley-cyrus-discuss-ufos-rock-stars-tour-bus-moncler|access-date=October 22, 2020|website=[[Interview (magazine)|Interview]]|archive-date=October 22, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201022021726/https://www.interviewmagazine.com/fashion/rick-owens-and-miley-cyrus-discuss-ufos-rock-stars-tour-bus-moncler|url-status=live}}</ref>

To promote ''Plastic Hearts'', Cyrus teased a concert tour around the album's release.<ref name="capitalfm.com"/> The tour was postponed due to the pandemic but Cyrus was able to headline several music festivals in the country during summer 2021, including [[Austin City Limits Music Festival|Austin City Limits]], [[Lollapalooza]], and [[Music Midtown]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Wang|first=Jessica|date=June 16, 2021|title=Miley Cyrus Reveals Her Lower Back Tattoo, Along With New Tour Dates, With New String Bikini Pic|url=https://hollywoodlife.com/2021/06/16/miley-cyrus-back-tattoo-bikini-tour-dates-photo/|access-date=June 23, 2021|website=Hollywood Life|archive-date=June 24, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210624203204/https://hollywoodlife.com/2021/06/16/miley-cyrus-back-tattoo-bikini-tour-dates-photo/|url-status=live}}</ref> Later that year, she revealed she would tour South America [[Gypsy Heart Tour|for the first time in seven years]] in early 2022.<ref>{{cite news|date=October 28, 2021|title=Lollapalooza bringing Foo Fighters, The Strokes, Miley Cyrus & more to South America in 2022|url=https://consequence.net/2021/10/lollapalooza-argentina-and-brasil-2022-lineups/|access-date=October 30, 2021|website=Consequence|archive-date=February 24, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230224100804/https://consequence.net/2021/10/lollapalooza-argentina-and-brasil-2022-lineups/|url-status=live}}</ref> The second special off her deal with NBCUniversal was ''[[Miley's New Year's Eve Party]]'', which Cyrus co-hosted from Miami with ''[[Saturday Night Live]]'' cast member [[Pete Davidson]] and also co-executive produced under her production company Hopetown Entertainment,<ref>{{cite web|last=Schneider|first=Michael|date=November 29, 2021|title=Miley Cyrus and Pete Davidson to Host New Year's Eve Special for NBC, From Exec Producer Lorne Michaels|url=https://variety.com/2021/tv/news/miley-cyrus-pete-davidson-nbc-new-years-eve-1235121419/|access-date=November 30, 2021|website=Variety|archive-date=November 29, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211129234923/https://variety.com/2021/tv/news/miley-cyrus-pete-davidson-nbc-new-years-eve-1235121419/|url-status=live}}</ref> featuring performances by Cyrus, [[24kGoldn]], [[Anitta (singer)|Anitta]], [[Billie Joe Armstrong]], [[Brandi Carlile]], [[Jack Harlow]], Kitty Cash, and [[Saweetie]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Pedersen |first=Erik |date=December 20, 2021 |title=Performers Set For NBC's Miley Cyrus-Pete Davidson New Year's Eve Special – Watch The Promo |url=https://deadline.com/2021/12/miley-cyrus-new-years-eve-performers-pete-davidson-nbc-performers-set-for-nbcs-miley-cyrus-pete-davidson-nbc-1234899932/ |access-date=December 21, 2021 |website=Deadline|archive-date=December 20, 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211220235658/https://deadline.com/2021/12/miley-cyrus-new-years-eve-performers-pete-davidson-nbc-performers-set-for-nbcs-miley-cyrus-pete-davidson-nbc-1234899932/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

In February 2022, Cyrus embarked on her music festival concert tour, [[Attention Tour]], in support of ''Plastic Hearts'', which took place in [[North America|North]], [[South America|South]], and [[Central America]]. This marked her first tour to South America since her Gypsy Heart Tour in 2011. The tour concluded on March 26, 2022.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Iasimone |first=Ashley |date=March 27, 2022 |title=Miley Cyrus Tearfully Dedicates 'Angels Like You' to Taylor Hawkins at Lollapalooza Brazil |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/miley-cyrus-taylor-hawkins-angels-like-you-lollapalooza-brazil-1235049642/ |access-date=June 8, 2022 |magazine=Billboard |archive-date=May 30, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230530151602/https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/miley-cyrus-taylor-hawkins-angels-like-you-lollapalooza-brazil-1235049642/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Arena |first=Crypto com |title=Bud Light Super Bowl Music Fest: Green Day & Miley Cyrus|url=https://www.cryptoarena.com/events/detail/superbowlnusicfest-3-22 |access-date=June 8, 2022 |website=Crypto.com Arena|archive-date=May 22, 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220522170911/https://www.cryptoarena.com/events/detail/superbowlnusicfest-3-22 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Miley Cyrus recovering from COVID after Latin American tour: 'It was worth it' |url=https://www.hola.com/us/celebrities/20220404331019/miley-cyrus-covid-latin-american-tour/?viewas=amp |access-date=June 8, 2022 |website=www.hola.com | date=April 4, 2022 |archive-date=May 28, 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220528051145/https://www.hola.com/us/celebrities/20220404331019/miley-cyrus-covid-latin-american-tour/?viewas=amp |url-status=live }}</ref> On April 1, 2022, Cyrus released her third live album, ''[[Attention: Miley Live]]''.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Kreps |first=Daniel |date=March 27, 2022 |title=Miley Cyrus Announces First-Ever New Live Album 'Attention: Miley Live' |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/miley-cyrus-new-live-album-attention-1328145/ |magazine=Rolling Stone |access-date=June 10, 2022 |archive-date=May 29, 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220529042103/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/miley-cyrus-new-live-album-attention-1328145/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Most of the album was recorded during her concert as part of the Super Bowl Music Fest at the [[Crypto.com Arena]] in Los Angeles on February 12, 2022, with the set list including songs from her albums ''Plastic Hearts'', ''Miley Cyrus & Her Dead Petz'', ''Bangerz'', ''The Time of Our Lives'', ''Breakout'', and ''Meet Miley Cyrus'', along with multiple cover songs. The album also includes two unreleased tracks—"Attention" and "You". She said the album was "curated by the fans for the fans".<ref>{{cite web |last=Major |first=Michael |title=VIDEO: Miley Cyrus Releases 'Never Be Me' From 'ATTENTION: MILEY LIVE' Album |url=https://www.broadwayworld.com/bwwmusic/article/VIDEO-Miley-Cyrus-Releases-Never-Be-Me-From-ATTENTION-MILEY-LIVE-Album-20220330 |access-date=June 10, 2022 |website=Broadway World|archive-date=February 24, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230224100803/https://www.broadwayworld.com/bwwmusic/article/VIDEO-Miley-Cyrus-Releases-Never-Be-Me-From-ATTENTION-MILEY-LIVE-Album-20220330 |url-status=live }}</ref> Emily Swingle of ''[[Clash (magazine)|Clash]]'' gave acclaim to Cyrus's versatile vocals, saying her "voice is truly a force to be reckoned with, seamlessly fitting whatever genre she chooses to tackle. From the playful, [[Country rap|country-hip-hop]] banger that is '4x4', to [[Hip hop music|rap]]-heavy '[[23 (Mike Will Made It song)|23]]', to the [[blues]]y, rich cover of [[Janis Joplin]]'s '[[Maybe (The Chantels song)|Maybe]]', it seems like Cyrus can fit into just about any genre she gets her paws on."<ref>{{cite web |title=Miley Cyrus - ATTENTION: MILEY LIVE |url=https://www.clashmusic.com/reviews/miley-cyrus-attention-miley-live |access-date=June 10, 2022 |website=Clash Magazine |date=April 7, 2022 |archive-date=June 2, 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220602221549/https://www.clashmusic.com/reviews/miley-cyrus-attention-miley-live |url-status=live }}</ref> By the end of that month, Cyrus released the deluxe version of the album, which includes six additional songs including a mashup of "Mother's Daughter" and "Boys Don't Cry" featuring [[Anitta (singer)|Anitta]], that are mostly part of her time at the Lollapalooza festival in Brazil and other shows in Latin America; she commented on the addition of her single "Angels Like You" at her concert in Colombia in gratitude due to the song reaching the number one spot on iTunes in that country and because her fans sang the song all night outside the hotel where she was staying in Bogotá.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Rowley |first=Glenn |date=April 25, 2022 |title=Miley Cyrus Announces Deluxe Version of 'Attention: Miley Live' |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/pop/miley-cyrus-attention-live-deluxe-album-1235063242/ |access-date=June 10, 2022 |magazine=Billboard |archive-date=April 25, 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220425210103/https://www.billboard.com/music/pop/miley-cyrus-attention-live-deluxe-album-1235063242/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite tweet|number=1519744596267483139|user=MileyCyrus|title=On 4/29 I'm adding MORE songs to the #ATTENTION live album! Including Angels Like You which was added into the set the night before inspired by the fans below my hotel room in Bogota singing it ALL NIGHT LONG! Woke up to Angels being #1 in Colombia!|first=Miley|last=Cyrus}}</ref> The following month, NBC announced that ''Miley's New Year's Eve Party'' had been renewed for a second iteration set to be aired on New Year's Eve 2022–23.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Del Rosario |first1=Alexandra |date=May 16, 2022 |title=Miley Cyrus Returning To Host NBC's New Year's Eve Special – Upfronts |url=https://deadline.com/2022/05/miley-cyrus-host-nbc-2023-new-years-eve-special-upfronts-1235024271/ |access-date=July 17, 2022 |website=[[Deadline Hollywood|Deadline]] |archive-date=May 22, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230522151213/https://deadline.com/2022/05/miley-cyrus-host-nbc-2023-new-years-eve-special-upfronts-1235024271/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last1=Verhoeven |first1=Beatrice |date=June 25, 2022 |title=Miley Cyrus on Challenges of 'Miley's New Year's Eve Party' and Why Pete Davidson Was the Best Co-Host |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/tv/tv-features/miley-cyrus-new-years-eve-party-pete-davidson-1235168144/ |access-date=November 3, 2022 |website=The Hollywood Reporter |archive-date=February 6, 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240206171301/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/tv/tv-features/miley-cyrus-new-years-eve-party-pete-davidson-1235168144/ |url-status=live }}</ref> In August 2022, it was announced that Cyrus was set to star in a [[Christmas film|Christmas]] [[television film]] ''Dolly Parton's Mountain Magic Christmas'', produced by [[Dolly Parton]] for [[NBC]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Porter |first1=Rick |date=August 29, 2022 |title=Dolly Parton NBC Holiday Movie Sets Cast |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/tv/tv-news/dolly-parton-miley-cyrus-jimmy-fallon-nbc-holiday-movie-1235207972/ |access-date=September 4, 2022 |website=[[Deadline Hollywood|Deadline]] |archive-date=March 14, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230314234923/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/tv/tv-news/dolly-parton-miley-cyrus-jimmy-fallon-nbc-holiday-movie-1235207972/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

In December 2022, [[Morrissey]] announced that Cyrus wanted her backing vocals taken off from his upcoming record that was recorded two years earlier, but not yet released.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Willman |first=Chris |date=December 25, 2022 |title=Morrissey Says Miley Cyrus Wants Off His Next Album, and He's Split With Label and Management, Too |url=https://variety.com/2022/music/news/morrissey-miley-cyrus-wants-off-album-split-label-capitol-1235472792/ |access-date=December 26, 2022 |website=Variety |archive-date=February 9, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230209070821/https://variety.com/2022/music/news/morrissey-miley-cyrus-wants-off-album-split-label-capitol-1235472792/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Kreps |first=Daniel |date=December 24, 2022 |title=Morrissey Album Likely Delayed Again as Miley Cyrus Wants Guest Spot Taken Off |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/morrissey-album-delayed-miley-cyrus-capitol-records-split-1234652851/ |access-date=December 26, 2022 |magazine=Rolling Stone |archive-date=December 26, 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221226015515/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/morrissey-album-delayed-miley-cyrus-capitol-records-split-1234652851/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

===2023–present: ''Endless Summer Vacation''===
In late 2022, Cyrus and her longtime collaborator [[Mike Will Made It]] teased new music to be released in 2023, on the latter's social media.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Garner |first=Glenn |date=November 21, 2022 |title=Miley Cyrus Is Making New Music with 'Bangerz' Producer Mike WiLL Made-It to Debut in 2023 |url=https://people.com/music/miley-cyrus-is-making-new-music-with-bangerz-producer-mike-will-made-it-to-debut-in-2023/ |access-date=January 2, 2023 |magazine=[[People (magazine)|People]] |publisher=[[Dotdash Meredith]] |archive-date=January 1, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230101072358/https://people.com/music/miley-cyrus-is-making-new-music-with-bangerz-producer-mike-will-made-it-to-debut-in-2023/ |url-status=live}}</ref> Cyrus continued to tease a new musical era through a cryptic promotional campaign—which included posters in cities around the world, countdowns on her website, and video previews—with the caption, "New Year, New Miley".<ref>
