Miley Cyrus has been described mainly as a [[Pop music|pop]] singer<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.allmusic.com/artist/miley-cyrus-mn0000551762|title=Miley Cyrus|work=[[AllMusic]]|access-date=March 12, 2023|archive-date=March 12, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230312233814/https://www.allmusic.com/artist/miley-cyrus-mn0000551762|url-status=live}}</ref> who has also developed a [[Rock music|rock]] style.<ref name="statenews genres">{{cite web|first=Liz|last=Nass|url=https://statenews.com/article/2022/01/miley-cyrus-tops-the-itunes-charts?ct=content_open&cv=cbox_latest|title=Miley Cyrus trailblazes on the iTunes charts|magazine=State News|date=January 14, 2022|access-date=March 21, 2022|archive-date=March 18, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220318195232/https://statenews.com/article/2022/01/miley-cyrus-tops-the-itunes-charts?ct=content_open&cv=cbox_latest|url-status=live}}</ref> Her music has also spanned many other different genres including [[teen pop]],<ref name="statenews genres"/> [[Country music|country]],<ref name="nytimes genres">{{cite news|first=Lindsay|last=Zoladz|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/12/01/arts/music/miley-cyrus-plastic-hearts-review.html|title=Miley Cyrus Finally Embraces Her Rock 'n' Roll Heart|magazine=[[The New York Times]]|date=December 1, 2020|access-date=March 21, 2022|archive-date=December 21, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221221081401/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/12/01/arts/music/miley-cyrus-plastic-hearts-review.html|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Hip hop music|hip hop]],<ref name="nytimes genres"/> and [[Psychedelic music|psychedelic]].<ref name="nytimes genres"/> Cyrus has cited [[Elvis Presley]] as her biggest inspiration.<ref>{{Cite video |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CV1YDqQn1WQ  |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/varchive/youtube/20211213/CV1YDqQn1WQ |archive-date=December 13, 2021 |url-status=live|title=Miley Cyrus Talks Malibu, Sobriety & Liam Hemsworth |publisher=Zach Sang}}{{cbignore}}</ref> She has also cited artists such as [[Madonna]], [[Lana Del Rey]], [[Dolly Parton]], [[Timbaland]], [[Whitney Houston]], [[Christina Aguilera]], [[Joan Jett]], [[Lil Kim]], [[Shania Twain]], [[Hanson (band)|Hanson]], [[OneRepublic]], and [[Britney Spears]] as influences.<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Diehl|first=Matt|title=Miley Cyrus 2.0: The Billboard Cover Story|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/1567023/miley-cyrus-20-the-billboard-cover-story|magazine=Billboard|access-date=October 3, 2013|date=June 14, 2013|archive-date=September 26, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130926015739/http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/1567023/miley-cyrus-20-the-billboard-cover-story?|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|last=Ganz|first=Caryn|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/albumreviews/ultraviolence-20140620|title=Lana Del Rey: Ultraviolence|magazine=[[Rolling Stone]]|date=June 20, 2014|access-date=June 20, 2014|archive-date=June 23, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140623133054/http://www.rollingstone.com/music/albumreviews/ultraviolence-20140620|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="Cyrus">{{Cite news|url=http://www.entertainmentwise.com/news/43649/miley-cyrus-aims-to-be-the-next-madonna |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080707030240/http://www.entertainmentwise.com/news/43649/miley-cyrus-aims-to-be-the-next-madonna |url-status=dead |archive-date=July 7, 2008 |title=Miley Cyrus Wants To Be The Next Madonna |date=July 4, 2008 |access-date=April 18, 2013 |last=Mander |first=Harjeet |work=Entertainment Wise }}</ref><ref name="Cyrus2">{{Cite news|url=http://www.adnmundo.com/contenidos/adncool/miley_cyrus_quiere_ser_nueva_madonna_co04078.html|title=Miley Cyrus: Quiere ser la nueva Madonna|date=July 8, 2008|access-date=April 18, 2013|publisher=ADNMundo.com|language=es|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://archive.today/20130628092420/http://www.adnmundo.com/contenidos/adncool/miley_cyrus_quiere_ser_nueva_madonna_co04078.html|archive-date=June 28, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=UzitDwAAQBAJ&dq=miley+cyrus+influenced+by+whitney+houston&pg=PT119|title=She Can't Stop - Miley Cyrus: The Biography|isbn=978-1-78418-197-0|last1=Oliver|first1=Sarah|date=September 4, 2014|publisher=Kings Road|access-date=April 15, 2022|archive-date=February 6, 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240206171300/https://books.google.com/books?id=UzitDwAAQBAJ&dq=miley+cyrus+influenced+by+whitney+houston&pg=PT119#v=onepage&q=miley%20cyrus%20influenced%20by%20whitney%20houston&f=false|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="Miley Cyrus2">{{Cite news|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/showbiz/news/a107641/miley-cyrus-hopes-to-emulate-madonna.html|title=Miley Cyrus hopes to emulate Madonna|date=July 5, 2008|access-date=April 18, 2013|work=Digital Spy|last=Kilkelly|first=Daniel|archive-date=February 25, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150225160006/http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/showbiz/news/a107641/miley-cyrus-hopes-to-emulate-madonna.html|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317232413/https://www.oanow.com/corner/miley-cyrus-lists-her-top-female-influences/article_793f619f-1cf1-59e6-9c50-1eda36c332ab.html|archive-date=March 17, 2020|url-status=dead|url=http://www.thecornernews.com/blogs/news_to_me/article_21a47238-e7c8-11e2-9eb9-001a4bcf6878.html|title=Miley Cyrus lists her top 5 female influences|website=Thecornernews.com|access-date=July 31, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Artists Following Miley Cyrus|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140313033803/http://www.mtv.com/artists/miley-cyrus/related-artists/?filter=influencedBy|archive-date=March 13, 2014|url-status=dead|url=http://www.mtv.com/artists/miley-cyrus/related-artists/?filter=influencedBy |website= [[MTV]]|access-date=July 8, 2016}}</ref> Since the beginning of her music career, Cyrus has been described as being predominantly a pop artist.<ref name="debutalbum">{{cite web|url=http://www.commonsensemedia.org/music-reviews/hannah-montana-soundtrack |title=Hannah Montana Soundtrack – Music Review |publisher=Common Sense Media|access-date=April 29, 2013|date=June 29, 2007 }}</ref> Her ''Hannah Montana 2: Meet Miley Cyrus'' debut studio effort was characterized as sounding similar to her releases as "Hannah Montana" featuring a [[pop-rock]] and [[bubblegum pop]] sound.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://cinemablend.com/music/CD-Review-Hannah-Montana-2-Meet-Miley-Cyrus-4945.html |title=CD Review: Hannah Montana 2 – Meet Miley Cyrus |publisher=Cinema Blend |date=June 27, 2007 |access-date=April 29, 2013 |archive-date=July 2, 2007 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070702030255/https://cinemablend.com/music/CD-Review-Hannah-Montana-2-Meet-Miley-Cyrus-4945.html |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.commonsensemedia.org/music-reviews/hannah-montana-2-meet-miley-cyrus |title=Hannah Montana 2: Meet Miley Cyrus – Music Review |publisher=Common Sense Media|access-date=April 29, 2013|date=June 29, 2007 }}</ref> Cyrus hoped that the release of ''Breakout'' (2008) would help distance her from this sound; the record featured Cyrus experimenting with various genres.<ref>{{cite news|last=Wood |first=Mikael |url=https://latimes.com/entertainment/news/music/la-et-miley-cyrus-breakout-review22-jul200822,0,7262817.story |title=Miley Cyrus' 'Breakout': A long way from Montana |website=Los Angeles Times|date=July 21, 2008 |access-date=April 29, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Phares |first=Heather |url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/breakout-mw0000790148|title=Breakout – Miley Cyrus : Songs, Reviews, Credits, Awards |website=AllMusic |date=July 22, 2008 |access-date=April 29, 2013}}</ref> Cyrus co-wrote eight songs for the album and was quoted as saying: "I just hope this record showcases that, more than anything, I'm a [song]writer."<ref name="Serjeant, Jill"/> The songs on her early releases feature lyrics on the topics of love and relationships.<ref name=debutalbum />

Cyrus possesses a [[mezzo-soprano]] [[Voice type|vocal range]],<ref>{{cite web|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151006215548/http://www.vh1.com/news/54763/snl-40-miley-cyrus-paul-simon-cover/|archive-date=October 6, 2015|url-status=live|url=https://www.vh1.com/news/01vbvr/snl-40-miley-cyrus-paul-simon-cover|title=Miley Cyrus Reminds Us She Can Seriously Sing With Paul Simon Cover On 'SNL 40'|publisher=vh1.com|access-date=February 15, 2015}}</ref> although her vocals were once described as [[alto]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/2556726/miley-cyrus-hotel-transylvania/|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160331144155/http://www.mtv.com/news/2556726/miley-cyrus-hotel-transylvania/|url-status=dead|archive-date=March 31, 2016|title=Miley Cyrus Joins The Ranks Of The Be-Fanged In 'Hotel Transylvania'|website=Mtv.com|access-date=July 31, 2016}}</ref> with a "Nashville [[Guttural vocals|twang]]" in both her spoken and singing voice. Her voice has a distinctive raspy sound to it, similar in vein to that of [[Pink (singer)|Pink]] and [[Amy Winehouse]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Coetzee|first=Nikita|url=https://www.news24.com/channel/music/news/watch-miley-cyrus-incredible-performance-with-her-sister-for-mtv-unplugged-will-give-you-chills-20201019|title=Miley Cyrus' incredible performance with her sister for MTV Unplugged will give you chills|work=[[News24 (website)|News24]]|date=October 19, 2020|access-date=November 26, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://georgetownvoice.com/2020/11/20/miley-cyrus-tiktok-covers/|title=Miley Cyrus proves she has a voice for rock with viral TikTok covers|work=[[The Georgetown Voice]]|date=November 20, 2020|access-date=November 26, 2020}}</ref><ref name="EW2" /> On "Party in the U.S.A." (2009), her vocals feature [[Belt (music)|belter]] [[refrain]]s,<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/blogs/chartblog/2009/10/miley_cyrus_party_in_the_usa.shtml|title=Miley Cyrus – Party in the U.S.A.|first=Vicki|last=Lutas|work=BBC News|access-date=August 28, 2010}}</ref> while those on the song "Obsessed" (2009) are described as "husky".<ref name="digitalspy">{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.com/music/review/a187431/miley-cyrus-the-time-of-our-lives.html|title=Miley Cyrus: 'The Time Of Our Lives'|first=Nick|last=Levine|date=November 9, 2009|publisher=[[Digital Spy]]. [[Hearst Corporation]]|access-date=October 8, 2010}}</ref> Releases such as "The Climb" (2009) and "These Four Walls" (2008) feature elements of [[country music]] and showcase Cyrus's "twangy vocals".<ref>{{cite web|work=The Gazette  |url=http://www.canada.com/montrealgazette/news/arts/story.html?id=488ae70a-b05d-4bce-aa26-0f3c14f2510e |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080729010848/http://www.canada.com/montrealgazette/news/arts/story.html?id=488ae70a-b05d-4bce-aa26-0f3c14f2510e |url-status=dead |archive-date=July 29, 2008 |title=CD review: Breakout, Miley Cyrus |publisher=Canada |date=July 23, 2008 |access-date=April 29, 2013 }}</ref> Cyrus experimented with an [[electropop]] sound on "[[Fly on the Wall (song)|Fly on the Wall]]" (2008), a genre that she would explore further with the release of ''Can't Be Tamed'' (2010), her third studio album.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/958051/miley-cyrus-summer-album-preview-2010 |title=Miley Cyrus: Summer Album Preview 2010|magazine=Billboard|date=May 26, 2010|access-date=April 29, 2013}}</ref> It was initially intended to feature [[Rock music|rock]] elements prior to its completion,<ref name="billboardcoverstory3">{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/957988/miley-cyrus-the-billboard-cover-story?page=0%2C2|title=Miley Cyrus: The Billboard Cover Story|pages=3–4|first=Anne | last=Donahue |magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=May 28, 2010|access-date=February 9, 2014}}</ref> and Cyrus claimed after its release that it could be her final pop album.<ref name="Hiatus">{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/1627962/miley-cyrus-covers-poisons-every-rose-has-its-thorn/|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140813003140/http://www.mtv.com/news/1627962/miley-cyrus-covers-poisons-every-rose-has-its-thorn/|url-status=dead|archive-date=August 13, 2014|title=Miley Cyrus Covers Poison's 'Every Rose Has Its Thorn'|first=James | last=Dinh |publisher=[[MTV News]]. [[Viacom (2005–present)|Viacom]]|date=December 9, 2009|access-date=February 9, 2014}}</ref> The album's songs speak of Cyrus's desire to achieve freedom in both her personal and professional life.<ref name="Hiatus" /> She began working on ''Bangerz'' (2013) during a musical hiatus, and described the record as having a "dirty south feel" prior to its release.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://fistintheair.com/2012/11/10/miley-cyrus-to-make-dirty-south-hip-hop-album/ |title=Miley Cyrus to make "Dirty South Hip Hop Album" |publisher=Fist in the Air |date=November 10, 2012 |access-date=April 29, 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130404023936/http://fistintheair.com/2012/11/10/miley-cyrus-to-make-dirty-south-hip-hop-album/ |archive-date=April 4, 2013 |url-status=dead }}</ref> Critics noted the use of [[Hip hop music|hip hop]] and [[synthpop]] on the album.<ref name="BillboardReview">{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/review/5740707/miley-cyrus-bangerz-track-by-track-review|title=Miley Cyrus, 'Bangerz': Track-By-Track Review|last=Lipshutz|first=Jason|magazine=Billboard|date=October 1, 2013|access-date=October 1, 2013}}</ref> The album's songs are placed in chronological order telling the story of her failed relationship with Liam Hemsworth.<ref>{{cite AV media|people=[[Ellen DeGeneres]], Miley Cyrus|year=2013|title=Miley Discusses Her Relationship with Liam Hemsworth|medium=[[YouTube]]|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mH3HQg5UoC0 |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/varchive/youtube/20211213/mH3HQg5UoC0 |archive-date=December 13, 2021 |url-status=live|access-date=October 12, 2013|time=1:06 minutes|publisher=[[The Ellen DeGeneres Show]]|location=Burbank, California}}{{cbignore}}</ref> Cyrus described ''Miley Cyrus & Her Dead Petz'' (2015) as "a little psychedelic, but still in that [[Pop music|pop]] world".<ref name="Retwired"/> For her rock-influenced album, ''Plastic Hearts'', Cyrus cited Britney Spears and [[Metallica]] as major influences.<ref>{{cite web |title=Miley Cyrus says new album is inspired by Britney Spears and Metallica|publisher=UK Official Charts |date=September 10, 2020 |access-date=December 7, 2020|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/miley-cyrus-says-new-album-is-inspired-by-britney-spears-and-metallica__30961/}}</ref> Inspired by pop and dance-pop, ''Endless Summer Vacation'' (2023) "feels like a recap of her career's 15-plus years, with Cyrus breezing through genres with the ease of a well-seasoned tourist."<ref name="rollingstonereview2">{{Cite magazine |last=Johnston |first=Maura |authorlink=Maura Johnston |date=March 11, 2023 |title=Miley Cyrus Sums Up Everything She's Great At On 'Endless Summer Vacation' |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-album-reviews/miley-cyrus-sendless-summer-vacation-1234692905/ |access-date=March 11, 2023 |magazine=[[Rolling Stone]] |archive-date=March 11, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230311173548/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-album-reviews/miley-cyrus-sendless-summer-vacation-1234692905/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Cyrus related its overall concept to her affection for Los Angeles.

===Stage performances===
{{update|section|date=July 2023}}
Cyrus has become known for her controversial musical performances, including on her [[Bangerz Tour]] (2014) and [[Milky Milky Milk Tour]] (2015).<ref name="shock">{{cite web|url=http://www.foxnews.com/entertainment/2015/11/22/miley-cyrus-dons-yet-another-risque-outfit/|title=Miley Cyrus dons yet another risque outfit|website=[[Fox News]]|access-date=February 20, 2020}}</ref> Her performance of "Party in the U.S.A." at the [[2009 Teen Choice Awards]] sparked a "national uproar" because of her outfit and perceived pole dancing.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/videos/news/426175/miley-cyrus-performs-party-in-the-usa.jhtml#id=1617967|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090814114057/http://www.mtv.com/videos/news/426175/miley-cyrus-performs-party-in-the-usa.jhtml#id=1617967|url-status=dead|archive-date=August 14, 2009|title=Miley Cyrus Performs 'Party in the U.S.A.'|work=MTV News. Viacom|date=August 10, 2009|access-date=August 10, 2009}}</ref><ref name=newsday>{{cite web|last=Kahn | first=Robert |url=http://www.newsday.com/entertainment/celebrities/miley-cyrus-pole-dancing-performance-sparks-criticism-1.1360720|title=Miley Cyrus' pole-dancing performance sparks criticism|work=[[Newsday]]|date=August 10, 2009|access-date=June 4, 2010}}</ref> She faced similar controversy over her performance of "Can't Be Tamed" (2010) on ''[[Britain's Got Talent]]'', where the singer pretended to kiss one of her female backup dancers onstage;<ref name=bgt>{{cite web|url=https://www.accessonline.com/articles/miley-cyrus-on-her-racy-britains-got-talent-performance-get-over-it-86391|title=Miley Cyrus on Her Racy 'Britain's Got Talent' Performance: 'Get Over It!'|date=June 5, 2010|website=Access Online|access-date=October 2, 2019}}</ref> she defended the performance, arguing that she did nothing wrong.<ref name=bgt /> 

Cyrus became the subject of media and public scrutiny following her performance of "We Can't Stop" (2013) and "[[Blurred Lines]]" (2013) with Robin Thicke at the 2013 MTV Video Music Awards. Clad in a flesh-colored latex two-piece, she touched Thicke's [[crotch]] area with a giant foam finger and [[Twerking|twerked]] against his crotch.<ref>{{cite news|last=Wyatt | first=Daisy |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/news/the-tongue-the-twerking-the-teddy-outfit-should-someone-have-stopped-miley-cyrus-vma-performance-8785494.html |title=The tongue, the twerking, the teddy outfit: Should someone have stopped Miley Cyrus' VMA performance? |work=[[The Independent]]|date=August 28, 2013 |access-date=September 10, 2013 |location=London|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170305160652/http://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/news/the-tongue-the-twerking-the-teddy-outfit-should-someone-have-stopped-miley-cyrus-vma-performance-8785494.html|archive-date=March 5, 2017}}</ref> The performance resulted in a media frenzy; one reviewer likened the performance to a "bad acid trip",<ref name="Hollywood Reporter"/> while another described it as a "trainwreck in the classic sense of the word as the audience reaction seemed to be a mix of confusion, dismay and horror in a cocktail of embarrassment".<ref>{{cite news|title=The Most Awkward Hip-Hop Moments at MTV's 2013 Video Music Awards|last=Steiner | first=B. J. |url=http://www.xxlmag.com/news/2013/08/the-most-awkward-hip-hop-moments-at-mtvs-2013-video-music-awards/|newspaper=XXL Magazine|date=August 26, 2013|access-date=August 26, 2013}}</ref> Cyrus entered the stage of her Bangerz Tour by sliding down a slide in the shape of a tongue, and draw media attention during the tour for her unique outfits and racy performances.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/danielpapalia/2014/08/21/miley-cyrus-banned-from-performing-in-dominican-republic-ssas/|title=Miley Cyrus Banned From Performing in Dominican Republic|last=Papalia | first=Daniel |date=August 21, 2014|work=[[Forbes]]|access-date=August 22, 2014}}</ref>

==Public image==
[[File:Miley Cyrus 38th People's Choice Awards (cropped).jpg|thumb|upright|Cyrus at the [[38th People's Choice Awards|2012 People's Choice Awards]]]]

In the early years of her career, Cyrus had a generally wholesome image as a teen idol.<ref name=teenidol>{{cite news|last=Abramowitz | first=Rachel |url=https://www.latimes.com/archives/la-xpm-2008-may-28-et-brief28-story.html|title=All lenses are on Miley|newspaper=Los Angeles Times|date=May 28, 2008|access-date=June 4, 2010|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120201123251/https://articles.latimes.com/2008/may/28/entertainment/et-brief28|archive-date=February 1, 2012|url-status=live}}</ref> Her fame increased dramatically in the wake of the ''Vanity Fair'' photo scandal in 2008, and it was reported that photographs of Cyrus could be sold to photo agencies for up to $2,000 per photo.<ref name=teenidol /> In subsequent years, her image continued to shift dramatically from her teen idol status.<ref name=teenidol /> In 2008, [[Donny Osmond]] wrote of Cyrus's imminent transition to adulthood: "Miley will have to face adulthood... As she does, she'll want to change her image, and that change will be met with adversity."<ref>{{cite magazine|author-link=Donny Osmond|last=Osmond|first=Donny|url=http://content.time.com/time/specials/2007/article/0,28804,1733748_1733752_1734628,00.html#ixzz0pT6GawvW|title=Miley Cyrus – The 2008 TIME 100|magazine=[[Time (magazine)|Time]]|date=April 30, 2009|access-date=June 4, 2010}}</ref> The release of her 2010 album ''Can't Be Tamed'' saw Cyrus officially attempting to distance herself from her teenage persona by releasing controversial music videos for her songs "Can't Be Tamed" and "Who Owns My Heart".<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/viral-videos/954643/miley-cyrus-hits-the-club-in-who-owns-my-heart-clip|title=Miley Cyrus Hits the Club in 'Who Owns My Heart' Clip|first=Megan|last=Vick|date=October 8, 2010|magazine=Billboard|access-date=October 15, 2010}}</ref><ref name="mtvptc">{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1649660/20101009/cyrus__miley.jhtml|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101011121614/http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1649660/20101009/cyrus__miley.jhtml|url-status=dead|archive-date=October 11, 2010|title=Miley Cyrus 'Who Owns My Heart' Video Blasted By Parents Television Council|first=Mawuse|last=Ziegbe|date=October 9, 2010|work=MTV News|publisher=Viacom|access-date=October 15, 2010}}</ref> Her behavior throughout 2013 and 2014 sparked a substantial amount of controversy, although her godmother Dolly Parton said "...the girl can write. The girl can sing. The girl is smart. And she doesn't have to be so drastic. But I will respect her choices. I did it my way, so why can't she do it her way?"<ref>{{cite magazine|author-link=Dolly Parton|last=Parton|first=Dolly|url=http://time.com/70803/miley-cyrus-2014-time-100/|title=Miley Cyrus|magazine=[[Time (magazine)|Time]]|date=April 23, 2014|access-date=May 2, 2014}}</ref> Liel Leibovitz at ''[[Tablet (magazine)|Tablet]]'' noted in 2013: "Talking to the website ''Hunger'', the singer argued that those adults who deem her gyrations too sultry and her music too saccharine were simply too ancient—and Jewish—to get it. 'With magazines, with movies, it's always weird when things are targeted for young people yet they're driven by people that are like 40 years too old', Cyrus opined. And one group stands out in [her] mind as deserving of most of the blame: 'It can't be like this 70-year-old Jewish man that doesn’t leave his desk all day, telling me what the clubs want to hear.'"<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Leibovitz|first=Liel|url=https://www.tabletmag.com/sections/news/articles/miley-cyrus-anti-semitic-slip-is-showing/|title=Miley Cyrus' Anti-Semitic Slip Is Showing|magazine=[[Tablet (magazine)|Tablet]]|date=October 10, 2013|access-date=June 25, 2024}}</ref>

Cyrus was ranked number 17 on ''[[Forbes]]''{{'}}s list of the most powerful celebrities in 2014; the magazine notes that "The last time she made our list was when she was still rolling in ''Hannah Montana'' money. Now the pop singer is all grown up and courting controversy at every turn."<ref name=Forbes14>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/miley-cyrus/|title= Celebrity 100 » #17 Miley Cyrus |access-date=July 1, 2014|work=[[Forbes]]}}</ref> In August 2014, her life was documented in a comic book titled ''Fame: Miley Cyrus''; it begins with her controversial 2013 MTV Video Music Awards performance and covers her Disney fame as well as exploring her childhood in Tennessee.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/celebritynews/11030138/Miley-Cyrus-life-turned-into-a-comic-book.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140814051353/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/celebritynews/11030138/Miley-Cyrus-life-turned-into-a-comic-book.html|url-status=dead|archive-date=August 14, 2014|title=Miley Cyrus' life turned into a comic book|date=August 13, 2014|website=[[The Daily Telegraph]]|access-date=August 13, 2014}}</ref> The comic book was written by Michael L. Frizell, drawn by Juan Luis Rincón, and is available in both print and digital formats.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/1899633/miley-cyrus-comic-book/|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140819100841/http://www.mtv.com/news/1899633/miley-cyrus-comic-book/|url-status=dead|archive-date=August 19, 2014|title=Miley Cyrus Is Getting Her Own Comic Book: Get A Sneak Peek|last=Blake | first=Emily |date=August 14, 2014|publisher=MTV|access-date=August 15, 2014}}</ref> In September 2010, Cyrus placed tenth on ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]''{{'}}s first-ever edition of its 21 Under 21 listicle;<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/956152/21-under-21-miley-cyrus|title=21 Under 21: Miley Cyrus|date=September 23, 2010|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|access-date=August 15, 2014}}</ref> she was ranked twenty-first in 2011<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.teen.com/2011/09/28/music/billboard-21-minors-under-21-list-justin-bieber-demi-lovato-photos/#1 |title=Billboard Ranks Music's Hottest 21 Under 21! Can You Guess Who's Number 1?! (Pics) |website=teen.com |publisher=Clevver Network. |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170305190544/http://www.teen.com/2011/09/28/music/billboard-21-minors-under-21-list-justin-bieber-demi-lovato-photos/ |archive-date=March 5, 2017 |access-date=March 5, 2017}}</ref> and eighteenth in 2012.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/475072/miley-cyrus-21-under-21-2012|title=Miley Cyrus: 21 Under 21 (2012)|last=Maloy | first=Sarah |date=September 17, 2012|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|access-date=August 15, 2014}}</ref> In 2013, ''[[Maxim (magazine)|Maxim]]'' listed Cyrus as number one on their annual Hot 100 list.<ref>{{cite web|title=Miley Cyrus: Number 1 On Maxim's Hot 100|url=http://www.maxim.com/girls-of-maxim/miley-cyrus-number-1-maxims-hot-100|work=Maxim|access-date=April 7, 2014|date=May 10, 2013}}</ref> Cyrus was chosen by ''[[Time (magazine)|Time]]'' magazine as one of the finalists for [[Time Person of the Year|Person of the Year]] in November 2013;<ref>{{cite web|title=Miley Cyrus Makes Time's Person of the Year List|url=http://www.etonline.com/music/141626_Miley_Cyrus_Makes_Time_s_Person_of_the_Year_List/|publisher=Entertainment Tonight|access-date=April 5, 2014|date=December 10, 2013|archive-date=April 21, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140421082350/http://www.etonline.com/music/141626_Miley_Cyrus_Makes_Time_s_Person_of_the_Year_List/|url-status=dead}}</ref> she came in third place with 16.3% of the staff vote.<ref>{{cite web|last=Franceschi |first=Lorenzo |url=http://mashable.com/2013/12/05/egyptian-general-time-person-year-poll/ |title=Egyptian General Trumps Miley to Win 'Time' Person of the Year Poll |publisher=Mashable|date=December 5, 2013 |access-date=January 12, 2014}}</ref> In March 2014, [[Skidmore College]] in [[New York (state)|New York]] began to offer a special topics sociology course entitled "The Sociology of Miley Cyrus: Race, Class, Gender and Media" which was "using Miley as a lens through which to explore sociological thinking about identity, entertainment, media and fame".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.abcnews.go.com/Entertainment/skidmore-college-offer-class-miley-cyrus/story?id=23085821/ |title=Skidmore College Will Offer a Class on Miley Cyrus |work= ABC News|date=March 27, 2014 |access-date=May 11, 2014}}</ref> In 2015, Cyrus was listed as one of the nine runners-up for ''[[The Advocate (LGBT magazine)|The Advocate]]''{{'}}s Person of the Year.<ref>{{cite web|author=<!--Not stated--> |url=http://www.advocate.com/people/2015/11/05/person-year-finalists |title=Person of the Year: The Finalists |work=The Advocate |date= November 5, 2015|access-date=November 6, 2015}}</ref> In March 2024, to commemorate the 65th anniversary of [[International Women's Day]], Cyrus was one of a number of celebrities who had their likeness turned into [[Bratz]] doll.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://exclaim.ca/music/article/sinead-o-connor-remembered-by-bratz-with-her-own-doll|title=Sinéad O'Connor Remembered by Bratz with Her Own Doll|last=Brasil|first=Sydney|date=March 18, 2024|magazine=[[Exclaim!]]|access-date=March 18, 2024}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Cyrus currently resides in [[Hidden Hills, California]], and also owns a $5.8 million home in her hometown of [[Franklin, Tennessee|Franklin]].<ref>{{cite web|last=David|first=Mark|url=https://www.dirt.com/entertainers/musicians/miley-cyrus-house-hidden-hills-1203330615/|title = Miley Cyrus Lands Back in Hidden Hills|website=Dirt.com|access-date=February 10, 2022|date = July 23, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Haggard |first1=Amanda |title=Miley Cyrus buys Franklin home for $5.8M |url=https://www.nashvillepost.com/business/development/miley-cyrus-buys-franklin-home-for-5-8m/article_8a104a2f-ff9a-5fa4-95bc-b8876ff5cbe8.html |website=[[NashvillePost.com]] |access-date=February 10, 2022 |date=August 14, 2017}}</ref> While Cyrus was raised as a [[Christians|Christian]] and identified herself as such during her childhood and early adult life,<ref name=baptized /> she includes references to [[Tibetan Buddhism]] in the lyrics to her song "Milky Milky Milk" (2015)<ref name="vftibet">{{cite web|url=https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2015/10/miley-cyrus-naked-concert|title=Miley Cyrus Reportedly Planning Naked Concert for Art (or Something)|website=Vanityfair.com|date=October 13, 2015|access-date=December 24, 2015}}</ref> and is also influenced by [[Hindu]] beliefs.<ref>{{cite web|date=February 7, 2017|title=Miley Cyrus' Lakshmi Puja And The West's Obsession With India|url=https://www.mansworldindia.com/people/personalities/talk/miley-cyrus-lakshmi-puja-wests-obsession-india/|access-date=June 11, 2021}}</ref>

Since 2019, she has been a vocally [[Voluntary childlessness|childfree]] person.<ref>{{Cite web |date=July 13, 2019 |title=Miley Cyrus Says Climate Change Has Affected Her Stance on Having Kids |url=https://www.elle.com/culture/celebrities/a28381501/miley-cyrus-climate-change-baby-plans-liam-hemsworth/ |access-date=January 27, 2024 |website=ELLE}}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Kaufman |first=Gil |date=August 14, 2020 |title=Miley Cyrus Talks Ditching Weed, Deep Meaning Behind 'Midnight Sky' and Whether She'll Ever Marry Again |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/pop/miley-cyrus-siriusxm-interview-sobriety-marriage-children-9434397/ |access-date=January 27, 2024 |magazine=Billboard}}</ref>
[[File:Miley Cyrus performs at the Kids Inaugural cropped 2.jpg|left|thumb|upright|Cyrus performing at the [[Verizon Center (Washington, D.C.)|Verizon Center]] in [[Washington, D.C.]] on January 19, 2009]]

===Sexuality and gender===
Cyrus [[Coming out|came out]] to her mother at age 14<ref name="Petrusich">{{cite magazine|first=Amanda|last=Petrusich| title=Free to Be Miley | magazine=Paper Magazine| date=June 9, 2015 | url=http://www.papermag.com/free-to-be-miley-1427581961.html | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160107201726/http://www.papermag.com/free-to-be-miley-1427581961.html | archive-date=January 7, 2016 | url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name="Gordon"/><ref name="celebrity.yahoo.com">{{cite web|title = Miley Cyrus: I Told My Mom I Love Women When I Was 14| date=June 10, 2015 |url = https://celebrity.yahoo.com/blogs/celeb-news/miley-cyrus--i-told-my-mom-i-love-women-at-14-000638339.html|access-date = June 10, 2015}}</ref> and has said: "I never want to label myself! I am ready to love anyone that loves me for who I am! I am open."<ref name="Brett Malec">{{cite web|title=Miley Cyrus: I've Had Relationships That Weren't ''Straight, Heterosexual'' Ones|url=http://www.eonline.com/news/654205/miley-cyrus-i-ve-had-relationships-that-weren-t-straight-heterosexual-ones|publisher=[[E! Online]]|access-date=May 10, 2015|first=Brett | last=Malec |date=May 6, 2015}}</ref> In June 2015, ''Time'' magazine reported she is [[gender fluid]].<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/6598191/miley-cyrus-gender-fluid-nothing-to-do-with-any-parts |title=Miley Cyrus Says She's Gender Fluid: 'It Has Nothing To Do With Any Parts of Me' |magazine=Billboard |date=June 16, 2015 |access-date=September 5, 2015}}</ref><ref name="Gordon">{{cite web|last=Gordon |first=Naomi |url=http://www.digitalspy.com/celebrity/news/a665877/miley-cyrus-opens-up-on-sexuality-im-pansexual-but-im-not-in-a-relationship.html#~pmG7ETX5OITeQL |title=Miley Cyrus opens up on sexuality: "I'm pansexual - but I'm not in a relationship" - Celebrity News |website=Digital Spy |date= August 28, 2015|access-date=September 5, 2015}}</ref><ref name="celebrity.yahoo.com"/><ref name="Brett Malec"/> She was quoted as stating she "doesn't relate to being boy or girl, and I don't have to have my partner relate to boy or girl."<ref name="Petrusich"/> Cyrus stated she is "literally open to every single thing that is consenting and doesn't involve an animal and everyone is of age".<ref name="Petrusich"/>

Cyrus is a supporter of the [[LGBT community]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/photos/photos-from-miley-cyrus-live-in-la/1642003/4970369/photo.jhtml#4970369 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131004224430/http://www.mtv.com/photos/photos-from-miley-cyrus-live-in-la/1642003/4970369/photo.jhtml |url-status=dead |archive-date=October 4, 2013 |title=Miley dedicated 'My Heart Beats for Love' to all her gay fans.|work=MTV News. Viacom|access-date=April 29, 2013}}</ref> Her song ''My Heart Beats for Love'' (2010) was written for one of Cyrus's gay friends,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://oceanup.com/2010/06/16/miley-cyrus-i-wrote-stay-about-liam |title=Miley Cyrus, 'I Wrote 'STAY' About Liam' |publisher=Ocean Up |date=June 16, 2010 |access-date=April 29, 2013}}</ref> while she has since claimed [[London]] to be her favorite place to perform due to its extensive gay scene.<ref>{{cite news|title=Miley Cyrus: I love London because there are so many gay people|url=http://www.pinknews.co.uk/2012/12/31/miley-cyrus-i-love-london-because-there-are-so-many-gay-people/|newspaper=Pink News|access-date=January 1, 2013|last=Roberts | first=Scott |date=December 31, 2012}}</ref> Cyrus also has an [[equals sign]] tattooed on her ring finger in support of same-sex marriage.<ref>{{cite web|last=Ford |first=Rebecca |url=https://hollywoodreporter.com/news/miley-cyrus-supports-gay-marriage-217430 |title=Miley Cyrus Supports Gay Marriage With Tattoo |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=July 30, 2011 |access-date=May 14, 2015}}</ref> After her 2018 marriage to a man, Cyrus went on the record to state she still identified as [[queer]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://people.com/music/miley-cyrus-sexuality-everything-she-has-said/ |title=Everything Miley Cyrus Has Said About Her Sexuality |last=Mizoguchi |first=Karen |date=August 12, 2019 |website=People|access-date=August 16, 2019}}</ref> She founded the [[Happy Hippie Foundation]] in 2014, which works to "Fight injustice facing [[Homelessness|homeless]] youth, LGBTQ youth and other vulnerable populations".<ref name="The Happy Hippie Foundation"/>

===Veganism===
Cyrus became a [[vegan]] and stopped eating animal products in 2014.<ref name=MileyVegan>{{Cite web |last=Starostinetskaya |first=Anna |title=Miley Cyrus on Ditching Veganism: "I Think When You Become the Face of Something, It's a Lot of Pressure." |url=https://vegnews.com/2020/9/miley-cyrus-on-ditching-veganism-i-think-when-you-become-the-face-of-something-it-s-a-lot-of-pressure |access-date=July 30, 2022 |website=VegNews.com}}</ref> In September 2020, Cyrus revealed on ''[[The Joe Rogan Experience]]'' that she had to switch to a [[Pescetarianism|pescatarian]] diet after suffering from [[Omega-3 fatty acids|omega-3]] deficiency, saying "I've been a vegan for a very long time and I had to introduce fish and omegas into my life because my brain wasn't functioning properly."<ref name=MileyVegan/> Cyrus further revealed that she cried when eating her first fish after her vegan diet, saying "I cried for the fish&nbsp;... it really hurts me to eat fish."<ref>{{Cite web |last=Leffler |first=Samantha |date=September 3, 2020 |title=Miley Cyrus Cried the 1st Time She Ate Fish After Her Vegan Diet |url=https://www.usmagazine.com/food/news/miley-cyrus-cried-the-1st-time-she-ate-fish-after-vegan-diet/ |access-date=July 30, 2022 |website=Us Weekly}}</ref> Her decision to quit being vegan sparked backlash from people in the vegan and [[vegetarian]] community, who accused Cyrus of "spreading misinformation about omega-3" and "abandoning her vegan diet".<ref>{{Cite web |title=Miley Cyrus is no longer vegan and people are fuming |url=https://www.capitalfm.com/artists/miley-cyrus/not-vegan-diet-2020/ |access-date=2024-06-09 |website=Capital |language=en}}</ref>

===Cannabis use===
Cyrus has been open about her recreational use of [[Cannabis (drug)|cannabis]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Longmire|first=Becca|title=Happy Birthday Miley Cyrus! Her 21st Year In Pictures: Liam Hemsworth Split, Nakedness, Twerking, More|url=http://www.entertainmentwise.com/photos/133560/5/Happy-Birthday-Miley-Cyrus-Her-21st-Year-In-Pictures-Liam-Hemsworth-Split-Nakedness-Twerking-More|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140409171927/http://www.entertainmentwise.com/photos/133560/5/Happy-Birthday-Miley-Cyrus-Her-21st-Year-In-Pictures-Liam-Hemsworth-Split-Nakedness-Twerking-More|url-status=dead|archive-date=April 9, 2014|publisher=Entertainment Wise|access-date=November 24, 2013|date=November 23, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://abcnews.go.com/blogs/entertainment/2013/06/miley-cyrus-alcohol-more-dangerous-than-weed-2/ |title=Miley Cyrus: Alcohol More Dangerous Than Weed|work=ABC News|date=June 19, 2013 |access-date=October 7, 2013}}</ref> She told ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' in 2013 that it was "the best drug on earth" and called it, along with [[MDMA]], a "happy drug".<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/miley-cyrus-on-why-she-loves-weed-went-wild-at-the-vmas-and-much-more-20130927|title=Miley Cyrus on Why She Loves Weed, Went Wild at the VMAs and Much More|magazine=[[Rolling Stone]]|date= September 27, 2013|last=Eells | first=John |access-date=October 8, 2013}}</ref> While accepting the Best Video Award at the [[2013 MTV Europe Music Awards]], Cyrus appeared to smoke a [[Joint (cannabis)|joint]] onstage; this was removed from the delayed broadcast of the show in the United States.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/miley-cyrus-smokes-a-joint-on-stage-at-mtv-emas/|title=Miley Cyrus smokes a joint on stage at MTV EMAs|work=[[CBS News]]|date=November 10, 2013|access-date=April 29, 2013}}</ref> In a 2014 interview with ''[[W (magazine)|W]]'' magazine, Cyrus stated "I love weed" and "I just love getting stoned."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wmagazine.com/people/celebrities/2014/02/miley-cyrus-ronan-farrow/|title=My Oh Miley!|work=W Magazine|date=February 3, 2014|access-date=February 5, 2014|archive-date=November 10, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161110162516/http://www.wmagazine.com/people/celebrities/2014/02/miley-cyrus-ronan-farrow/|url-status=dead}}</ref> In a 2017 interview on ''[[The Tonight Show Starring Jimmy Fallon]]'', Cyrus said that she had quit cannabis before the press tour for her ''Younger Now'' album so she could be "super clear" when discussing the record.<ref>{{cite magazine |url=https://ew.com/tv/2017/06/15/miley-cyrus-marijuana-jimmy-fallon/ |title=Miley Cyrus Reveals Why She Quit Smoking Marijuana |last=Romano |first=Nick |date=June 17, 2017 |magazine=Entertainment Weekly|access-date=August 16, 2019}}</ref> During a 2018 interview with [[Andy Cohen (TV personality)|Andy Cohen]], she credited her mother for reintroducing her to cannabis.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/allthemoms/2018/12/10/miley-cyrus-says-mom-got-her-smoking-marijuana-again/2269110002/ |title=Miley Cyrus smoking weed again: 'My mom got me back on it' |last=Haller |first=Sonja |date=December 10, 2018 |website=USA Today|access-date=August 16, 2019}}</ref> In 2019, Cyrus sent "Nothing Breaks Like a Heart" collaborator [[Mark Ronson]] a cannabis bouquet from [[Lowell Herb Co]] as a [[tongue-in-cheek]] Valentine's Day gift.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.pedestrian.tv/entertainment/miley-cyrus-mark-ronson-weed-bouquet/ |title=Miley Cyrus Gave Mark Ronson A Weed Bouquet For Valentine's Day |last=Duncan |first=Alasdair |date=February 15, 2019 |website=Pedestrian TV |access-date=August 16, 2019}}</ref> She invested in the [[cannabis company]] in August.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://culturemagazine.com/miley-cyrus-and-other-stars-invest-in-cannabis-company/ |title=Miley Cyrus and Other Stars Invest in Cannabis Company |last=Adams |first=Benjamin M. |date=August 22, 2019 |website=Culture Magazine |access-date=September 15, 2019 |archive-date=June 30, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200630171633/https://culturemagazine.com/miley-cyrus-and-other-stars-invest-in-cannabis-company/ |url-status=dead }}</ref>

Before and shortly after vocal cord surgery in November 2019, Cyrus stated that she had stayed sober from the use of cannabis and [[alcohol (drug)|alcohol]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Miley Cyrus' Mom Tish Opens Up About Singer's Sobriety: 'She's the Cleanest Person I Know'|url=https://people.com/music/miley-cyrus-mom-tish-opens-up-about-singer-sobriety/|access-date=May 4, 2021|website=People}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.delish.com/just-for-fun/a29552468/miley-cyrus-sober-four-months/|title=Miley Cyrus Said She's Been Sober For Four Months: "It's The Best I've Ever Felt"|first=Emily|last=Dixon|date=October 22, 2019|website=Delish}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.delish.com/food-news/a33915279/miley-cyrus-vocal-surgery-sobriety/|title=Miley Cyrus Said She Got Sober After Undergoing Vocal Surgery Last Year|first=Kristin|last=Salaky|date=September 3, 2020|website=Delish}}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/9444320/miley-cyrus-vocal-surgery-got-her-sober|title=Miley Cyrus Says Vocal Surgery Got Her Sober|date=September 3, 2020|magazine=Billboard}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.goodmorningamerica.com/culture/story/miley-cyrus-reveals-sobriety-journey-influenced-song-72374179|title=Miley Cyrus reveals how her sobriety journey influenced her new song|website=Good Morning America}}</ref>

===Relationships===
Cyrus has said that she dated singer-actor [[Nick Jonas]] from June 2006 to December 2007,<ref>{{cite web|title=Joe Jonas Confirms Nick and Miley Dating|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1614365/joe-jonas-confirms-nick-miley-dating.jhtml|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121105222222/http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1614365/joe-jonas-confirms-nick-miley-dating.jhtml|url-status=dead|archive-date=November 5, 2012|publisher=[[MTV News]]. Viacom.|access-date=April 29, 2014}}</ref> claiming they were "in love" and began dating soon after they first met.<ref>{{cite web|title=Miley Cyrus Says She and Nick Jonas Were 'In Love'|url=http://www.foxnews.com/story/2008/08/07/miley-cyrus-says-and-nick-jonas-were-in-love/|publisher=[[Fox News]]|access-date=August 8, 2008|date=August 7, 2008}}</ref> Their relationship attracted considerable media attention.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/1591633/miley-cyrus-super-sorry-for-mocking-demi-lovato-selena-gomez-in-video/|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141108002954/http://www.mtv.com/news/1591633/miley-cyrus-super-sorry-for-mocking-demi-lovato-selena-gomez-in-video/|url-status=dead|archive-date=November 8, 2014|title=Miley Cyrus 'Super Sorry' For Mocking Demi Lovato, Selena Gomez In Video|website=Mtv.com|access-date=July 31, 2016}}</ref> Cyrus was in a nine-month relationship with model [[Justin Gaston]] from 2008 to 2009.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.chicagotribune.com/news/ct-xpm-2009-06-10-0906090336-story.html|title=Miley Cyrus, Justin Gaston post to Twitter about their breakup|newspaper=Chicago Tribune|date=June 10, 2009|access-date=May 30, 2019}}</ref> While filming ''The Last Song'', Cyrus began an [[on-again, off-again relationship]] with her co-star [[Liam Hemsworth]] in 2009.<ref name="Fisher, Luchina">{{cite web|title=Liam Hemsworth: Five Things to Know About Miley's Man|url=https://abcnews.go.com/Entertainment/things-mileys-man-liam-hemsworth/story?id=16003401|work=[[ABC News (United States)|ABC News]]|access-date=May 2, 2014|last=Fisher | first=Luchina |date=March 26, 2012}}</ref> During the breakups, Cyrus was romantically linked to actors [[Lucas Till]] (2009) and [[Josh Bowman]] (2011).<ref name="vulture">{{cite web |url=https://www.vulture.com/2019/08/miley-cyrus-liam-hemsworth-relationship-timeline.html |title=Miley Cyrus, Liam Hemsworth, and All the People Who Orbited Their Decade-Long Relationship |last=Haylock |first=Zoe |date=August 13, 2019 |website=Vulture.com |access-date=August 15, 2019}}</ref> Cyrus and Hemsworth were first engaged from May 2012 until September 2013.<ref>{{cite news|title=Miley Cyrus engaged to 'Hunger Games' star|url=http://www.cnn.com/2012/06/06/showbiz/miley-cyrus-engaged/|work=CNN|access-date=April 7, 2014|date=June 9, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Heller|first=Corinne|title=Miley Cyrus, Liam Hemsworth end engagement (Confirmed)|url=http://www.ontheredcarpet.com/Miley-Cyrus--Liam-Hemsworth-end-engagement-Confirmed/9250360|publisher=On the Red Carpet|access-date=April 7, 2014|date=September 16, 2013}}</ref> She has also dated actor [[Patrick Schwarzenegger]] (2014–2015) and model [[Stella Maxwell]] (2015).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.elle.com/culture/music/a12505661/miley-cyrus-shes-not-him-lyrics-liam-hemsworth-stella-maxwell-lyrics/|title=All the Liam Hemsworth and Stella Maxwell References in Miley Cyrus's "She's Not Him" Lyrics|last=Bailey|first=Alyssa|work=Elle|date=September 29, 2017|access-date=May 30, 2019}}</ref><ref name="Fisher, Luchina"/><ref>{{cite web|last=Saad|first=Nardine|title=Miley Cyrus, Patrick Schwarzenegger reportedly call it quits|date=April 21, 2015|website=[[Los Angeles Times]]|url=https://latimes.com/entertainment/gossip/la-et-mg-miley-cyrus-patrick-schwarzenegger-split-break-up-20150421-story.html|access-date=July 10, 2015}}</ref>

Cyrus and Hemsworth rekindled their relationship in March 2016,<ref>{{cite news|last=Ledbetter|first=Carly|title=Dolly Parton Confirms Miley Cyrus And Liam Hemsworth Are Back On|date=March 9, 2016|newspaper=The Huffington Post|url=https://huffingtonpost.com/entry/dolly-parton-miley-cyrus-back-on_us_56e022bae4b065e2e3d4319f|access-date=May 28, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=B. Kile|first=Meredith|title=Miley Cyrus and Liam Hemsworth Attend 'Huntsman' Premiere Together, Fans Freak Out|date=April 11, 2016|publisher=[[Entertainment Tonight]]|url=http://www.etonline.com/news/186541_miley_cyrus_and_liam_hemsworth_attend_huntsman_premiere_together_fans_freak_out/ |access-date=May 28, 2016}}</ref> and became re-engaged that October.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/entertainthis/2016/10/27/miley-cyrus-liam-hemsworth-engagement-ring-ellen-degeneres-show/92827846/|title=Finally! Miley Cyrus addresses her engagement ring from Liam Hemsworth on 'Ellen'|newspaper=USA Today|access-date=October 27, 2016}}</ref> In November 2018, Cyrus and Hemsworth's home burned down in the [[Woolsey Fire]] in [[California]].<ref name=":3">{{cite web | url=https://m.facebook.com/story.php?story_fbid=10156917914262147&id=5845317146&_ft_=mf_story_key.10156917914262147 | title=Miley Cyrus| website=[[Facebook]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite tweet|number=1061862918281515009|user=MileyCyrus|title=Completely devestated by the fires affecting my community. I am one of the lucky ones. My animals and LOVE OF MY LIFE made it out safely & that's all that matters right now. My house no longer stands but the memories shared with family & friends stand strong. I am grateful for|date=November 12, 2018|author=Miley Ray Cyrus|access-date=March 18, 2019}}</ref> On December 23, Cyrus and Hemsworth married in a private wedding ceremony in their home in [[Nashville, Tennessee|Nashville]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/miley-cyrus-liam-hemsworth-are-married-1171589|title=Miley Cyrus and Liam Hemsworth Are Married|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=December 26, 2018}}</ref> She felt that her marriage "[redefined] what it looks like for someone that's a queer person like [herself] to be in a hetero relationship" though she was "still very sexually attracted to women". Cyrus indicated that the ceremony was "kind of out of character for [her]" because "[they have] worn rings forever [and] definitely didn't need it in any way". She believed the loss of their home to be the catalyst for getting married, citing that "the timing felt right" and that "no one is promised the next day, or the next, so [she tries] to be 'in the now' as much as possible".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.elle.com/culture/celebrities/a26443527/miley-cyrus-on-liam-hemsworth-marriage/|title=Miley Cyrus Explains Why She and Liam Hemsworth Got Married Even Though She Felt She 'Didn't Need' To|last=Bailey|first=Alyssa|work=Elle|date=February 21, 2019|access-date=May 30, 2019}}</ref> On August 10, 2019, Cyrus announced their separation;<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.teenvogue.com/story/miley-cyrus-liam-hemsworth-reportedly-split-up|title=Miley Cyrus and Liam Hemsworth Have Reportedly Split Up|last=Elizabeth|first=De|date=August 10, 2019|access-date=August 10, 2019}}</ref> eleven days later, Hemsworth filed for divorce, citing "irreconcilable differences",<ref>{{cite web|url=https://people.com/music/liam-hemsworth-files-divorce-miley-cyrus/|title=Liam Hemsworth Files for Divorce from Miley Cyrus After 7 Months of Marriage|magazine=People|first=Jeff|last=Nelson|date=August 21, 2019|access-date=August 21, 2019}}</ref> and their divorce was finalized on January 28, 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://abcnews.go.com/Entertainment/wireStory/miley-cyrus-liam-hemsworth-single-divorce-finalized-68595531|title=Miley Cyrus, Liam Hemsworth single again, divorce finalized|website=ABC News|access-date=January 28, 2020}}</ref>

After announcing her separation from Hemsworth, she dated Kaitlynn Carter from August to September 2019.<ref>{{cite web|title=Miley Cyrus Spotted Kissing Kaitlynn Carter in Italy|url=https://www.etonline.com/miley-cyrus-spotted-kissing-brody-jenners-ex-kaitlynn-carter-in-italy-see-the-pda-packed-pics|access-date=August 19, 2020|website=Entertainment Tonight|date=August 10, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|last1=Gonzales|first1=Erica|last2=Sanchez|first2=Chelsey|date=September 26, 2019|title=Miley Cyrus Is Reportedly "Looking Forward to Being Single"|url=https://www.harpersbazaar.com/celebrity/latest/a28678451/miley-cyrus-kaitlynn-carter-relationship/|access-date=August 19, 2020|magazine=Harper's BAZAAR}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Carter|first=Kaitlynn|date=November 4, 2019|title=Kaitlynn Carter Opens Up About Her Summer of Self-Discovery|url=https://www.elle.com/culture/celebrities/a29646191/kaitlynn-carter-miley-cyrus-relationship-essay/|access-date=August 19, 2020|website=Elle}}</ref> In October 2019, Cyrus began dating Australian singer [[Cody Simpson]], a longtime friend.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.news.com.au/entertainment/celebrity-life/hook-ups-break-ups/cody-simpson-confirms-relationship-with-passionate-miley-cyrus/news-story/3e83ecbbd7553138c97937794af14f34|title= Cody Simpson confirms relationship with 'passionate' Miley Cyrus|website=News.com.au|last=Coy|first=Bronte|date=October 15, 2019}}</ref> In August 2020, Cyrus announced that she and Simpson had split up.<ref>{{cite web|last=Weaver|first=Hilary|date=August 15, 2020|title=Why Miley Cyrus and Cody Simpson's Relationship 'Fizzled Out'|url=https://www.elle.com/culture/a33612620/miley-cyrus-cody-simpson-breakup-reason/|access-date=August 19, 2020|website=Elle}}</ref> Her announcement coincided with the release of her single "[[Midnight Sky]]", which was inspired by her breakups with Hemsworth, Carter, and Simpson.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.yahoo.com/entertainment/new-miley-cyrus-song-declares-i-dont-belong-to-anyone-just-hours-after-cody-simpson-split-054151259.html|title=New Miley Cyrus song declares 'I don't belong to anyone' just hours after Cody Simpson split|date=August 14, 2020|website=Yahoo! Entertainment|publisher=Yahoo|access-date=August 14, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200814215019/https://www.yahoo.com/entertainment/new-miley-cyrus-song-declares-i-dont-belong-to-anyone-just-hours-after-cody-simpson-split-054151259.html|archive-date=August 14, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Ryan|first=Patrick|title=Miley Cyrus gets personal on new disco-inspired song 'Midnight Sky,' shares self-directed video|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/entertainment/music/2020/08/14/miley-cyrus-midnight-sky-new-song-video/3370913001/|access-date=August 19, 2020|website=USA Today}}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine|date=August 14, 2020|title=She's Here: Miley Cyrus Drops 'Midnight Sky' Single & Video|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/9433998/miley-cyrus-midnight-sky-single-video|access-date=August 19, 2020|magazine=Billboard}}</ref> Cyrus began dating musician Maxx Morando in 2021, who also worked as a producer on her album ''Endless Summer Vacation'' (2023).<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Gibson |first=Kelsie |date=February 7, 2024 |title=Who Is Miley Cyrus' Boyfriend? All About Maxx Morando |url=https://people.com/music/maxx-morando-facts-dating-miley-cyrus/ |access-date=April 19, 2024 |magazine=People}}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Park |first=Sabrina |date=February 4, 2024 |title=Who Is Miley Cyrus's Boyfriend, Maxx Morando? |url=https://www.harpersbazaar.com/celebrity/latest/a43272763/who-is-miley-cyrus-new-boyfriend-maxx-morando/ |access-date=April 19, 2024 |magazine=[[Harper's Bazaar]]}}</ref>

==Philanthropy==
Throughout her career Cyrus has sung on several charity singles such as: "[[Just Stand Up!]]", "[[Send It On (Disney song)|Send It On]]", "[[Everybody Hurts (Helping Haiti song)|Everybody Hurts]]" and "[[We Are the World 25 for Haiti]]".<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1593043/20080819/carey_mariah.jhtml|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080828040741/http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1593043/20080819/carey_mariah.jhtml|url-status=dead|archive-date=August 28, 2008|title=Mariah Carey, Beyonce, Fergie, Miley Cyrus, More Collaborate On Cancer Benefit Single|last=Kaufman|first=Gil|date=August 19, 2008|work=MTV News. Viacom.|access-date=August 20, 2008}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1608455/20090403/cyrus__miley.jhtml|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090406015055/http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1608455/20090403/cyrus__miley.jhtml|url-status=dead|archive-date=April 6, 2009|title=Miley Cyrus And Nick Jonas Hook Up For Charity|first=Gil|last=Kaufman|date=April 3, 2009|work=MTV News. Viacom.|access-date=November 11, 2009}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/entertainment/8492058.stm|title=Haiti all-star charity single gets first airplay |work=BBC News|date=February 2, 2010|access-date=February 2, 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.usatoday.com/life/music/news/2010-02-15-wearetheworld15_ST_N.htm |title=Quincy Jones, Lionel Richie pass 'We Are the World' baton |last=Gundersen | first=Edna |website=[[USA Today]] |date=February 14, 2010 |access-date=February 15, 2010}}</ref> She is an avid supporter of the [[City of Hope National Medical Center]] in California, having attended benefit concerts in 2008, 2009 and 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wdrb.com/story/8814486/the-walt-disney-company-is-presenting-miley-cyrus-jonas-brothers-and-demi-lovato-in-a-special-concert-to-benefit-city-of-hope-on-september-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140808035714/http://www.wdrb.com/story/8814486/the-walt-disney-company-is-presenting-miley-cyrus-jonas-brothers-and-demi-lovato-in-a-special-concert-to-benefit-city-of-hope-on-september-14|url-status=dead|archive-date=August 8, 2014|title=The Walt Disney Company Is Presenting Miley Cyrus, Jonas Brothers and Demi Lovato in a Special Concert to Benefit City of Hope on September 14|date=August 8, 2008|publisher=WDRB|access-date=July 31, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.accessonline.com/articles/miley-cyrus-jesse-mccartney-and-demi-lovato-to-perform-at-concert-for-hope-benefit-77416|title=Miley Cyrus, Jesse McCartney And Demi Lovato To Perform At Concert For Hope Benefit|date=October 16, 2009|work=Access Online|access-date=October 2, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vh1.com/celebrity/2012-10-11/the-singers-big-gown-showdown-miley-cyrus-vs-jordin-sparks-vs-britney-spears/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121015061534/http://www.vh1.com/celebrity/2012-10-11/the-singers-big-gown-showdown-miley-cyrus-vs-jordin-sparks-vs-britney-spears/ |url-status=dead |archive-date=October 15, 2012 |title=The Singer's Big Gown Showdown: Miley Cyrus Vs. Jordin Sparks Vs. Britney Spears |last=Muttoo | first=Ambika |date=October 11, 2012 |publisher=[[VH1]] }}</ref> In 2008 and 2009, during her Best of Both Worlds and Wonder World Tours, for every concert ticket sold, she donated one dollar to the organization.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cityofhope.org/about/publications/news/Pages/miley-cyrus-demi-lovato-and-jesse-mccartney-perform-benefit-concert-for-city-of-hope-on-october-25.aspx |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090928075257/http://www.cityofhope.org/about/publications/news/Pages/miley-cyrus-demi-lovato-and-jesse-mccartney-perform-benefit-concert-for-city-of-hope-on-october-25.aspx |url-status=dead |archive-date=September 28, 2009 |title=Miley Cyrus, Demi Lovato and Jesse McCartney to perform at second annual Concert for Hope presented by Staples, Inc., October 25 at Nokia Theatre L.A. LIVE |date=September 22, 2009 |access-date=October 8, 2009 |publisher=[[City of Hope National Medical Center]] }}</ref> Cyrus celebrated her 16th birthday at Disneyland by delivering a [[US$]]1{{nbsp}}million donation from Disney to [[Youth Service America]].<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://variety.com/2008/tv/news/miley-cyrus-sha-19457/|title=Miley Cyrus: Sharing her 'Sweet 16′ fun at Disneyland|date=October 6, 2008|magazine=Variety|access-date=August 1, 2014}}</ref> In July 2009, Cyrus performed at the [[Elizabeth Glaser Pediatric AIDS Foundation]]'s 20th annual '' Time for Heroes'' celebrity picnic<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.looktothestars.org/news/2574-miley-cyrus-to-give-her-time-for-heroes|title=Miley Cyrus To Give Her Time For Heroes|date=May 26, 2009|publisher=Look to the Stars|access-date=July 31, 2014}}</ref> and donated several items including autographed merchandise, and a script from ''Hannah Montana'' for the Ronald McDonald House Auction.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chattanoogan.com/2009/7/21/155294/Miley-Cyrus-Donates-Items-For-Ronald.aspx|title=Miley Cyrus Donates Items For Ronald McDonald House Auction|date=July 21, 2009|publisher=Chattanoogan|access-date=August 1, 2014}}</ref> 

Cyrus has supported charities including the [[Elton John AIDS Foundation]], [[Entertainment Industry Foundation]], [[Habitat for Humanity]], [[United Service Organizations]], Youth Service America and [[Music for Relief]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.looktothestars.org/charity/elton-john-aids-foundation|title=Elton John AIDS Foundation Celebrity Supporters & Events|publisher=Look to the Stars|access-date=July 31, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.looktothestars.org/charity/entertainment-industry-foundation|title=Entertainment Industry Foundation Celebrity Supporters & Events|publisher=Look to the Stars|access-date=July 31, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.looktothestars.org/charity/habitat-for-humanity|title=Habitat For Humanity Celebrity Supporters & Events|publisher=Look to the Stars|access-date=July 31, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.looktothestars.org/charity/muhammad-ali-parkinson-center|title=Muhammad Ali Parkinson Center Celebrity Supporters & Events|publisher=Look to the Stars|access-date=July 31, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.looktothestars.org/charity/united-service-organization|title=United Service Organization Celebrity Supporters & Events|publisher=Look to the Stars|access-date=July 31, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://act.mtv.com/posts/miley-cyrus-says-get-your-good-on-encourages-youth-volunteerism/|title=Miley Cyrus Says 'Get Your Good On,' Encourages Youth Volunteerism|last=Walker|first=Caroline|date=July 5, 2011|work=MTV News. Viacom|access-date=July 31, 2014|archive-date=August 9, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140809181111/http://act.mtv.com/posts/miley-cyrus-says-get-your-good-on-encourages-youth-volunteerism/|url-status=dead}}</ref>  In January 2010, Cyrus posted the final video to her ''mileymandy'' YouTube Account.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.youtube.com/user/mileymandy | title=Mileymandy - YouTube | website=[[YouTube]] }}</ref> In the video, Cyrus promoted support for ''[[To Write Love on Her Arms (film)|To Write Love on Her Arms]]'',<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rNLR41afZsQ | title=TWLOHA | website=[[YouTube]] | date=January 20, 2010 }}</ref><ref>{{cite tweet |url=https://twitter.com/twloha/status/8021909563 |title=Miley Cyrus asks her fans to help TWLOHA win $1 million for suicide prevention |user=TWLOHA |number=8021909563 |date=January 21, 2010 |access-date=July 18, 2022}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.seventeen.com/celebrity/music/news/a6613/miley-cyrus-supports-to-write-love-on-her-arms/ | title=Miley Cyrus Supports to Write Love on Her Arms | date=January 22, 2010 }}</ref> and he next day appeared in a promotional video for the film with [[Joaquin Phoenix]], and [[Liv Tyler]].<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tzX6XXVEa4s | title=MILEY CYRUS TEACHES JOAQUIN PHOENIX & LIV TYLER How to Vote for TWLOHA and Suicide Prevention | website=[[YouTube]] | date=January 22, 2010 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.looktothestars.org/video/199-miley-cyrus-teaches-joaquin-phoenix-and-liv-tyler-how-to-support-twloha-com |title=Miley Cyrus Teaches Joaquin Phoenix and Liv Tyler How To Support TWLOHA.com |publisher=Look to the Stars |access-date=July 2, 2022}}</ref>  In February 2010, she donated several items, including the dress she wore to the [[52nd Annual Grammy Awards]], and two tickets to the Hollywood premiere of her film ''The Last Song'', to raise money for the victims of the [[2010 Haiti earthquake]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/showbiz/news/a200707/miley-cyrus-auctions-grammy-dress-for-haiti.html#~oLCiyn4qZ3SGbQ|title=Miley Cyrus auctions Grammy dress for Haiti|last=Martin | first=Lara |date=February 1, 2010|website=[[Digital Spy]]|access-date=July 31, 2014}}</ref> In April 2010, Cyrus, working with the [[Make-A-Wish Foundation]], performed for and met with 29 children at [[The Grove at Farmers Market]] in Los Angeles, California.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zDBH9S4Mfc4 | title=Miley Cyrus Makes Memorable Day for 29 Wish Kids for World Wish Day® 2010 | website=[[YouTube]] | date=April 10, 2011 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=o8AAQeieXmo | title=Miley Cyrus Performs "The Climb" at Make-A-Wish® Celebration for World Wish Day | website=[[YouTube]] | date=April 30, 2010 }}</ref> Cyrus continued to support The Make-A-Wish Foundation, and met with at least 150 children.<ref name="youtube1">{{cite web | url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=veo4U5omHZY | title=MIley Cyrus Talks About Being a Make-A-Wish® Wish Granter | website=[[YouTube]] | date=April 23, 2012 }}</ref>

[[File:Miley Cyrus at Kids' Inaugural 3 cropped.jpg|thumb|upright|Cyrus performing at the Kids Inaugural: We Are the Future concert in 2009]]

In January 2011, Cyrus met an ailing fan with [[spina bifida]] with the charity [[Kids Wish Network]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kidswishnetwork.org/2011/02/kids-wish-network-and-miley-cyrus-grant-wish-to-ailing-boy-with-spina-bifida/ |title=Kids Wish Network and Miley Cyrus Grant Wish to Ailing Boy with Spina Bifida |date=January 25, 2011 |publisher=[[Kids Wish Network]] |access-date=July 31, 2014 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140812052614/http://kidswishnetwork.org/2011/02/kids-wish-network-and-miley-cyrus-grant-wish-to-ailing-boy-with-spina-bifida/ |archive-date=August 12, 2014 }}</ref> In April 2011, she appeared in a commercial for the [[American Red Cross]] asking people to pledge $10 to help those affected by the [[2011 Tōhoku earthquake and tsunami]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.redcrossyouth.org/2011/04/14/miley-cyrus-psa-japan-relief/|title=Miley Cyrus PSA: Japan Relief|date=April 14, 2014|publisher=Red Cross|access-date=August 1, 2014}}</ref> That same year, [[Hilary Duff]] presented Cyrus with the first-ever Global Action Youth Leadership Award at the first Annual Global Action Awards Gala for her support of [[Blessings in a Backpack]], an organization that works to feed hungry children in schools, and her personal ''Get Ur Good On'' campaign with the Youth Services of America. Cyrus stated: "I want (kids) to do something they love. Not something that seems like a chore because someone tells them that's the right thing to do or what their parents want or what's important to people around them, but what's in their heart."<ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://www.contactmusic.com/news/cyrus-honoured-with-youth-award_1202984|title=Miley Cyrus – Cyrus Honoured With Youth Award|author=Wenn|magazine=Contactmusic|date=February 20, 2011|access-date=May 21, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/miley-cyrus-honored-with-youth-leadership-award/|title=Miley Cyrus honored with youth leadership award|last=Lee | first=Joyce |work=[[CBS News]]|date=February 22, 2011|access-date=May 21, 2014}}</ref> In December 2011, she appeared in a commercial for the charity [[J/P Haitian Relief Organization]], and teamed up with her elder brother Trace Cyrus to design a limited-edition T-shirt and hoodie for charity. All proceeds from the sale of these items went to her charity, Get Ur Good On, which supports education for under-privileged children.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=AyIGaIIp9lE |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/varchive/youtube/20211213/AyIGaIIp9lE |archive-date=December 13, 2021 |url-status=live|title=Miley Cyrus J P HRO Super Give Away [Help Haiti Home]|website=[[YouTube]]|date=December 17, 2011|access-date=July 31, 2014}}{{cbignore}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/the-hook/464800/miley-cyrus-designs-t-shirt-with-brother|title=Miley Cyrus Designs T-Shirt With Brother|last=DelliCarpini | first=Gregory Jr. |date=December 29, 2011|magazine=Billboard|access-date=August 1, 2014}}</ref> That month, she performed "The Climb" at the ''CNN Heroes: An All-Star Tribute'' at the Shrine Auditorium in Los Angeles.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.edition.cnn.com/2011/11/30/living/cnnheroes-preview/|title=An awards show unlike any other|last=Almond | first=Kyle |date=December 12, 2011|work=CNN|access-date=August 1, 2014}}</ref>

In 2012, Cyrus released a cover version of Bob Dylan's "[[You're Gonna Make Me Lonesome When You Go]]" with Johnzo West for the charity [[Amnesty International]] as a part of the album ''[[Chimes of Freedom (album)|Chimes of Freedom]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.amnestyusa.org/news/multimedia/miley-cyrus-featuring-johnzo-west-you-re-gonna-make-me-lonesome-when-you-go|title=NMiley Cyrus featuring Johnzo West - 'You're Gonna Make Me Lonesome When You Go'|date=April 30, 2015|publisher=[[Amnesty International]]|access-date=August 7, 2016}}</ref> She also appeared in a commercial for the [[Rock the Vote]] campaign, which encouraged young people to make their voices heard by voting in the 2012 federal election.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://popdust.com/2012/09/19/miley-cyrus-rock-the-vote-campaign-election-2012-video/|title=Miley Cyrus and Her New Hair Encourage You to Vote in This Year's Election|last=Exton | first=Emily |date=September 19, 2012|publisher=Popdust|access-date=July 11, 2014}}</ref> For her 20th birthday, activists at [[People for the Ethical Treatment of Animals]] (PETA) adopted a pig called Nora in her name.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://www.contactmusic.com/news/miley-cyrus-thanks-fans-for-birthday-fundraising_3388301|title=Miley Cyrus – Miley Cyrus Thanks Fans For Birthday Fundraising|author=Wenn|magazine=Contactmusic|date=November 25, 2012|access-date=May 21, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/showbiz/news/a440762/miley-cyrus-thanks-fans-for-birthday-fundraising.html#~oEU6EYoSCAxTxyIn|title=Miley Cyrus thanks fans for birthday fundraising|first1=Zeba|last1=Blay|website=[[Digital Spy]]|date=November 26, 2012|access-date=May 21, 2014}}</ref> Cyrus also supports 39 well-known charities, including [[Make-a-Wish Foundation]], [[Cystic Fibrosis Foundation]], [[St. Jude Children's Research Hospital|St.&nbsp;Jude's Children's Research Hospital]], [[To Write Love on Her Arms]], [[NOH8 Campaign]], [[Love Is Louder Than the Pressure to Be Perfect]] and [[The Jed Foundation]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.noh8campaign.com/article/miley-cyrus-teams-up-with-noh8-and-takes-a-stand-for-equality|title=Miley Cyrus teams up with NOH8 and takes a stand for Equality!|publisher=[[NOH8 Campaign]]|date=December 29, 2011|access-date=July 11, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.seventeen.com/health/tips/celebs-say-love-is-louder#slide-2|title=Celebs Say "Love Is Louder..."|last=Zellner | first=Maggie |work=[[Seventeen (American magazine)|Seventeen]]|access-date=July 11, 2014|date=July 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Love is Louder with Demi Lovato|url=http://www.seventeen.com/health/tips/celebs-say-love-is-louder|last=Zellner | first=Maggie |work=[[Seventeen (American magazine)|Seventeen]]|access-date=July 11, 2014|date=July 2011}}</ref> In 2013, Cyrus was named the fourteenth-most-charitable celebrity of the year by [[Do Something]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.latinpost.com/articles/5221/20131226/top-20-celebrities-giving-charity-taylor-swift-justin-bieber-miley.htm|title=Top 20 Celebrities Giving to Charity: Taylor Swift, Justin Bieber, and Miley Cyrus Head List|last=Harding | first=Scharon |publisher=Latin Post|date=December 26, 2013|access-date=May 20, 2014}}</ref> She also appeared with Justin Bieber and [[Pitbull (rapper)|Pitbull]] in a television special entitled ''The Real Change Project: Artists for Education''.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/1555963/justin-bieber-miley-cyrus-pitbull-team-for-educational-tv-special|title=Justin Bieber, Miley Cyrus & Pitbull Team For Educational TV Special|last=Ng | first=Philiana |magazine=Billboard|date=April 4, 2013|access-date=May 20, 2014}}</ref> On August 28, 2014, Miley appeared alongside [[Justin Timberlake]] at an [[HIV/AIDS]] charity event in the White House.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.missuniversusa.com/miss-universe-will-meet-barack-obama/|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140808042531/http://missuniversusa.com/miss-universe-will-meet-barack-obama/|url-status=dead|archive-date=August 8, 2014|title=Miss Universe will meet Barack Obama|date=July 26, 2014|publisher=Miss Universe USA|access-date=July 31, 2014}}</ref>

At the [[2014 MTV Video Music Awards]], Cyrus won [[MTV Video Music Award for Video of the Year|Video of the Year]] for her song ''Wrecking Ball''. Instead of accepting the award herself, she invited a 22-year-old homeless man by the name of Jesse to collect it on her behalf; she had met him at My Friend's Place, an organization that helps homeless youth find shelter, work, health care, and education. His acceptance speech urged musicians to learn more about youth homelessness in Los Angeles through Cyrus's [[Facebook]] page.<ref>{{cite web|first1=Rheana|last1=Murray|title=Entertainment Meet the Homeless Man Who Accepted Miley Cyrus' VMA Award|url=https://abcnews.go.com/US/meet-homeless-man-accepted-miley-cyrus-vma-award/story?id=25114619|work=ABC News|access-date=August 25, 2014|date=August 25, 2014}}</ref> Cyrus then launched a [[Prizeo]] campaign to raise funds for the charity; those who made donations were entered into a sweepstake for a chance to meet Cyrus on her Bangerz Tour in [[Rio de Janeiro]] that September.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2014/08/25/arts/music/miley-cyrus-steals-video-music-awards-again-this-time-by-staying-in-her-seat.html|title=VMAs 2014: Miley Cyrus Causes a Stir Again, This Time by Staying in Her Seat|work=[[The New York Times]]|date=August 25, 2014 |access-date=December 24, 2015|last1=Barnes |first1=Brooks }}</ref> In early 2015, Cyrus teamed up with [[MAC Cosmetics]] to launch her own branded Viva Glam lipstick, with proceeds to the [[Mac AIDS Fund]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.indiatvnews.com/lifestyle/news/miley-cyrus-to-launch-her-lipstick-for-mac-charity-3956.html|title=Miley Cyrus collaborates with a cosmetic brand to raise money for HIV charity|work=India TV|access-date=November 24, 2020}}</ref>

In June 2017, Cyrus performed at [[One Love Manchester]], a televised benefit concert organized by [[Ariana Grande]] following the [[Manchester Arena bombing]] on her concert two weeks earlier.<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Smirke|first=Richard|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/7817617/one-love-manchester-concert-ariana-grande-bravery-resilience|title=Bravery, Resilience Shine as Ariana Grande Leads All-Star Benefit Concert for Victims of Manchester Bombing|magazine=Billboard|date=June 4, 2017}}</ref> During an appearance on ''[[The Ellen DeGeneres Show]]'' in August 2017, Cyrus said that she would donate $500,000 to [[Hurricane Harvey]] relief efforts.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.eonline.com/news/877028/miley-cyrus-moved-to-tears-over-hurricane-harvey-and-donates-500-000-to-flood-relief-efforts|title=Miley Cyrus Moved to Tears Over Hurricane Harvey and Donates $500,000 to Flood Relief Efforts|work=[[E!]]|access-date=November 24, 2020}}</ref> In August 2019, she performed at the Sunny Hill Festival in [[Kosovo]], a festival to raise funds to help people with financial difficulties there, created by [[Dua Lipa]] and her father.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.etonline.com/dua-lipa-on-why-it-was-so-special-to-have-miley-cyrus-perform-at-her-sunny-hill-festival-in-kosovo|title=Dua Lipa on Why It Was So Special to Have Miley Cyrus Perform at Her Sunny Hill Festival in Kosovo (Exclusive)|access-date=April 6, 2020|last=Seemayer|first=Zach|date=September 9, 2019 |publisher=Entertainment Tonight}}</ref> In September 2019, Cyrus met with another fan through the Make-A-Wish Foundation at the 2019 [[iHeartRadio Music Festival]] in Las Vegas, Nevada.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6m8HnfWKyiE | title=Miley Cyrus Makes a Fan's Dream Come True! | website=[[YouTube]] | date=October 24, 2019 }}</ref><ref name="youtube1"/> Cyrus and her boyfriend [[Cody Simpson]] donated 120 [[taco]]s to healthcare workers amid the [[COVID-19 pandemic]] in April 2020.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://people.com/music/miley-cyrus-cody-simpson-deliver-tacos-healthcare-workers/|title=Miley Cyrus and Cody Simpson Deliver Tacos to Healthcare Workers amid Coronavirus Pandemic|work=People|access-date=November 24, 2020}}</ref> That same month, she partnered again with MAC Cosmetics's  annual Viva Glam campaign to donate $10 million toward 250 local organizations nationwide heavily impacted by the pandemic.

Cyrus showed support for the [[Black Lives Matter]] movement by sharing links and resources on social media, donning a Black Lives Matter face mask, and attending [[George Floyd protests|protests following the murder of George Floyd]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://theindependent.sg/miley-cyrus-and-cody-simpson-take-a-break-from-black-lives-matter-protests/|title=Miley Cyrus and Cody Simpson take a break from Black Lives Matter protests|first=Lydia|last=Koh|website=Theindependent.sg|date=June 15, 2020|access-date=December 5, 2020}}</ref>

===Happy Hippie Foundation===
Cyrus is the founder of the [[Happy Hippie Foundation]], which works to "fight injustice facing homeless youth, LGBTQ youth, and other vulnerable populations".<ref name="The Happy Hippie Foundation">{{cite web|url=http://www.happyhippies.org/|title=The Happy Hippie Foundation|website=Happyhippies.org|access-date=July 31, 2016}}</ref> From 2014 to 2016 the foundation served nearly 1,500 homeless youth in Los Angeles, reached more than 25,000 LGBTQ youth and their families with resources about gender, and provided social services to transgender individuals, youth in conflict zones, and people affected by crises.<ref>{{cite news |last=Setoodeh |first=Ramin |title=Miley Cyrus Stands Up for Homeless Youth |url=https://variety.com/2016/music/news/miley-cyrus-happy-hippe-foundation-homeless-youth-1201884032/ |access-date=December 7, 2018 |date=October 11, 2016}}</ref> Happy Hippie encourages Cyrus's fans to support causes including gender equality, LGBTQ rights and mental health through awareness campaigns and fundraising. Leading up to the 2020 presidential election, Happy Hippie encouraged its Instagram followers to seek out [[VoteRiders]] for assistance ensuring that gender identity would not affect their right to vote.

On June 15, 2015, Cyrus launched the campaign #InstaPride<ref>{{cite magazine |title=Miley Cyrus Instagram Instapride |url=http://time.com/3917249/miley-cyrus-instagram-instapride/ |magazine=[[Time (magazine)|Time]] |access-date=October 17, 2018}}</ref> in collaboration with Instagram. The campaign features a series of portraits starring [[transgender]] and gender-expansive people, which were posted to her Instagram feed with the hashtags "#HappyHippiePresents" and "#InstaPride". It stated that it was aimed at encouraging diversity and tolerance by showing these people in a positive light as examples for others who might be struggling to figure themselves out, and as a reference point for people who didn't know personally anyone in that situation. Cyrus was behind the camera for the entire photoshoot, and interviewed her 14 subjects to share their personal stories. She said she wanted to bring attention to and celebrate people who would not normally find themselves being the stars of a photoshoot or portrayed on the cover of a magazine.<ref>{{cite magazine |title=Miley Cyrus launches Instapride campaign to honor transgender people |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/miley-cyrus-launches-instapride-campaign-to-honor-transgender-people-62976/ |magazine=Rolling Stone  |access-date=October 17, 2018|date=June 15, 2015 }}</ref>

Following the loss of Miley and Hemsworth's Malibu home from the [[Woolsey Fire]], the community and they launched the Malibu Foundation for relief efforts following the [[2018 California wildfires]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://malibufoundation.gvng.org/ |title=Malibu Foundation |work=Malibufoundation.gvng.org |access-date=January 12, 2019 |archive-date=January 12, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190112010803/https://malibufoundation.gvng.org/ |url-status=dead }}</ref> Miley's Happy Hippie Foundation donating $500,000 to the Malibu Foundation.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://malibufoundation.gvng.org/posts/29/details |title=Thank You Miley And Liam! |work=Malibufoundation.gvng.org |date=November 13, 2018 |access-date=January 12, 2019 |archive-date=March 27, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200327151844/https://malibufoundation.gvng.org/posts/29/details |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|first=Antoinette |last=Bueno |url=https://www.etonline.com/miley-cyrus-and-liam-hemsworth-donate-500k-to-malibu-relief-after-losing-home-to-woolsey-fire |title=Miley Cyrus and Liam Hemsworth Donate $500K to Malibu Relief After Losing Home to Woolsey Fire |work=Entertainment Tonight |date=November 13, 2018 |access-date=January 12, 2019}}</ref>

In 2024 Cyrus announced that the foundation would be renamed as Miley Cyrus Foundation.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.wmagazine.com/culture/miley-cyrus-cover-interview-2024|title=Miley Cyrus Finally Gets Her "Flowers"|last=Hawgood|first=Alex|magazine=[[W (magazine)|W]]|date=June 3, 2024|access-date=June 3, 2024}}</ref>

==Cultural impact and status==
[[File:InThisLifeUnderGround.jpg|thumb|upright|Cyrus has been compared to the "Queen of Pop", [[Madonna]], being considered by many as the "Madonna of her generation".<ref name="theguardian.com">{{cite news|date=June 10, 2015|title=Canny and confrontational, Miley Cyrus is this generation's Madonna |first=Rebecca|last=Nicholson|url=http://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2015/jun/10/proper-punk-miley-cyrus-madonna-sexuality|access-date=February 14, 2022|newspaper=The Guardian}}</ref>]]

Cyrus's early success as the face of [[Disney Channel]]'s billion-dollar franchise ''[[Hannah Montana]]''<ref>{{Cite book|last=Steinberg|first=Shirley R.|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=jR-yDwAAQBAJ&pg=PP1|title=Kinderculture: The Corporate Construction of Childhood|date=May 4, 2018|publisher=Routledge|isbn=978-0-429-96364-3}}</ref> played an important role in shaping the 2000s teen pop culture, earning her the honorific nickname of "[[Honorific nicknames in popular music|Teen Queen]]".<ref>{{cite magazine |date=April 6, 2009 |title=Miley Cyrus: Teen Queen |url=https://parade.com/75655/parade/miley-cyrus-3/ |access-date=February 16, 2021 |magazine=[[Parade (magazine)|Parade]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date=June 10, 2013 |title=From Teen Queen to Leading Lady: Miley Cyrus' Sizzlin' Style Through the Years! |url=http://www.etonline.com/gallery/featured/85422_From_Teen_Queen_to_Leading_Lady_Miley_Cyrus_Sizzlin_Style_Through_the_Years/index.html |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130610135948/http://www.etonline.com/gallery/featured/85422_From_Teen_Queen_to_Leading_Lady_Miley_Cyrus_Sizzlin_Style_Through_the_Years/index.html |archive-date=June 10, 2013 |access-date=February 17, 2021 |work=[[Entertainment Tonight]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Kitchener |first=Shaun |date=November 7, 2011 |title=Miley Cyrus Is Dracula's Daughter |url=http://www.entertainmentwise.com/news/64816/Miley-Cyrus-Is-Draculas-Daughter |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130619091256/http://www.entertainmentwise.com/news/64816/Miley-Cyrus-Is-Draculas-Daughter |archive-date=June 19, 2013 |access-date=February 17, 2021 |website=[[Entertainmentwise]]}}</ref> Bickford stated ''Hannah Montana'' adopted a business model of combining celebrity acts with film, television, and popular music for a pre-adolescent audience. He called the series "genre-defining"<ref name=":1">{{Cite journal|last=Bickford|first=Tyler|date=2015|title=Tween Intimacy and the Problem of Public Life in Children's Media: "Having It All" on the Disney Channel's "Hannah Montana"|url=https://www.jstor.org/stable/43958468|journal=Women's Studies Quarterly|volume=43|issue=1/2|pages=66–82|jstor=43958468|issn=0732-1562}}</ref> and likened this model to [[1990s in music|1990s]] [[teen pop]] artists such as [[Britney Spears]] and [[NSYNC]], who were also marketed to children.<ref name=":1" /> Morgan Genevieve Blue of ''Feminist Media Studies'' stated the series' primary female characters, Miley and her alter ego Hannah, are positioned as [[Postfeminism|post-feminist]] subjects in a way their representation is confined to notions of femininity and consumerism.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Blue|first=Morgan Genevieve|date=September 1, 2013|title=The Best of Both Worlds?|url=https://doi.org/10.1080/14680777.2012.724024|journal=Feminist Media Studies|volume=13|issue=4|pages=660–675|doi=10.1080/14680777.2012.724024|s2cid=147354770|issn=1468-0777}}</ref> ''[[The Times]]'' journalist Craig McLean named Cyrus the "world's biggest-ever teenage star".<ref>{{Cite news|last=McLean|first=Craig|title=Why Miley Cyrus is the world's biggest ever teenage star|newspaper=[[The Times]]|url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/why-miley-cyrus-is-the-worlds-biggest-ever-teenage-star-3c282393cr2|access-date=February 17, 2021|issn=0140-0460}}</ref>

During the Best of Both Worlds Tour, tickets were sold out in minutes and stadiums were completely filled making it the highest-grossing concert tour for a new act in 2007 and 2008.<ref name=":4">{{Cite magazine|author=<!--Not stated--> |date=November 20, 2008|title=Springsteen, Chesney Rule Billboard Touring Awards|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/springsteen-chesney-rule-billboard-touring-awards-1043438/|access-date=February 14, 2022|magazine=Billboard}}</ref> According to ''Billboard'' boxscore,<ref>{{Cite magazine|last1=Cohen|first1=Jonathan|date=March 4, 2008|title='Hannah Montana' Tour Heading To CD/DVD|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/hannah-montana-tour-heading-to-cddvd-1046364/|access-date=February 14, 2022|magazine=Billboard}}</ref> the Best of Both Worlds Tour had a total attendance of approximately one million people<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=48SZ4YlqhgEC&q=billboard.biz+boxscore+Miley+Cyrus&pg=PT6|title=Billboard|date=June 27, 2009}}</ref> and grossed over US$54 million, earning Cyrus the award for Breakthrough Act at the 2008 [[Billboard Touring Awards]].<ref name=":4" /> In 2012, ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' ranked Cyrus as one of the top 25 teen idol breakout moments of the rock era, which Andy Greene wrote: "Miley's rise was meteoric. Tickets to her 2007 Best of Both Worlds tour sold out faster than any tour in memory&nbsp;... It seemed like she was poised to become a more stable version of Britney Spears – especially after singles 'The Climb' and 'Party In The USA'".<ref>{{Cite magazine|last1=Greene|first1=Andy|date=May 11, 2012|title=The Top 25 Teen Idol Breakout Moments|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-lists/teen-idol-breakouts-158080/|access-date=February 14, 2022|magazine=Rolling Stone}}</ref> Due to her popularity, [[Paul McCartney]] compared their success to that of [[the Beatles]] in an interview during his tour in 2011. In this regard, he commented: "I think when they have new sensations, like Miley Cyrus or Justin Bieber, teenagers identify with them, in the same way that the boys identified with The Beatles, [...] when you have thousands of teenagers feeling the same, they become elated because they have this love for something in common, whether it is The Beatles, Miley Cyrus, Justin Bieber, or whatever."<ref>{{cite web|title=Puranoticia {{!}} Paul McCartney compara a Miley Cyrus y Justin Bieber con los Beatles|url=https://www.puranoticia.cl/front/contenido/2011/05/08/noticia-3422.php|access-date=February 14, 2022|website=www.puranoticia.cl}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|title=Compara Paul McCartney a Cyrus y Bieber con The Beatles|url=https://www.razon.com.mx/entretenimiento/compara-paul-mccartney-a-cyrus-y-bieber-con-the-beatles/|access-date=February 14, 2022|website=La Razón}}</ref>

Over the years, Cyrus's song "Party in the U.S.A." gained popularity in American culture on holidays and historic events. The song has re-entered the charts every [[Independence Day (United States)|Independence Day]] since its release. Following the [[death of Osama bin Laden]] on May 2, 2011, a resurgence in popularity of the music video occurred. The official [[YouTube]] video was flooded with comments regarding the death of bin Laden and it was immediately deemed a celebratory anthem for the event.<ref>{{cite web|last=Abebe|first=Nitsuh|title=Why Miley Cyrus's 'Party in the U.S.A.' Became the Osama Bin Laden Death Anthem - Slideshow|date=May 2, 2011 |url=https://www.vulture.com/2011/05/why_miley_cyruss_party_in_the.html|access-date=February 17, 2021|work=Vulture}}</ref> In 2013, an online petition on the [[White House]]'s "We the People" petitions website was urging then-president [[Barack Obama]] to change the U.S. national anthem from "[[The Star-Spangled Banner]]" to "Party in the U.S.A."<ref>{{cite news|title=Miley Cyrus Has a 'Party in the U.S.A' in Patriotic Gear for Fourth of July|url=https://people.com/music/miley-cyrus-party-in-the-usa-fourth-of-july/|access-date=February 17, 2021|work=People}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Hernandez|first=Brian Anthony|title=Petition Wants Miley's 'Party in the U.S.A.' to be New National Anthem|date=July 7, 2013|url=https://mashable.com/2013/07/07/miley-cyrus-party-usa/|access-date=February 17, 2021|publisher=Mashable}}</ref> Following the [[2020 United States presidential election|2020 presidential election]], as major news outlets announced [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]] nominee [[Joe Biden]] the winner of the presidential race, on November 7, 2020, supporters in New York City started singing "Party in the U.S.A." at [[Times Square]].<ref>{{cite web|title='Party in the USA': People in America take to streets dancing to celebrate Joe Biden's big victory|url=https://www.timesnownews.com/the-buzz/article/party-in-the-usa-people-in-america-take-to-streets-dancing-to-celebrate-joe-bidens-big-victory/678881|access-date=February 17, 2021|website=timesnownews.com|date=November 8, 2020}}</ref>
[[File:Miley Cyrus figure at Madame Tussauds London (33900187296).jpg|thumb|Miley Cyrus figure at [[Madame Tussauds London]]]]
Cyrus's album ''[[Bangerz]]'' (2013), along with its promotional events, is considered to be one of the most controversial moments in the 2010s wider popular culture and established Cyrus among the decade's most controversial figures.<ref>{{Cite magazine|last=Spanos|first=Brittany|date=May 8, 2017|title=Miley Cyrus' 10 Biggest Scandals|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-lists/miley-cyrus-10-biggest-scandals-108463/|access-date=February 17, 2021|magazine=Rolling Stone}}</ref> ''[[Glamour (magazine)|Glamour]]'' writer Mickey Woods likened the promotional "era" for the album to those of [[Britney Spears]]'s and [[Christina Aguilera]]'s third and fourth studio albums ''[[Britney (album)|Britney]]'' (2001) and ''[[Stripped (Christina Aguilera album)|Stripped]]'' (2002), respectively, adding that Cyrus's record "will probably be retrospectively deemed iconic, maybe even classic".<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Woods|first=Mickey|title=6 Reasons We Love Miley Cyrus' New Album Bangerz|url=https://www.glamour.com/story/we-love-miley-cyrus-new-album|access-date=February 17, 2021|magazine=Glamour|date=October 8, 2013}}</ref> ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' listed ''Bangerz'' as one of the best and most influential albums of the 2010s noting that "with this pivotal album release, Cyrus took control of her public persona, surprising less with her provocative antics than with her constant artistic evolution".<ref>{{Cite magazine|title=The 100 Greatest Albums of the 2010s: Staff Picks|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/list/8543722/best-albums-of-the-2010s-top-100|access-date=February 17, 2021|magazine=Billboard|date=November 19, 2019}}</ref> The album is considered a [[Trendsetting|trendsetter]] in "weaving together urban and pop influences, what's most revered now is what it represented then" according to Lyndsey Havens.<ref name="wcs_2010s">{{Cite magazine|title=Songs That Defined the Decade: Miley Cyrus' 'We Can't Stop'|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/songs-that-defined-the-decade/8544137/miley-cyrus-we-cant-stop-songs-that-defined-the-decade/|access-date=February 17, 2021|magazine=Billboard|date=November 21, 2019}}</ref> Patrick Ryan of ''[[USA Today]]'' commented that Cyrus's collaborations with [[Mike Will Made It]] on the album contributed to his new-found prominence, stating that Mike Will Made It's position as an executive producer has helped him "[jump] to the forefront as an interesting character [...] in an era where a lot of producers have fallen behind the scenes again".<ref>{{cite web|last=Ryan|first=Patrick|title=Thanks to Miley, hitmaker Mike Will made it|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/music/2013/10/07/producer-mike-will-made-it-miley-cyrus-bangerz/2925501/|access-date=February 17, 2021|work=USA Today}}</ref> ''[[Vice (magazine)|Vice]]'' described Cyrus as "the most punk rock musician out there right now" and that she is "spinning circles around every single pop star who is trying to be edgy right now".<ref>{{cite web|last=Ozzi|first=Dan |title= Miley Cyrus is Punk AF |url=https://www.vice.com/en/article/rqwqmr/miley-cyrus-is-punk-as-fuck|access-date=June 11, 2021|work=Vice|date=September 19, 2013}}</ref> [[MTV]] named Cyrus their Best Artist of 2013, and James Montgomery of [[MTV News]] elaborated on the network's decision that Cyrus "[declared] her independence and [dominated] the pop-culture landscape", adding that "she schooled{{mdash}}and shocked{{mdash}}us all in 2013, and did so on her own terms."<ref>{{cite web|author=<!--Not stated-->|title=Best Artists Of 2013|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/1718726/best-artists-2013/|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140520004400/http://www.mtv.com/news/1718726/best-artists-2013/|url-status=dead|archive-date=May 20, 2014|access-date=February 17, 2021|publisher=[[MTV News]]}}</ref> ''Billboard'' staff called Cyrus the "Most Talked About Pop Star" of 2013, and also recognized the controversial evolution of her career as the "Top Music Moment" of the year, elaborating that she was a "maelstrom that expanded and grazed nearly every aspect of pop culture in 2013.";<ref>{{Cite magazine|title=Top 20 Music Moments of 2013|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/list/5847822/top-20-music-moments-of-2013|access-date=February 17, 2021|magazine=Billboard|date=December 19, 2012}}</ref> the publication also listed "We Can't Stop" as best song of 2013 for being "one of the bolder musical choices in recent memory, and that risk paid off tremendously."<ref>{{Cite magazine|title=20 Best Songs of 2013: Critics' Picks|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/list/5840322/20-best-songs-of-2013-critics-picks|access-date=February 17, 2021|magazine=Billboard}}</ref> and one of the songs that defined the decade stating it "created a new play in the playbook" of pop music.<ref name="wcs_2010s" /> The song's music video and her controversial 2013 VMAs performance with Robin Thicke were declared as the 27th greatest music video and one of the most "defining" pop culture moments of the 2010s.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=''Billboard'' Staff |date=November 26, 2019 |title=The 100 Greatest Music Videos of the 2010s: Staff Picks |url=https://www.billboard.com/media/lists/best-music-videos-2010s-top-100-8544596/ |access-date=April 20, 2024 |magazine=Billboard}}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine |last=''Billboard'' Staff |date=December 20, 2019 |title=The 100 Moments That Defined the Decade in Music |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/pop/100-best-music-moments-decade-10s-7873025/ |access-date=April 20, 2024 |magazine=Billboard}}</ref>

In 2015, Rebecca Nicholson from ''The Guardian'' published an article calling Cyrus the [[Madonna]] of her generation, saying that "she's a ''Disney'' survivor with a fluid approach to gender identity. And, like the old three-chord punks, she gives really good quote". According to Nicholson, Cyrus takes "the 90s Madonna approach to public sexuality: it's deliberately provocative, and crucially, it is not being served up for male consumption." Likewise, she defends Cyrus's controversial rebellion, highlighting that behind the character there is a human, talented and strong person who manages to connect with the public, just like the "Queen of Pop".<ref name="theguardian.com"/> In November of the same year, ''Billboard'' cataloged the singer as one of the "Greatest of All Time ''Billboard'' 200 Artists", occupying position thirty-one; she was on the ninth rank among female artists.<ref>{{Cite magazine |date=November 12, 2015 |title=Greatest of All Time ''Billboard'' 200 Artists |url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/greatest-billboard-200-artists/ |access-date=February 14, 2022 |magazine=Billboard}}</ref> In 2017, the aforementioned magazine also published an article naming the singer a "Queer Superhero" for her philanthropic fight for the LGBTQ+ community.<ref>{{Cite magazine|last1=Porter|first1=Zachariah|date=February 26, 2019|title=Miley Cyrus Is a Queer Superhero: 8 Times She Showed Love to the LGBTQ Community|url=https://www.billboard.com/culture/pride/miley-cyrus-queer-lgbtq-drag-race-7933969/|access-date=February 14, 2022|magazine=Billboard}}</ref> In 2019, ''Billboard'' ranked her 62nd on its "Greatest of All Time Artists" chart,<ref>{{cite magazine |title=Greatest of All Time Artists |url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/greatest-of-all-time-artists |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191114170915/https://www.billboard.com/charts/greatest-of-all-time-artists |archive-date=November 14, 2019 |access-date=April 19, 2024 |magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]}}</ref> and 55th on the [[Billboard Decade-End#2010s|2010s decade-end chart of Top Artists]], signifying the most successful acts of the decade.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Trust |first=Gary |date=November 14, 2019 |title=The Decade in Charts: Mark & Bruno's 'Uptown Funk!' Rules Hot 100 & Adele's '21' Tops ''Billboard'' 200 |url=https://www.billboard.com/pro/decade-in-charts-2010s-hot-100-billboard-200/ |url-access=subscription |access-date=April 20, 2024 |magazine=Billboard}}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine |date=November 14, 2019 |title=Decade-End Charts: Top Artists (2010s) |url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/decade-end/top-artists/ |url-access=subscription |access-date=April 20, 2024 |magazine=Billboard}}</ref>

