* {{Cite web |last=Karl |first=Abigail |date=October 19, 2023 |title=From Disney Darling to Pop Icon: Miley Cyrus' Evolution |url=https://whatstrending.com/from-disney-darling-to-pop-icon-miley-cyrus-evolution/ |access-date=June 4, 2024 |website=[[What's Trending]] }}</ref><ref name="greatestpop2023">{{Cite magazine |last=Atkinson |first=Katie |date=December 8, 2023 |title=Billboard's Greatest Pop Stars of 2023: Comeback Artist of the Year — Miley Cyrus |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/pop/miley-cyrus-greatest-pop-star-2023-comeback-of-the-year-1235547218/ |access-date=June 6, 2024 |magazine=Billboard}}</ref> with the [[BBC]] calling her "the ultimate 21st century pop star".<ref>{{Cite web |last=Levine |first=Nick |date=March 10, 2023 |title=Why Miley Cyrus is the ultimate 21st-Century pop star |url=https://www.bbc.com/culture/article/20230309-why-miley-cyrus-is-the-ultimate-21st-century-pop-star |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230310010813/https://www.bbc.com/culture/article/20230309-why-miley-cyrus-is-the-ultimate-21st-century-pop-star |archive-date=March 10, 2023 |access-date=March 10, 2023 |work=[[BBC Online|BBC Culture]]}}</ref> ''Billboard'' included Cyrus in its "Greatest Pop Stars of 2023" listicle, naming her the "Comeback Artist of the Year". The magazine noted that her 2023 single "Flowers"—"the biggest chart smash of her career"—"re-established [Cyrus] as one of pop's foremost hitmakers" and led to a commercial resurgence.<ref name="greatestpop2023"/> In 2024, at age 31, Cyrus became the youngest recipient of the [[Disney Legends]] award, for her outstanding contributions to the Walt Disney Company.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Stephan |first=Katcy |date=August 11, 2024 |title=Miley Cyrus Honored as Youngest-Ever Disney Legend at D23: 'It's Legendary to Be Afraid and Do It Anyway' |url=https://variety.com/2024/music/news/miley-cyrus-disney-legend-d23-1236101271/ |access-date=August 12, 2024 |magazine=Variety}}</ref>

Artists that have cited Cyrus or her work as inspiration or an influence include [[Chappell Roan]],<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Kaufman |first=Gil |date=August 13, 2024 |title=Chappell Roan Praises Miley Cyrus for Inspiration, Making Music That's 'So Authentic' in 2024 Disney Legends Ceremony Intro |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/pop/chappell-roan-praises-miley-cyrus-music-so-authentic-2024-disney-legends-ceremony-1235751977/ |access-date=August 26, 2024 |magazine=Billboard}}</ref> [[JoJo Siwa]],<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Kiley |first=Rachel |date=April 2, 2024 |title=JoJo Siwa wants her own Miley Cyrus ''Bangerz'' rebranding moment |url=https://www.out.com/gay-music/jojo-siwa-karma-miley-cyrus-bangerz-inspiration/ |access-date=April 19, 2024 |magazine=[[Out (magazine)|Out]]}}</ref> [[Lea Michele]],<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Ayers|first=Mike|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/5923073/lea-michele-interview-louder-album-cory-monteith-glee|title=Lea Michele Q&A: Talks 'Difficult' Cory Song, Finding Her Voice and Life After 'Glee'|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=March 3, 2014|access-date=August 26, 2024}}</ref> [[Lil Nas X]],<ref>{{Cite magazine |first=Tomás |last=Mier |date=September 15, 2021 |title=Lil Nas X Says Miley Cyrus Doesn't 'Even Realize How Much of a Legend' She Is: 'I Really Admire Her' |url=https://people.com/music/lil-nas-x-says-miley-cyrus-doesnt-even-realize-how-much-of-a-legend-she-is/ |magazine=People |access-date=September 23, 2021 |archive-date=September 25, 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210925103537/https://people.com/music/lil-nas-x-says-miley-cyrus-doesnt-even-realize-how-much-of-a-legend-she-is/ |url-status=live}}</ref> and [[Troye Sivan]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Barlow |first=Eve |title=Troye Sivan |url=https://www.wonderlandmagazine.com/2018/05/04/troye-sivan/ |magazine=Wonderland |access-date=April 18, 2023 |date=May 4, 2018}}</ref>

